61\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q39) dates</span></strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"> and so on</span><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"461\">.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Okay, so then we come to modern times. And in the 1940s, a remarkable series of studies was conducted with a man known simply as S. <span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Psychologists found that S never made notes about anything, although he was a</span><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"132\"> </strong></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">(Q40) journalist</strong></span>, and never forgot facts. The researchers concluded that S had an unusual medical condition which meant he developed incredible memory skills. This was important as it seemed to support the ideas of the ancient Greeks and other much earlier scholars. But in the later part of the 20th century, the focus switched to computers.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Okay well, that''s the historical context. Let''s now turn to...</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fbd3151c-b899-4ec9-b4fd-026275318817', '784abe17-25a4-4988-bebd-1bbbba08ffff', 'radio', 'Questions 36–40', '', '<p data-start="2019" data-end="2063">Choose the correct letter, <strong data-start="2046" data-end="2062">A, B, C or D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. The different layers of sediment have been mixed over time"}, {"option_text": "B. The sand evidence is unhelpful and should be disregarded"}, {"option_text": "C. The area needs to be re-examined when technology improves"}, {"option_text": "D. The charcoal found in the area cannot be dated"}], "question": "What conclusions did the writers reach about the inconsistencies in the data from Cuddie Springs?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Floods could have caused the death of the megafauna"}, {"option_text": "B. Floods could have disturbed the archaeological evidence"}, {"option_text": "C. Bushfires could have prevented humans from settling in the area for any length of time"}, {"option_text": "D. Bushfires could have destroyed much of the evidence left by megafauna and humans"}], "question": "According to the writers, what impact could a natural phenomenon have had on this site?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. They bred cattle whose bones could have been confused with megafauna"}, {"option_text": "B. They found that the soil was too waterlogged for farming"}, {"option_text": "C. They allowed cattle to move around freely at the site"}, {"option_text": "D. They brought stones there from another area"}], "question": "What did the writers speculate about the people who lived at this site in 1876?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. A rapid change in climate may have been responsible for the extinction of the megafauna"}, {"option_text": "B. Megafauna could have died out as a result of small numbers being killed year after year"}, {"option_text": "C. The population of humans at that time was probably insufficient to cause the extinction of the megafauna"}, {"option_text": "D. The extinction of ancient animals should not be compared to that of modern-day species"}], "question": "In the final paragraph, what suggestion do the writers make about Australia’s megafauna?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Their methods were not well thought out"}, {"option_text": "B. The excavations did not go deep enough"}, {"option_text": "C. Their technology failed to obtain precise data"}, {"option_text": "D. Their conclusions were based on inconsistent data"}], "question": "Which of the following best represents the writers’ criticism of Field and Wroe?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. A — The different layers of sediment have been mixed over time.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“These points suggest strongly that the sediments have been moved about and some of the old charcoal has been re-deposited in younger layers.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ những điểm bất nhất về tuổi thọ giữa cát và than củi, tác giả kết luận rằng các lớp trầm tích đã bị dịch chuyển qua lại (<em data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">moved about</em>) và tái tích tụ lại, tức là chúng đã bị trộn lẫn vào nhau theo thời gian (<strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"222\">mixed over time</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. B — Floods could have disturbed the archaeological evidence.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Flood events more likely explain the accumulation of megafauna remains, and could have mixed old bones with fresh deposits.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả cho rằng hiện tượng thiên nhiên là các trận lũ hoang dã (<em data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">Flood events</em>) có thể đã làm xáo trộn, trộn lẫn xương cũ với các trầm tích mới (<em data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">mixed old bones with fresh deposits</em>), tức là làm nhiễu loạn các bằng chứng khảo cổ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"240\">disturbed the archaeological evidence</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. D — They brought stones there from another area.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“...we speculate that the graziers made sure it was protected from damage... by lining the surface with small stones collected from further afield...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả suy đoán những người chăn nuôi gia súc năm 1876 đã bảo vệ giếng nước bằng cách rải lên bề mặt các viên đá nhỏ được thu lượm từ những nơi xa hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"165\">collected from further afield / brought stones there from another area</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. B — Megafauna could have died out as a result of small numbers being killed year after year.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Using a mathematical model, it was found that a group of 10 people killing only one juvenile Diprotodon each year would be sufficient to bring about the extinction of that species within 1,000 years.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mô hình toán học chỉ ra chỉ cần một nhóm 10 người giết <em data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">chỉ một</em> con đại động vật non mỗi năm (<em data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">killing only one... each year</em>) là đủ để làm loài đó tuyệt chủng trong 1,000 năm. Ý này tương ứng với việc chết dần do một số lượng nhỏ bị giết từ năm này qua năm khác (<strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"273\">small numbers being killed year after year</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. D — Their conclusions were based on inconsistent data.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“We carried out a reanalysis of the scientific data from Cuddie Springs that brings into question their conclusions.”</em> và <em data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">“However, our analysis revealed a number of inconsistencies.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lời chỉ trích lớn nhất và xuyên suốt của tác giả đối với Field và Wroe là các kết luận của họ không vững chắc, bởi vì khi phân tích lại dữ liệu khoa học thì phát hiện ra rất nhiều điểm mâu thuẫn, bất hợp lý (<strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"220\">based on inconsistent data / a number of inconsistencies</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('236c3fc1-6162-4c37-ab90-06c804b30869', '7f431135-bc3d-4ad3-8e56-1886656104df', 'matching', 'Questions 14–20', '', '<p>Reading Passage 2 has seven sections, <strong>A–G</strong>.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each section from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Write the correct number,<strong> i-viii</strong>, in boxes 14-20 on your answer sheet. </p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i      How new clothing styles are created"}, {"optionText": "ii     The rise of the fashion industry"}, {"optionText": "iii    Joining the garment pieces together"}, {"optionText": "iv    Producing materials with a range of features"}, {"optionText": "v     The importance of the fashion industry"}, {"optionText": "vi    Factors affecting international commerce"}, {"optionText": "vii   The attractions of becoming a fashion model"}, {"optionText": "viii Making patterns for people with different figures"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Section 1 (Đoạn A) — {v. The importance of the fashion industry}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The fashion industry is a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">multibillion-dollar global enterprise</strong>... by any measure, the industry <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">accounts for a significant share of world economic output</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này đưa ra các số liệu và khẳng định tầm vóc của ngành thời trang: là một doanh nghiệp toàn cầu trị giá nhiều tỷ đô-la và chiếm một phần đáng kể trong sản lượng kinh tế thế giới. Điều này làm nổi bật tầm quan trọng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"233\">The importance</strong>) về mặt kinh tế của ngành.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Section 2 (Đoạn B) — {ii. The rise of the fashion industry}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The fashion industry is a product of the modern age. <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">Prior to the mid-19th century</strong>, virtually all clothing was handmade... <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">By the beginning of the 20th century</strong>, with the development of new technologies... clothing had increasingly come to be <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"254\">mass-produced</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn phác họa lại dòng lịch sử phát triển của ngành thời trang từ giữa thế kỷ XIX (chỉ may tay cho cá nhân) cho đến đầu thế kỷ XX (bùng nổ công nghệ, máy may, sản xuất hàng loạt). Tiến trình lịch sử này chính là sự trỗi dậy/phát triển (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"252\">The rise</strong>) của ngành.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Section 3 (Đoạn C) — {iv. Producing materials with a range of features}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...fabrics made from both natural fibres and synthetic fibres... are produced... In addition, high-tech synthetic fabrics <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">confer such properties as moisture absorption, stain resistance, retention or dissipation of body heat, and protection against fire... hazards</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Materials\" (nguyên liệu) ở đây chính là các loại vải (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">fabrics/fibres</em>). Đoạn văn tập trung nói về việc sản xuất ra các loại vải có nhiều đặc tính/tính năng đặc biệt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">a range of features</strong>) như: hút ẩm, chống bẩn, giữ/tỏa nhiệt, chống cháy, chống tia UV...</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Section 4 (Đoạn D) — {i. How new clothing styles are created}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The vast majority of <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">designers</strong> work anonymously... <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">adapting designs into marketable garments</strong> for average consumers. They <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">draw inspiration from a wide range of sources</strong>... traditional design methods... have been supplemented or replaced by <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"250\">computer-assisted design techniques</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Toàn bộ đoạn này giải thích quy trình thiết kế trang phục: các nhà thiết kế lấy cảm hứng từ đâu, họ biến đổi các thiết kế thành sản phẩm thương mại như thế nào, và cách họ dùng công nghệ máy tính vẽ phác thảo. Đây chính là quy trình tạo ra các mẫu quần áo mới (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"273\">How new clothing styles are created</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Section 5 (Đoạn E) — {viii. Making patterns for people with different figures}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn </strong><strong>chứng</strong><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">“An important stage in garment production is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">translation of the clothing design into templates, in a range of sizes</strong>... Because the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">proportions of the human body change with increases or decreases in weight, templates cannot simply be scaled up or down</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Templates\" ở đây chính là các mẫu rập/khuôn mẫu để cắt vải (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">patterns</strong>). Đoạn văn nói về sự khó khăn khi thiết kế rập cho nhiều kích cỡ khác nhau do tỷ lệ cơ thể người thay đổi theo cân nặng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">people with different figures</strong> - người có vóc dáng khác nhau).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Section 6 (Đoạn F) — {iii. Joining the garment pieces together}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The next stage of production is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">assembly process</strong>... Technological innovation... has resulted in the automation of some stages of assembly. Nevertheless, <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">the fundamental process of sewing remains labour-intensive</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Assembly process\" (quá trình lắp ráp) và \"sewing\" (khâu/may) các mảnh vải lại với nhau chính là hành động ráp các mảnh quần áo lại thành một sản phẩm hoàn chỉnh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"175\">Joining the garment pieces together</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Section 7 (Đoạn G) — {vi. Factors affecting international commerce}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">trade in textiles and garments</strong> was strictly regulated by purchasing countries, which <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">imposed quotas and tariffs</strong>. Since the 1980s, these protectionist measures... have gradually been abandoned. They have been replaced by a <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"237\">free-trade approach</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"International commerce\" (thương mại quốc tế) đồng nghĩa với \"trade in textiles and garments\" (buôn bán dệt may toàn cầu). Các yếu tố ảnh hưởng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">Factors affecting</strong>) được liệt kê rõ bao gồm: hạn ngạch (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"212\">quotas</em>), thuế quan (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"232\">tariffs</em>), các biện pháp bảo hộ và hiệp định tự do thương mại (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"294\">free-trade approach</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e3f8be84-e168-4102-bd61-d28b14e0f83b', '7261888e-0e11-43bc-92ed-f7823fafa601', 'fillup', 'Questions 5–13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="7">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 5–13 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="12"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">New Evidence on Sleep Patterns</strong></span></p>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="0">New ideas about napping</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="14">
<li>
<p>scientists have recorded an afternoon drop in {energy}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>studies of hunter-gatherer societies show that napping was rare and occurred more often during the {summer} the devices may not have detected {short} naps</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="15" data-index-in-node="0">Daily activity cycles</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="16">
<li>
<p>the tribespeople went to sleep several hours after sunset</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>even with {fires} there was little light</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>tribespeople usually woke up around {sunrise}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>scientists found that {temperature} had almost as much influence on sleep patterns as light</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="17" data-index-in-node="0">Differences between tribespeople and people in industrialised regions</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="18">
<li>
<p>{sleeplessness} is something that very few of the tribespeople suffered from</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>the environment of tribespeople may have been more suitable for sleep</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>tribespeople had better fitness than industrialised populations and were not {overweight}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>tribespeople also had stronger {hearts}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. energy — {scientists have recorded an afternoon drop in energy}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Scientists have documented that people’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">energy</strong> often falls in the mid-afternoon.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “documented” đồng nghĩa với “recorded” (ghi nhận). “Mid-afternoon” tương ứng với “afternoon”. Các nhà khoa học đã ghi nhận sự sụt giảm năng lượng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">energy</strong>) vào giữa buổi chiều.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. summer — {napping was rare and occurred more often during the summer}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The researchers estimated that naps may have occurred on up to 7 percent of winter days and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">22 percent of summer days</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc ngủ trưa rất hiếm, nhưng số liệu cho thấy tỉ lệ ngủ trưa ở mùa hè (22%) cao hơn hẳn mùa đông (7%). Do đó, nó xảy ra thường xuyên hơn vào mùa hè (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">summer</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. short — {the devices may not have detected short naps}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…so it is possible that some of the study subjects took <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">naps that were short</strong>, perhaps 15 minutes or less.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thiết bị của họ chỉ phát hiện được những giấc ngủ dài, vì vậy có thể họ đã bỏ lỡ những giấc ngủ ngắn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">short</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. fires — {even with fires there was little light}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“All three tribes had <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">fires</strong> going, but the light itself was much lower than you might get from a light bulb.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù các bộ lạc đều có đốt lửa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">fires</strong>), nhưng lượng ánh sáng tỏa ra vẫn rất thấp so với bóng đèn hiện đại.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. sunrise — {tribespeople usually woke up around sunrise}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“They did, however, have a tendency to wake up anywhere between an hour before and an hour after <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">sunrise</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các bộ lạc có xu hướng thức dậy trong khoảng 1 tiếng trước hoặc sau khi mặt trời mọc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">sunrise</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. temperature — {temperature had almost as much influence… as light}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…looking into the significance of <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">temperature</strong>. They found that it also played a big role, though it was <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">somewhat less important than light</strong> in influencing sleep patterns.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhiệt độ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">temperature</strong>) đóng vai trò lớn, chỉ kém quan trọng hơn ánh sáng một chút trong việc ảnh hưởng đến giấc ngủ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. sleeplessness — {sleeplessness is something that very few… suffered from}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Importantly, almost none of them were troubled by <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">sleeplessness</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Almost none” đồng nghĩa với “very few”. Chứng mất ngủ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">sleeplessness</strong>) là thứ mà rất ít người trong các bộ lạc này gặp phải.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. overweight — {tribespeople… were not overweight}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Not a single one is <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">overweight</strong>, indicating their overall higher levels of physical fitness.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Không một ai trong số họ bị thừa cân (<strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">overweight</strong>), chứng tỏ họ có thể chất tốt hơn người hiện đại.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. hearts — {tribespeople also had stronger hearts}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“They also tended to have healthier <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">hearts</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Healthier” đồng nghĩa với “stronger” trong ngữ cảnh này. Họ có trái tim (<strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">hearts</strong>) khỏe mạnh hơn.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('39c5377d-d64e-4a65-95ca-607cc4e184bb', '76bdd23b-3a55-439e-bc53-38c8ecd65cfd', 'radio', 'Questions 27–31', '', '<p>Choose the correct answer</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "oppose the views of Charles Darwin"}, {"option_text": "compare experts’ opinions of Darwin’s theory"}, {"option_text": "explain the theory of evolutionary psychology"}, {"option_text": "name experts in the field of evolutionary psychology"}], "question": "The writer’s purpose in the first paragraph is to"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "Our characters determine our career choices"}, {"option_text": "We begin life without any predispositions"}, {"option_text": "Our interests and skills depend on our environment"}, {"option_text": "We inherit ideas and characteristics from our ancestors"}], "question": "In the third paragraph, which view about evolutionary psychology matches Nicholson’s opinion?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "criticise primitive survival strategies"}, {"option_text": "explain attitudes and actions at work"}, {"option_text": "demonstrate the slowness of evolution"}, {"option_text": "suggest companies today are poorly structured"}], "question": "The writer discusses the key element of emotion in order to"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "Companies will remain in city centres"}, {"option_text": "Promotion will no longer motivate people"}, {"option_text": "Employees will be less independent than now"}, {"option_text": "Social interaction will remain important to workers"}], "question": "Which of the following does Nicholson predict will happen in the business world?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "How successful companies manage change"}, {"option_text": "Understanding the origins of workplace behaviour"}, {"option_text": "Darwin’s theories rejected by modern management"}, {"option_text": "Why post-industrial organisations need to evolve more quickly"}], "question": "Which of the following is the most suitable title for Part 3?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"140\" data-end=\"198\"><strong data-start=\"144\" data-end=\"198\">27. explain the theory of evolutionary psychology.</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"200\" data-end=\"220\"><strong data-start=\"200\" data-end=\"211\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 1</p>\n<p data-start=\"222\" data-end=\"380\"><strong data-start=\"222\" data-end=\"236\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"236\" data-end=\"239\">“Darwinian evolutionary theory is the foundation of a new wave of ideas… these ideas have been given the title of ‘evolutionary psychology’.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"382\" data-end=\"544\"><strong data-start=\"382\" data-end=\"397\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"397\" data-end=\"400\">Đoạn 1 giới thiệu và giải thích evolutionary psychology là gì → không phản đối Darwin, không so sánh quan điểm, mà chủ yếu giải thích khái niệm.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"546\" data-end=\"549\">\n<p data-start=\"551\" data-end=\"619\"><strong data-start=\"555\" data-end=\"619\">28. We inherit ideas and characteristics from our ancestors.</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"621\" data-end=\"641\"><strong data-start=\"621\" data-end=\"632\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3</p>\n<p data-start=\"643\" data-end=\"781\"><strong data-start=\"643\" data-end=\"657\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"657\" data-end=\"660\">“our brains… have an inherited evolutionary design…”<br data-start=\"712\" data-end=\"715\">“the brain actually houses a store of knowledge when we are born…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"783\" data-end=\"928\"><strong data-start=\"783\" data-end=\"798\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"798\" data-end=\"801\">Nicholson bác bỏ ý tưởng “blank page” và cho rằng chúng ta sinh ra đã có sẵn kiến thức và khuynh hướng → thừa hưởng từ tổ tiên.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"930\" data-end=\"933\">\n<p data-start=\"935\" data-end=\"985\"><strong data-start=\"939\" data-end=\"985\">29. explain attitudes and actions at work.</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"987\" data-end=\"1020\"><strong data-start=\"987\" data-end=\"998\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn nói về emotion</p>\n<p data-start=\"1022\" data-end=\"1123\"><strong data-start=\"1022\" data-end=\"1036\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1036\" data-end=\"1039\">“Emotion… continues to be our radar, guiding us throughout today’s… business world.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"1125\" data-end=\"1263\"><strong data-start=\"1125\" data-end=\"1140\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"1140\" data-end=\"1143\">Tác giả nói về cảm xúc để giải thích hành vi và thái độ nơi làm việc, không phải để phê phán hay nói về tốc độ tiến hóa.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"1265\" data-end=\"1268\">\n<p data-start=\"1270\" data-end=\"1334\"><strong data-start=\"1274\" data-end=\"1334\">30. Social interaction will remain important to workers.</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"1336\" data-end=\"1359\"><strong data-start=\"1336\" data-end=\"1347\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn cuối</p>\n<p data-start=\"1361\" data-end=\"1479\"><strong data-start=\"1361\" data-end=\"1375\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1375\" data-end=\"1378\">“people will still want to meet each other face-to-face.”<br data-start=\"1435\" data-end=\"1438\">“working from home leaves them isolated…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"1481\" data-end=\"1585\"><strong data-start=\"1481\" data-end=\"1496\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"1496\" data-end=\"1499\">Nicholson cho rằng con người vẫn muốn gặp trực tiếp → tương tác xã hội vẫn quan trọng.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"1587\" data-end=\"1590\">\n<p data-start=\"1592\" data-end=\"1652\"><strong data-start=\"1596\" data-end=\"1652\">31. Understanding the origins of workplace behaviour</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"1654\" data-end=\"1674\"><strong data-start=\"1654\" data-end=\"1665\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2</p>\n<p data-start=\"1676\" data-end=\"1820\"><strong data-start=\"1676\" data-end=\"1691\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"1691\" data-end=\"1694\">Đoạn 2 nói về việc evolutionary psychology giúp hiểu vì sao con người cư xử như vậy tại nơi làm việc → hiểu nguồn gốc hành vi.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('98303ca0-d161-4936-bc38-9415d6b2fb9b', 'c25bcc60-1928-436c-8413-e24c68cc70b0', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-40', '<p data-path-to-node="3">Complete the notes below.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="3">Write <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="48">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="5"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="0">Music Education</strong></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="6"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0">Background</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="7">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,0,0">General feelings towards music education are {negative}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,0">Nowadays there''s no need to go to a formal performance to hear music.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,2,0">The speaker heard music made with bottles hit by a fork.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,3,0">You can listen to music in a shop, a bus station, a café, or a {gallery}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,4,0">It''s not necessary to have {talent}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,5,0">Babies love music being played to them.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,6,0">People in {prison} benefited from putting on a musical.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,7,0">in order to get pleasure from music.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="8"><strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="0">Main advantages of music in education</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="9">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,0,0">Teachers can use music as a {link} with the lives of young people</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,1,0">Children''s confidence increases, as well as their {concentration}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="10"><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">Specific examples</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="11">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="11,0,0">Impressive project in Venezuela for disadvantaged young people.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="11,1,0">In Scotland, children''s {mathematics} skills increased.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="11,2,0">Very young children learnt a foreign language by {singing}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="11,3,0">Children who had recorder lessons in groups became better at {teamwork}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="12"><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">Children with disabilities</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="13">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="13,0,0">The deaf are usually taught to play a {drum} before other instruments.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="13,1,0">Blind children sometimes have instinctive musical ability.</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cc337207-39ec-4577-974d-1f9574cf75d7', '76bdd23b-3a55-439e-bc53-38c8ecd65cfd', 'radio', 'Questions 32–35', '', '<p data-start="1563" data-end="1797">Choose <strong data-start="1570" data-end="1577">YES</strong> if the statement agrees with the views of the writer in the text, choose <strong data-start="1651" data-end="1657">NO</strong> if the statement contradicts the views of the writer, or choose <strong data-start="1722" data-end="1735">NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Nicholson makes a persuasive argument in his book"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Tooby and Cosmides believe natural selection through the generations has prepared our minds well for the modern workplace"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Our reliance on technology causes emotional problems in the workplace"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "People today are more trusting than they used to be"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"1880\" data-end=\"1895\"><strong data-start=\"1884\" data-end=\"1895\">32. YES</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"1897\" data-end=\"1984\"><strong data-start=\"1897\" data-end=\"1911\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1911\" data-end=\"1914\">“It is an effective approach explaining why people behave as they do…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"1986\" data-end=\"2073\"><strong data-start=\"1986\" data-end=\"2001\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2001\" data-end=\"2004\">Tác giả đánh giá sách là hiệu quả → đồng ý rằng lập luận thuyết phục.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2075\" data-end=\"2078\">\n<p data-start=\"2080\" data-end=\"2094\"><strong data-start=\"2084\" data-end=\"2094\">33. NO</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2096\" data-end=\"2177\"><strong data-start=\"2096\" data-end=\"2110\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2110\" data-end=\"2113\">“there have not been enough generations for a brain… to evolve…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2179\" data-end=\"2285\"><strong data-start=\"2179\" data-end=\"2194\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2194\" data-end=\"2197\">Tooby và Cosmides nói não bộ chưa thích nghi với đời sống hiện đại → trái với statement.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2287\" data-end=\"2290\">\n<p data-start=\"2292\" data-end=\"2313\"><strong data-start=\"2296\" data-end=\"2313\">34. NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2315\" data-end=\"2452\"><strong data-start=\"2315\" data-end=\"2330\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2330\" data-end=\"2333\">Bài nói business world nhấn mạnh lý trí hơn cảm xúc, nhưng không nói công nghệ gây vấn đề cảm xúc → không đủ thông tin.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2454\" data-end=\"2457\">\n<p data-start=\"2459\" data-end=\"2473\"><strong data-start=\"2463\" data-end=\"2473\">35. NO</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2475\" data-end=\"2561\"><strong data-start=\"2475\" data-end=\"2489\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2489\" data-end=\"2492\">“it takes very little to trigger people’s innate distrust of others…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2563\" data-end=\"2652\"><strong data-start=\"2563\" data-end=\"2578\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2578\" data-end=\"2581\">Con người vẫn có xu hướng nghi ngờ → không phải ngày nay tin tưởng hơn.</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5c9f243b-8aa7-4e92-9d00-dab1422fc326', '6724fea2-58e5-4d49-b6f5-e97ea571208f', 'matrix', 'Questions 1–4', '', '<p>Write the correct letter <strong>A–H</strong> in boxes 1–4 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p><strong>NB</strong>: You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The reason why museum directors need to constantly alter and update their exhibits.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Mention of the length of time people will queue up to see a blockbuster.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Terms that people have used when referring to blockbusters.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "The various ways that institutions like museums get financial support.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. The reason why museum directors need to constantly alter and update their exhibits. — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Maintaining and increasing visitor levels is thus paramount and involves not only creating or hiring blockbuster exhibitions but providing <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"151\">regular exhibition changes and innovations</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vì bảo tàng hoạt động dưới hệ thống đa nguồn vốn (plural funding), việc duy trì và tăng lượng khách là ưu tiên hàng đầu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">paramount</strong>). Để làm được điều đó, họ phải liên tục thay đổi và đổi mới các buổi triển lãm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Mention of the length of time people will queue up to see a blockbuster. — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“A blockbuster is a ‘large-scale loan exhibition that people who normally don’t go to museums will <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">stand in line for hours</strong> to see’…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Stand in line for hours” (xếp hàng hàng giờ đồng hồ) chính là thông tin về khoảng thời gian (length of time) mà mọi người sẵn sàng chờ đợi (queue up) để xem triển lãm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Terms that people have used when referring to blockbusters. — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the words that are starting to appear in some descriptions of blockbusters are <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">‘less scholarly,’ ‘non-elitist,’ and ‘populist’</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các từ (words/terms) được dùng để gọi hoặc mô tả về blockbuster bao gồm: ít tính học thuật (less scholarly), không dành cho giới thượng lưu (non-elitist) và mang tính đại chúng (populist).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. The various ways that institutions like museums get financial support. — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Museums… currently operate under a system of <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">plural funding</strong>: revenue raised through <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">contributions by federal, state, and/or local governments</strong>, combined with revenue raised through <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">admission charges and other activities</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C liệt kê các cách thức (various ways) bảo tàng nhận hỗ trợ tài chính (financial support): từ ngân sách chính phủ các cấp cho đến phí vào cửa và các hoạt động kinh doanh khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('65efaeed-1a74-4449-9edd-e2a44c1cb87d', '76bdd23b-3a55-439e-bc53-38c8ecd65cfd', 'matching', 'Questions 36–40', '', '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words. Choose the correct answer and move it into the gap.</p>
<p> </p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p data-start=\"2380\" data-end=\"2424\">Nicholson’s advice to the corporate world</p>\n<p data-start=\"2426\" data-end=\"2997\">Nicholson believes that if we know why people act the way they do, we can change <strong data-start=\"2507\" data-end=\"2520\">{business environments}</strong> so employees will work more efficiently. Nicholson’s ideas are unwelcome to <strong data-start=\"2597\" data-end=\"2610\">{MBA graduates}</strong> but some executives are more open to what evolutionary psychology says. However, these executives still believe that there is a <strong data-start=\"2739\" data-end=\"2752\">{magic formula}</strong> that will make employees act according to the company’s policies. According to Nicholson, these senior executives are engaging in <strong data-start=\"2883\" data-end=\"2896\">{back-to-front thinking}</strong> and we should not try to change <strong data-start=\"2929\" data-end=\"2942\">{human nature}</strong>, but instead we should change our business structures.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2999\" data-end=\"3013\"> </p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "business leaders"}, {"optionText": "MBA graduates"}, {"optionText": "promotion structures"}, {"optionText": "reward strategy"}, {"optionText": "magic formula"}, {"optionText": "strategic planning"}, {"optionText": "back-to-front thinking"}, {"optionText": "business environments"}, {"optionText": "human nature"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"2710\" data-end=\"2743\"><strong data-start=\"2714\" data-end=\"2743\">36. business environments</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2745\" data-end=\"2811\"><strong data-start=\"2745\" data-end=\"2759\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2759\" data-end=\"2762\">“it is possible to mould corporate environments…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2813\" data-end=\"2846\">→ Thay đổi môi trường kinh doanh.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2848\" data-end=\"2851\">\n<p data-start=\"2853\" data-end=\"2878\"><strong data-start=\"2857\" data-end=\"2878\">37. MBA graduates</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2880\" data-end=\"2946\"><strong data-start=\"2880\" data-end=\"2894\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2894\" data-end=\"2897\">“One group that resists… is young MBA graduates…”</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2948\" data-end=\"2951\">\n<p data-start=\"2953\" data-end=\"2978\"><strong data-start=\"2957\" data-end=\"2978\">38. magic formula</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2980\" data-end=\"3036\"><strong data-start=\"2980\" data-end=\"2994\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2994\" data-end=\"2997\">“cling to the idea of a magic formula…”</p>\n<hr data-start=\"3038\" data-end=\"3041\">\n<p data-start=\"3043\" data-end=\"3077\"><strong data-start=\"3047\" data-end=\"3077\">39. back-to-front thinking</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"3079\" data-end=\"3133\"><strong data-start=\"3079\" data-end=\"3093\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"3093\" data-end=\"3096\">“But that is back-to-front thinking…”</p>\n<hr data-start=\"3135\" data-end=\"3138\">\n<p data-start=\"3140\" data-end=\"3164\"><strong data-start=\"3144\" data-end=\"3164\">40. human nature</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"3166\" data-end=\"3268\"><strong data-start=\"3166\" data-end=\"3180\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"3180\" data-end=\"3183\">“we should be reinventing our business structures, not our fundamental human nature.”</p>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c34abd62-d97d-4085-b89d-8c1e0ef42183', '6724fea2-58e5-4d49-b6f5-e97ea571208f', 'checkbox', 'Questions 9 and 10', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> letters, A–E.</p>
<p>Write the correct letters in boxes 9 and 10 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A. Some of the money they raise can be used for structural repairs."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. They can provide funds to help support amateur artists."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C. Local services benefit from the extra business they bring about."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D. They encourage overseas workers into the local area."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E. They raise employee performance levels."}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. A. Some of the money they raise can be used for structural repairs. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“For museums in some countries, it may be the money that they require to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">replace parts of their collections or to fix buildings that are in need of attention</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “fix buildings that are in need of attention” (sửa chữa các tòa nhà cần được quan tâm/tu sửa) chính là việc sửa chữa cấu trúc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">structural repairs</strong>) được nhắc đến trong câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. C. Local services benefit from the extra business they bring about. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…blockbusters mean crowds, and crowds are good for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">local economy, providing increased trade for shops, hotels, restaurants, the transport industry, and retailers</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc tăng trưởng kinh doanh (increased trade) cho các cửa hàng, khách sạn, nhà hàng… chính là minh chứng cho việc các dịch vụ địa phương (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">local services</strong>) được hưởng lợi từ lượng khách khổng lồ mà blockbuster mang lại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a256e120-9ddc-4c53-822d-05d0188f7c5e', '6724fea2-58e5-4d49-b6f5-e97ea571208f', 'checkbox', 'Question 11–13', '', '<p>Choose <strong>THREE</strong> letters, A–G.</p>
<p>Write the correct letters in boxes 11–13 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A. They do not suit museum management styles."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. Specialist business advice has to be paid for."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C. They involve an increased workload for personnel."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D. They do not increase overall annual visitor numbers."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "E. They are very tiring to put on."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "F. What is popular in one country may not be popular in another."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "G. The content can be weakened through financial pressure."}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. C. They involve an increased workload for personnel. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Everyone, from general laborers to… administrative staff is <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">required to perform additional tasks</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc mọi nhân viên từ lao động phổ thông đến hành chính đều phải thực hiện các “nhiệm vụ bổ sung” chính là minh chứng cho việc khối lượng công việc tăng lên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">increased workload</strong>) đối với nhân sự (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"207\">personnel</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. E. They are very tiring to put on. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Creating, mounting, or hiring blockbusters is <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">exhausting</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “exhausting” (gây kiệt sức) đồng nghĩa với “very tiring”. Bài đọc khẳng định quá trình chuẩn bị và tổ chức các buổi triển lãm này cực kỳ mệt mỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. G. The content can be weakened through financial pressure. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…pure concentration on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">bottom line</strong> [financial pressure] can <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">squeeze substance out of an exhibition</strong> [weakened content].”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc quá tập trung vào lợi nhuận (bottom line) sẽ làm “vắt kiệt” chất lượng nội dung của buổi triển lãm. “Squeeze substance out” tương ứng với việc nội dung bị làm cho yếu đi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"188\">weakened content</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('583423e0-3996-4d9a-b5c4-7dc3a19508d9', 'a85cdea7-bfce-461c-9c67-6c420c6886d9', 'matching', 'Questions 14-20', '', '<p>Write the correct number, <strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="150">i–ix</strong>, in boxes 14-20 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_paragraph_information', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Ray’s account of his working methods"}, {"optionText": "ii. The botanical expert who inspired Ray"}, {"optionText": "iii. A succession of academic achievements"}, {"optionText": "iv. Ray’s informal tuition"}, {"optionText": "v. Ray’s appreciation of his contemporary academic culture"}, {"optionText": "vi. A childhood interest in plants"}, {"optionText": "vii. Plans for a bold new project"}, {"optionText": "viii. A description of the content of Ray’s first book"}, {"optionText": "ix. A change of direction for Ray"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Paragraph A — {v. Ray’s appreciation of his contemporary academic culture}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“John Ray was <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">well aware</strong> that he lived through… he <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">gave thanks</strong> that he had been born at a time when… had given way to a new philosophy… that we now call science.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Appreciation” (sự trân trọng/đánh giá cao) thể hiện qua việc Ray cảm thấy may mắn và biết ơn (gave thanks) khi được sống trong thời kỳ cách mạng khoa học, nơi tư duy của Aristotle được thay thế bằng quan sát thực tế.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Paragraph B — {iii. A succession of academic achievements}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“admitted to Cambridge University in 1644… graduated in 1648… appointed <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">Lecturer in Greek</strong> in 1651, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">Lecturer in Mathematics</strong> in 1653, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"151\">Lecturer in Humanities</strong> in 1655.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này liệt kê một chuỗi các cột mốc thành công trong học thuật (succession of academic achievements) của Ray: từ việc đỗ đại học cho đến khi được bổ nhiệm làm giảng viên ở nhiều bộ môn khác nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Paragraph C — {ix. A change of direction for Ray}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“developed the interest to which he would <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">devote the rest of his life: the study of the natural world</strong>. He explains this <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">conversion into a naturalist</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Change of direction” (thay đổi định hướng) chính là việc Ray chuyển từ nghiên cứu ngôn ngữ/toán học sang dành trọn đời cho tự nhiên học (conversion into a naturalist) sau một lần ốm phải đi dạo ngoài trời.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Paragraph D — {iv. Ray’s informal tuition}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…first-year students… were being taught (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">unofficially – none of this was part of their formal education</strong>) by Ray. Many of them… But a few of them took his efforts… much more seriously.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Informal tuition” (giảng dạy không chính thức) tương ứng với cụm “unofficially / not part of formal education”. Ray đã dạy các sinh viên về thực vật học ngoài giờ lên lớp chính quy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Paragraph E — {i. Ray’s account of his working methods}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“I had first to become familiar with the literature, to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">compare the plants</strong> that I found with the pictures… <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">search for similarities</strong> and saved a vast deal of labour…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Toàn bộ phần trích dẫn trong ngoặc kép là lời tự thuật của Ray (Ray’s account) về phương pháp làm việc (working methods): so sánh mẫu vật với hình vẽ, tìm kiếm sự tương đồng giữa các họ thực vật.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Paragraph F — {viii. A description of the content of Ray’s first book}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Ray’s Cambridge Catalogue of English Plants was <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">much more than a simple list</strong>… It gave the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">names of plants</strong>, included <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">information about where they grew</strong> and how common they were.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này mô tả chi tiết nội dung (description of the content) trong cuốn sách đầu tiên của Ray: không chỉ là danh sách tên mà còn có cả môi trường sống và mức độ phổ biến của cây.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Paragraph G — {vii. Plans for a bold new project}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Ray’s studies of plants were only the beginning of a <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">much larger ambition</strong>… imagine a more <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">comprehensive investigation of nature</strong>… classify living things according to careful observation…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Bold new project” (dự án mới táo bạo) tương ứng với “larger ambition” và “comprehensive investigation”. Ray dự định xây dựng một hệ thống phân loại vạn vật dựa trên đặc điểm chung thay vì chỉ nghiên cứu thực vật địa phương.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2b40c3b8-adf6-460a-a099-3d9f21b04f3c', '72c5dbc1-5a97-4756-9650-4555dfcd7901', 'checkbox', 'Questions 9 and 10', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> letters, A–E.</p>
<p>Write the correct letters in boxes 9 and 10 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A. Some of the money they raise can be used for structural repairs."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. They can provide funds to help support amateur artists."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C. Local services benefit from the extra business they bring about."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D. They encourage overseas workers into the local area."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E. They raise employee performance levels."}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. A. Some of the money they raise can be used for structural repairs. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“For museums in some countries, it may be the money that they require to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">replace parts of their collections or to fix buildings that are in need of attention</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “fix buildings that are in need of attention” (sửa chữa các tòa nhà cần được quan tâm/tu sửa) chính là việc sửa chữa cấu trúc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">structural repairs</strong>) được nhắc đến trong câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. C. Local services benefit from the extra business they bring about. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…blockbusters mean crowds, and crowds are good for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">local economy, providing increased trade for shops, hotels, restaurants, the transport industry, and retailers</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc tăng trưởng kinh doanh (increased trade) cho các cửa hàng, khách sạn, nhà hàng… chính là minh chứng cho việc các dịch vụ địa phương (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">local services</strong>) được hưởng lợi từ lượng khách khổng lồ mà blockbuster mang lại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8d6b6f57-6e76-4dee-bfde-a345a6e08568', 'b2790d42-5a99-42e3-bf99-2b2d43408089', 'fillup', 'Questions 21-24', '<p id="p-rc_b7491987131485d8-78" data-path-to-node="11"><span class="citation-4154 citation-end-4154">Complete the summary below.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="8"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="11"><span class="citation-4153">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="11" data-index-in-node="35"><span class="citation-4153">ONE WORD ONLY</span></strong><span class="citation-4153 citation-end-4153"> from the passage for each answer.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="9"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="11"><span class="citation-4152 citation-end-4152">Write your answers in boxes 21-24 on yo<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="10"><!----></sup></span>ur answer sheet.</p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<p data-path-to-node="12"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">A New Approach to Knowledge</strong></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="13">John Ray was a scholar and self-taught botanist, whose work reflected the {philosophy} that was taking place during the 17th century in people’s way of thinking about the natural world. This new approach is the basis of the modern field of {science}. It represented a complete break from the ideas of Aristotle, which had dominated thinking up until that time.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="14">As Ray himself explained, his interest in plants was aroused after graduating, when he had to spend time outdoors after a period of {illness}. He taught himself, in addition to many Cambridge {students}, and began compiling his catalogue of plants, which was published in 1660.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. philosophy — {whose work reflected the philosophy that was taking place}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…traditional dependence on the teaching of the Greek philosopher Aristotle… had given way to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">new philosophy</strong>, based on experiment and observation…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Công việc của John Ray phản ánh một hệ tư tưởng/triết lý mới (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">philosophy</strong>) đang hình thành trong thế kỷ 17, thay thế cho các quan điểm cũ của Aristotle.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. science — {This new approach is the basis of the modern field of science.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…a new philosophy, based on experiment and observation of the real world, that we <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">now call science</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cách tiếp cận dựa trên quan sát thực tế này chính là nền tảng của ngành khoa học (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">science</strong>) hiện đại ngày nay.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. illness — {his interest in plants was aroused… after a period of illness.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Ray tells us that he suffered an <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">illness</strong> in his early twenties… While doing this [walking/riding for recovery], he became interested in the local flora…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Niềm đam mê thực vật của Ray trỗi dậy sau khi ông trải qua một đợt bạo bệnh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">illness</strong>) và được khuyên nên dành thời gian vận động ngoài trời để hồi phục.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. students — {He taught himself, in addition to many Cambridge students}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“By the mid-1650s, even the first-year <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">students</strong> at Trinity College were able to identify the plants… as they were being taught… by Ray.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngoài việc tự học, Ray còn truyền dạy kiến thức của mình cho rất nhiều sinh viên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">students</strong>) tại trường Cambridge (mặc dù đây không phải là nội dung giảng dạy chính quy thời đó).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('35a62944-a453-4247-a59f-082c1a90c307', '72c5dbc1-5a97-4756-9650-4555dfcd7901', 'checkbox', 'Question 11–13', '', '<p>Choose <strong>THREE</strong> letters, A–G.</p>
<p>Write the correct letters in boxes 11–13 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A. They do not suit museum management styles."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. Specialist business advice has to be paid for."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C. They involve an increased workload for personnel."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D. They do not increase overall annual visitor numbers."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "E. They are very tiring to put on."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "F. What is popular in one country may not be popular in another."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "G. The content can be weakened through financial pressure."}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. C. They involve an increased workload for personnel. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Everyone, from general laborers to… administrative staff is <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">required to perform additional tasks</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc mọi nhân viên từ lao động phổ thông đến hành chính đều phải thực hiện các “nhiệm vụ bổ sung” chính là minh chứng cho việc khối lượng công việc tăng lên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">increased workload</strong>) đối với nhân sự (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"207\">personnel</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. E. They are very tiring to put on. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Creating, mounting, or hiring blockbusters is <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">exhausting</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “exhausting” (gây kiệt sức) đồng nghĩa với “very tiring”. Bài đọc khẳng định quá trình chuẩn bị và tổ chức các buổi triển lãm này cực kỳ mệt mỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. G. The content can be weakened through financial pressure. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…pure concentration on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">bottom line</strong> [financial pressure] can <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">squeeze substance out of an exhibition</strong> [weakened content].”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc quá tập trung vào lợi nhuận (bottom line) sẽ làm “vắt kiệt” chất lượng nội dung của buổi triển lãm. “Squeeze substance out” tương ứng với việc nội dung bị làm cho yếu đi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"188\">weakened content</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2f123901-cbda-4177-a493-6999b57d236d', '7ab6f0c0-96be-4b97-8e73-50c56f5b212d', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-36', '<p data-path-to-node="4">Complete the notes below.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="4">Write <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="48">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="5"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="0">The archaeological site of Trimera</strong></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="6"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0">Location</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="7">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,0,0">southern Europe</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,0">mountainous region overlooking a plain</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="8"><strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="0">History</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="9">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,0,0">12,000 years ago: hunter-gatherers lived in area</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,1,0">5,000 years ago: farmers lived on banks of the rivers</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,2,0">2,500 years ago: became a trade center</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,3,0">300 BC: invaded by Greeks</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,4,0">100 BC: invaded by Romans - trade in grain, olives and {pottery}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,5,0">518 AD: city abandoned following earthquake</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="10"><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">Rediscovery of site</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="11">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="11,0,0">1706: French explorer believed the site was the remains of a {castle}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="11,1,0">19th century: a map was made of the site</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="11,2,0">1982: a complete {survey} was made</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="12"><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">Excavation</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="13">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="13,0,0">the {market} was the first place to be excavated</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="13,1,0">a number of {silver coins} were discovered</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="13,2,0">evidence of a {textile} industry was found</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4f503424-4424-48ff-8ca4-3f6828133be1', '7ab6f0c0-96be-4b97-8e73-50c56f5b212d', 'fillup', 'Questions 37-40', '<p>Complete the table below.</p>
<p>Write <strong data-path-to-node="15" data-index-in-node="48">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; height: 168.542px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 33.3478%;"><col style="width: 33.3478%;"><col style="width: 33.3478%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 33.7083px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">Buildings</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">Where</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">Notes</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 33.7083px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">Doric House</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">Eastern area</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">inhabitants came here to collect {water}</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 33.7083px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">Theatre</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">next to a stone {bridge}</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">capacity of 5,000</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 33.7083px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">Stairway</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">south-western area</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">has sculptures of {lions}</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 33.7083px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">Roman Baths</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">central area</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">a statue of a Roman {emperor} was found</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bc051de2-7e75-41af-9bd1-3e2c5c4f8a1c', 'a673a9c0-921b-48d4-9683-64f1920b7fe8', 'fillup', 'Questions 9–13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes <strong>9–13</strong> on your answer sheet. </p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong> Fund-raising campaigns</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>The first modern appeals</strong></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<p>an appeal was made in the 1960s to help build the Student Union buildings</p>
</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<p>Henry Cooper’s campaign marked the {centenary} of the University</p>
</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<p>modern campaigns have focused on raising money from businesses and individuals</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>‘Leading the Way’</strong></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<p>this appeal is raising money to invest in the University’s {staff}</p>
</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<p>gifts are being sought from graduates who are located {overseas}</p>
</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<p>John Taylor believes research at the University helps the whole country</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Financial matters</strong></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<p>some donations had not been {recorded} by the University</p>
</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">
<p>there is a new financial {target} for the campaign </p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: left;"> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. centenary — {Henry Cooper’s campaign marked the centenary of the University}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“This was followed by another appeal in 1983 under the then Chancellor Henry Cooper, who raised $800,000 <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">to celebrate the University’s centenary</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Marked\" (đánh dấu) đồng nghĩa với \"to celebrate\" (kỷ niệm/chúc mừng). Chiến dịch của Henry Cooper được tổ chức để kỷ niệm 100 năm ngày thành lập trường (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"166\">centenary</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. staff — {this appeal is raising money to invest in the University’s staff}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“It is intended as a drive to secure support for the whole University, with a <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">focus on generating funds to recruit, support and retain the very best staff</strong> for the University.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Invest in\" (đầu tư vào) tương ứng với hành động cấp vốn để tuyển dụng, hỗ trợ và giữ chân (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">recruit, support and retain</em>). Đối tượng được đầu tư ở đây chính là đội ngũ nhân sự/giảng viên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">staff</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. overseas — {gifts are being sought from graduates who are located overseas}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...and targeting <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">alumni, or former students now living overseas</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Graduates\" (những người đã tốt nghiệp) đồng nghĩa với từ \"alumni\" hoặc \"former students\" (cựu sinh viên). Những người này hiện đang sinh sống ở nước ngoài (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">overseas</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. recorded — {some donations had not been recorded by the University}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...we have come to realise that there has been <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">considerable giving to the University that has not been previously recorded</strong> through our Advancement Office...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Donations\" (khoản quyên góp) tương ứng với từ \"giving\". Bài đọc chỉ ra lỗi sai là có nhiều khoản đóng góp trước đó chưa từng được ghi nhận lại (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">recorded</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. target — {there is a new financial target for the campaign}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The good news from this error is that... it was announced that <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">the campaign target was now being increased from $100 million to $150 million</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Financial\" (thuộc về tài chính/tiền bạc) được thể hiện qua con số cụ thể từ 100 triệu lên 150 triệu đô-la. Việc tăng số tiền này đồng nghĩa với việc chiến dịch đã đặt ra một mục tiêu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">target</strong>) tài chính mới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('22236731-af80-482f-9650-8b9cffca8053', '5659ac7c-e9b4-4d3f-a0f6-3a9967b1cefd', 'matching', 'Questions 14–20', '', '<p>Reading Passage 2 has seven sections, <strong>A–G</strong>.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each section from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Write the correct number,<strong> i-viii</strong>, in boxes 14-20 on your answer sheet. </p>', 'matching_paragraph_information', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i      How new clothing styles are created"}, {"optionText": "ii     The rise of the fashion industry"}, {"optionText": "iii    Joining the garment pieces together"}, {"optionText": "iv    Producing materials with a range of features"}, {"optionText": "v     The importance of the fashion industry"}, {"optionText": "vi    Factors affecting international commerce"}, {"optionText": "vii   The attractions of becoming a fashion model"}, {"optionText": "viii Making patterns for people with different figures"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Section 1 (Đoạn A) — {v. The importance of the fashion industry}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The fashion industry is a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">multibillion-dollar global enterprise</strong>... by any measure, the industry <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">accounts for a significant share of world economic output</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này đưa ra các số liệu và khẳng định tầm vóc của ngành thời trang: là một doanh nghiệp toàn cầu trị giá nhiều tỷ đô-la và chiếm một phần đáng kể trong sản lượng kinh tế thế giới. Điều này làm nổi bật tầm quan trọng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"233\">The importance</strong>) về mặt kinh tế của ngành.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Section 2 (Đoạn B) — {ii. The rise of the fashion industry}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The fashion industry is a product of the modern age. <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">Prior to the mid-19th century</strong>, virtually all clothing was handmade... <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">By the beginning of the 20th century</strong>, with the development of new technologies... clothing had increasingly come to be <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"254\">mass-produced</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn phác họa lại dòng lịch sử phát triển của ngành thời trang từ giữa thế kỷ XIX (chỉ may tay cho cá nhân) cho đến đầu thế kỷ XX (bùng nổ công nghệ, máy may, sản xuất hàng loạt). Tiến trình lịch sử này chính là sự trỗi dậy/phát triển (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"252\">The rise</strong>) của ngành.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Section 3 (Đoạn C) — {iv. Producing materials with a range of features}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...fabrics made from both natural fibres and synthetic fibres... are produced... In addition, high-tech synthetic fabrics <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">confer such properties as moisture absorption, stain resistance, retention or dissipation of body heat, and protection against fire... hazards</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Materials\" (nguyên liệu) ở đây chính là các loại vải (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">fabrics/fibres</em>). Đoạn văn tập trung nói về việc sản xuất ra các loại vải có nhiều đặc tính/tính năng đặc biệt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">a range of features</strong>) như: hút ẩm, chống bẩn, giữ/tỏa nhiệt, chống cháy, chống tia UV...</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Section 4 (Đoạn D) — {i. How new clothing styles are created}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The vast majority of <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">designers</strong> work anonymously... <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">adapting designs into marketable garments</strong> for average consumers. They <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">draw inspiration from a wide range of sources</strong>... traditional design methods... have been supplemented or replaced by <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"250\">computer-assisted design techniques</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Toàn bộ đoạn này giải thích quy trình thiết kế trang phục: các nhà thiết kế lấy cảm hứng từ đâu, họ biến đổi các thiết kế thành sản phẩm thương mại như thế nào, và cách họ dùng công nghệ máy tính vẽ phác thảo. Đây chính là quy trình tạo ra các mẫu quần áo mới (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"273\">How new clothing styles are created</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Section 5 (Đoạn E) — {viii. Making patterns for people with different figures}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn </strong><strong>chứng</strong><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">“An important stage in garment production is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">translation of the clothing design into templates, in a range of sizes</strong>... Because the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">proportions of the human body change with increases or decreases in weight, templates cannot simply be scaled up or down</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Templates\" ở đây chính là các mẫu rập/khuôn mẫu để cắt vải (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">patterns</strong>). Đoạn văn nói về sự khó khăn khi thiết kế rập cho nhiều kích cỡ khác nhau do tỷ lệ cơ thể người thay đổi theo cân nặng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">people with different figures</strong> - người có vóc dáng khác nhau).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Section 6 (Đoạn F) — {iii. Joining the garment pieces together}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The next stage of production is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">assembly process</strong>... Technological innovation... has resulted in the automation of some stages of assembly. Nevertheless, <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">the fundamental process of sewing remains labour-intensive</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Assembly process\" (quá trình lắp ráp) và \"sewing\" (khâu/may) các mảnh vải lại với nhau chính là hành động ráp các mảnh quần áo lại thành một sản phẩm hoàn chỉnh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"175\">Joining the garment pieces together</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Section 7 (Đoạn G) — {vi. Factors affecting international commerce}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">trade in textiles and garments</strong> was strictly regulated by purchasing countries, which <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">imposed quotas and tariffs</strong>. Since the 1980s, these protectionist measures... have gradually been abandoned. They have been replaced by a <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"237\">free-trade approach</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"International commerce\" (thương mại quốc tế) đồng nghĩa với \"trade in textiles and garments\" (buôn bán dệt may toàn cầu). Các yếu tố ảnh hưởng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">Factors affecting</strong>) được liệt kê rõ bao gồm: hạn ngạch (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"212\">quotas</em>), thuế quan (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"232\">tariffs</em>), các biện pháp bảo hộ và hiệp định tự do thương mại (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"294\">free-trade approach</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('18cda4bf-e7e4-47c3-808b-6cf8d3d36c6e', '20fdba7f-344e-4a73-be0a-2f932388dcec', 'radio', 'Questions 1-7', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "ln Ancient China, writing was occasionally done on silk."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Coloured paper was invented during the Tang Dynasty."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Papermakers from Samarkand were captured by the Chinese."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Papermaking as a large-scale industry originated in Iran."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Papermaking skills were brought to Europe via North Africa."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "When Gutenberg invented movable type, paper materials were very expensive."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The end of the trade in rags was brought about by the difficulty of transporting them."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1. In Ancient China, writing was occasionally done on silk.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “The light material of <strong>silk was sometimes used</strong>, but was normally too expensive to consider.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản khẳng định lụa (<strong>silk</strong>) <strong>đôi khi được sử dụng</strong> (<strong>sometimes used</strong>) để viết, điều này làm cho nhận định là đúng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>2. Coloured paper was invented during the Tang Dynasty.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “During the Tang Dynasty… tea was served from baskets with <strong>multi-colored paper cups and paper napkins</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nói rằng giấy nhiều màu (<strong>multi-colored paper</strong>) đã được <em>sử dụng</em> trong thời nhà Đường, nhưng <strong>không nói rõ</strong> rằng giấy màu đã được <strong>phát minh</strong> (<strong>invented</strong>) trong thời kỳ này.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>3. Papermakers from Samarkand were captured by the Chinese.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “During a battle on the banks of the Tarus river, a <strong>Chinese caravan was captured which happened to include several papermakers</strong>. <strong>They were taken away to Samarkand</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Chính người Trung Quốc (Chinese papermakers) đã bị quân đội Hồi giáo bắt và đưa đến Samarkand, chứ không phải thợ Samarkand bị người Trung Quốc bắt.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>4. Papermaking as a large-scale industry originated in Iran.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “The rudimentary and laborious process of papermaking was refined and <strong>bulk manufacturing of paper began in Iran</strong>, where they invented a method to make a thicker sheet of paper, which helped <strong>transform papermaking from an art into an important business</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc sản xuất hàng loạt (bulk manufacturing / large-scale industry) và chuyển đổi thành ngành kinh doanh quan trọng bắt đầu ở Iran.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>5. Papermaking skills were brought to Europe via North Africa.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “Finally, when the <strong>Moors from North Africa invaded Spain and Portugal they brought the technology with them</strong> and so it was that papermaking entered Europe in the 12th century.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công nghệ làm giấy đã đến châu Âu thông qua người Moor từ Bắc Phi.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>6. When Gutenberg invented movable type, paper materials were very expensive.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) Văn bản nói rằng <strong>da cừu</strong> (parchment) là vật liệu được ưa chuộng trước đó và rất đắt, nhưng <strong>không đề cập</strong> đến việc nguyên liệu làm giấy (như giẻ rách) có đắt vào thời Gutenberg hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>7. The end of the trade in rags was brought about by the difficulty of transporting them.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) “The early European papers were made from recycled cotton and linen – and a huge trade quickly developed around the trading of old rags… Yet <strong>soon this source became insufficient</strong> and some curious attempts were made to find new materials.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nguồn cung cấp giẻ rách không còn <strong>đủ</strong> (insufficient), chứ không phải do khó khăn trong vận chuyển (difficulty of transporting), nên nhận định là sai.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f5e99920-5247-4457-b97d-da6495f3ac8d', '20fdba7f-344e-4a73-be0a-2f932388dcec', 'fillup', 'Questions 8-13', '<p>Complete the table below.</p>
