</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>8. Egypt: Method of production (Papyrus)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>strips</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “The Egyptians cut the plant into <strong>strips</strong> which they softened in water. Papyrus was cross-woven into a mat and then pounded…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cây papyrus được cắt thành các <strong>strips</strong> (dải) trước khi được xử lý tiếp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>9. Europe: Materials used (Parchment)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>sheep</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “…it has been estimated that a single book written on parchment required the skins of 300 <strong>sheep</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Da cừu (<strong>sheep</strong>) là ví dụ cụ thể về nguyên liệu làm parchment.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>10. Europe: Method of production (Parchment)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>stretched</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “The skins had to be specifically prepared by drying them and they were then <strong>stretched</strong> on a special frame.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Da làm parchment được làm khô và sau đó được <strong>stretched</strong> (kéo căng).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>11. China: Materials used (Paper)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Bark</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “Ts’ai Lun seems to have made his paper by mixing finely chopped <strong>mulberry bark</strong> and hemp rags with water…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Vỏ cây (<strong>Bark</strong>) dâu tằm là một trong những nguyên liệu chính.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>12. Place: (Papermaking Center in 751 AD)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Samarkand</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “They were taken away to <strong>Samarkand</strong>, which was a good place to make paper…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Thợ làm giấy Trung Quốc bị bắt và đưa đến <strong>Samarkand</strong>, nơi này trở thành trung tâm làm giấy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>13. Samarkand: Method of production</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Stone</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “Samarkanders changed the technology of manufacturing paper. They began to prepare it in <strong>stone</strong> mills…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công nghệ mới ở Samarkand sử dụng cối xay làm bằng <strong>Stone</strong> (đá).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('711f2cff-e154-449d-ba17-81bda51075ab', 'a55fc91d-a8ba-4693-a8ba-90dcc56656d3', 'radio', 'Questions 1-7', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Pyramid of Cestius has always been one of Rome''s most popular tourist attractions"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The construction of the Pyramid was completed before Cestius'' death"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the Middle Ages, people thought an original founder of Rome was buried in the Pyramid of Cestius."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Today the height of the Pyramid is something that tourists and residents immediately notice."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Japanese businessman Yuzo Yagi was an admirer of both Italian and Egyptian architecture."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The restoration of the Pyramid of Cestius, which was funded by Yuzo Yagi, finished earlier than expected."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Most of the original frescoes inside Cestius’ tomb have survived to this day."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. The Pyramid of Cestius has always been one of Rome''s most popular tourist attractions. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Though Rome draws tourists from around the world to its many impressive sites, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">one notable monument there has never attracted nearly as much interest: The Pyramid of Cestius</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi khẳng định kim tự tháp này <em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">luôn luôn</em> là một trong những điểm thu hút khách du lịch nổi tiếng nhất của Rome. Ngược lại, bài đọc ghi rõ công trình này chưa bao giờ thu hút được nhiều sự quan tâm tương tự như các địa điểm khác (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"245\">never attracted nearly as much interest</em>). Thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"331\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. The construction of the Pyramid was completed before Cestius'' death. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The only one left standing... <span class=\"citation-197 citation-end-197\">was designed as the burial pyramid for a Roman politician named Caius Cestius, who ordered that the building work be completed within a period of 330 days. Construction took place at some point between 18 B.C. and 12 B.<sup class=\"superscript\"><!----></sup></span>C.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ cung cấp thông tin ông Cestius ra lệnh phải hoàn thành công trình trong vòng 330 ngày và thời gian xây dựng nằm trong khoảng từ năm 18 TCN đến 12 TCN, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"179\">hoàn toàn không đề cập</strong> đến việc công trình này xây xong trước hay sau khi ông ấy qua đời. Do đó đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"285\">NOT GIVEN</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. In the Middle Ages, people thought an original founder of Rome was buried in the Pyramid of Cestius. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“By the Middle Ages... a popular myth suggested that <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">it might be the tomb of Romulus or Remus, the legendary founders of Rome</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"An original founder of Rome\" (một nhà sáng lập ban đầu của Rome) tương ứng với cụm \"Romulus or Remus, the legendary founders of Rome\". Việc người thời Trung Cổ nghĩ rằng họ được chôn cất ở đây trùng khớp với giả thuyết dân gian lúc bấy giờ (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"254\">a popular myth suggested that it might be the tomb of...</em>). Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"323\">TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Today the height of the Pyramid is something that tourists and residents immediately notice. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Today, the Pyramid of Cestius stands near a busy intersection, <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">making it easy for tourists and residents to overlook its full height of 119 feet</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói ngày nay chiều cao của kim tự tháp là thứ mà du khách và người dân địa phương nhận ra ngay lập tức (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">immediately notice</em>). Tuy nhiên, bài đọc viết rằng vì nó nằm cạnh một giao lộ đông đúc nên mọi người rất dễ bỏ qua/ngó lơ chiều cao toàn phần của nó (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"273\">easy to overlook its full height</strong>). Thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"352\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Japanese businessman Yuzo Yagi was an admirer of both Italian and Egyptian architecture. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In 2011, Japanese entrepreneur Yuzo Yagi... announced his intention to fund a major renovation of the Pyramid of Cestius. He described it as <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">“an act of gratitude” to Italy, a country that contributed to his company’s success</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ giải thích lý do ông Yuzo Yagi tài trợ tiền trùng tu là vì muốn bày tỏ lòng biết ơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"109\">an act of gratitude</em>) với nước Ý, nơi giúp công ty ông thành công, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"179\">không hề có thông tin</strong> nào nói về việc ông có phải là người ngưỡng mộ kiến trúc Ý và Ai Cập (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"271\">an admirer of... architecture</em>) hay không. Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"323\">NOT GIVEN</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. The restoration of the Pyramid of Cestius, which was funded by Yuzo Yagi, finished earlier than expected. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...and thanks to his 2-million-euro donation, <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">the project was completed ahead of schedule</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Finished earlier than expected\" (hoàn thành sớm hơn dự kiến) đồng nghĩa hoàn toàn với cụm từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">\"completed ahead of schedule\"</strong> (hoàn thành trước thời hạn/lịch trình). Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"186\">TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Most of the original frescoes inside Cestius'' tomb have survived to this day. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Visitors can walk through a narrow corridor to reach the burial chamber, where they can admire frescoes... <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">Some frescoes have disappeared over time</strong>, but historical records confirm their existence.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói <em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">phần lớn</em> (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">most of</em>) các bức tranh bích họa nguyên bản vẫn tồn tại đến ngày nay. Nhưng bài đọc viết rõ một phần các bức bích họa này đã bị biến mất theo thời gian (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"186\">some frescoes have disappeared over time</em>). Đối với các câu hỏi về lượng từ (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"262\">Most</em> &gt;&lt; <em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"270\">Some</em>), thông tin bị lệch bản chất nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"318\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a1acab58-e260-402a-ab10-da3e7f8cb000', 'e872056b-9c62-44b2-8fcc-2f716d16337f', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information,<strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information,<strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries, the British East India Company faced a lot of competition."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Before 1800, cargo size was the most important consideration for the East India Company"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "At best, voyages of the East Indiamen to China and back took nearly two years to complete."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Before 1834, voyages to and from China were considered to be highly dangerous"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "After 1834, the ships which had served the East India Company stopped being used for commercial purposes."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the nineteenth century, British drinkers preferred tea made from mature leaves to that made from younger leaves.+"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. In the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries, the British East India Company faced a lot of competition. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_5de9fe4efc5b0522-28\" data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<span class=\"citation-129\">During the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries, the </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\"><span class=\"citation-129\">British East India Company had the monopoly on trade</span></strong><span class=\"citation-129\"> with China and India. This meant that </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"165\"><span class=\"citation-129\">because no rival could legally import tea or other goods</span></strong><span class=\"citation-129 citation-end-129\"> from these countries at this ti<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>me...”</em></p>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi khẳng định vào thế kỷ XVII - XVIII, công ty Đông Ấn Anh phải đối mặt với rất nhiều sự cạnh tranh (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">faced a lot of competition</em>). Tuy nhiên, bài đọc ghi rõ công ty nắm giữ sự độc quyền (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">monopoly</em>) và không có bất kỳ đối thủ nào (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"245\">no rival</em>) có thể nhập khẩu hợp pháp. Vì thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"329\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Before 1800, cargo size was the most important consideration for the East India Company. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Instead, <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">its priority was to minimise costs by carrying as much as possible on each ship</strong>. This meant that its ships – known as East Indiamen – were enormous, strong and very slow.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Priority\" (sự ưu tiên hàng đầu) đồng nghĩa với \"the most important consideration\" (yếu tố cân nhắc quan trọng nhất). Việc ưu tiên chở nhiều hàng nhất có thể trên mỗi chuyến tàu (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"191\">carrying as much as possible</em>) chính là tập trung vào kích thước/khối lượng hàng hóa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"276\">cargo size</strong>). Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"299\">TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. At best, voyages of the East Indiamen to China and back took nearly two years to complete. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...so <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">even with favourable sailing conditions, the round trip lasted almost two years</strong>, and if anything went wrong it could take a lot longer.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"At best\" (Trong điều kiện tốt nhất) tương ứng với cụm \"even with favourable sailing conditions\" (ngay cả với điều kiện căng buồm thuận lợi). \"Nearly two years\" (gần hai năm) đồng nghĩa với \"almost two years\". Chuyến đi khứ hồi đi và về (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"250\">voyages to China and back</strong>) tương ứng với cụm từ \"the round trip\". Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"326\">TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Before 1834, voyages to and from China were considered to be highly dangerous. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2 &amp; 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“...and if anything went wrong it could take a lot longer.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nhắc đến việc nếu có sự cố xảy ra (<em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">if anything went wrong</em>) thì chuyến đi sẽ mất nhiều thời gian hơn rất nhiều, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">hoàn toàn không có thông tin</strong> nào đánh giá hay xem xét liệu các chuyến hải trình này có cực kỳ nguy hiểm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"244\">highly dangerous</strong>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. After 1834, the ships which had served the East India Company stopped being used for commercial purposes. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“However, by 1834 the company had lost its trading monopolies... Having no more use for its great ships, <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">the company sold them off, and many were bought by merchants or their captains, who continued to plough the seas between Britain and China</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói sau năm 1834, các tàu này ngừng được sử dụng cho mục đích thương mại (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">stopped being used for commercial purposes</em>). Nhưng bài đọc viết công ty đã bán lại tàu cho các thương nhân và thuyền trưởng (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"219\">bought by merchants</em>), và họ <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"247\">tiếp tục ra khơi buôn bán</strong> giữa Anh và Trung Quốc (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"297\">continued to plough the seas</em>). Vì thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"375\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. In the nineteenth century, British drinkers preferred tea made from mature leaves to that made from younger leaves. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...because consumers in Britain in the nineteenth century <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">believed that the fresher and earlier-picked the tea, the better the resulting drink</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói người Anh thích trà làm từ lá già/lá trưởng thành (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">mature leaves</em>) hơn lá non (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">younger leaves</em>). Nhưng bài đọc viết người tiêu dùng tin rằng trà càng tươi (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">fresher</em>) và được hái càng sớm (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"209\">earlier-picked</em> - tức là lá non đầu vụ) thì càng ngon. Vì thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"310\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b8674488-6935-4749-b515-78f241d30820', 'e872056b-9c62-44b2-8fcc-2f716d16337f', 'fillup', 'Questions 7–13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 7–13 on your answer sheet. </p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong> Clipper races</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>The ships</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Clipper ships were first used for trading by American merchants.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The ships were remarkable for the number of {sails} they had.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The performance of British tea clippers was particularly affected when there were {storms} at sea.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The races</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>It was in a ship called {Challenger} that the British first competed successfully against the Americans.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Richard Green’s ship arrived two days ahead of its competitor.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Competition increased when additional Chinese trading {ports} were established.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Merchants were occasionally in such a hurry that they failed to complete the {paperwork} before leaving China.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>At the end of their journey, the ships needed the help of {tugs}.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The rewards</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The crews were motivated by both {money} and their enthusiasm for the competition. </p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. sails — {The ships were remarkable for the number of sails they had.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“These vessels were fast and slender, with a narrow hull that was deeper at the back than at the front, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">masses of sails on tall masts</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"remarkable for the number of...\" (gây chú ý vì số lượng của cái gì) đồng nghĩa với từ \"masses of...\" (hàng khối/rất nhiều cái gì). Thứ mà những con tàu này có rất nhiều chính là những cánh buồm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"215\">sails</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. storms — {The performance of British tea clippers was particularly affected when there were storms at sea.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...they had a narrower beam than their American equivalents, <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">making them less powerful during storms but faster in calmer weather</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Particularly affected\" (bị ảnh hưởng đặc biệt/trở nên yếu thế hơn) tương ứng với cụm \"less powerful\" (ít quyền năng hơn/yếu hơn). Tình huống trên biển gây ra sự ảnh hưởng này chính là những trận bão (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"213\">storms</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Challenger — {It was in a ship called Challenger that the British first competed successfully against the Americans.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Then in 1851 a British shipowner, Richard Green, <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">built the aptly named clipper Challenger with the stated intention of beating the American ships</strong>... In the event, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"188\">British ship beat its rival</strong> to London by two days...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Competed successfully against\" (cạnh tranh thành công/đánh bại) tương ứng với từ \"beating / beat its rival\". Tên con tàu mang lại chiến thắng đầu tiên này cho người Anh là <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"185\">Challenger</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. ports — {Competition increased when additional Chinese trading ports were established.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“But even without the Anglo-American rivalry, the competitive spirit continued. <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">It was really ignited when new ports were opened up for trade in China</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Competition increased / ignited\" (sự cạnh tranh tăng lên/bùng cháy mạnh mẽ). Nguyên nhân là do có thêm nhiều thương cảng mới được mở ra (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">ports</strong>). Chữ <em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">additional</em> đồng nghĩa với từ <em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"191\">new</em> trong ngữ cảnh này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. paperwork — {Merchants were occasionally in such a hurry that they failed to complete the paperwork before leaving China.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“As a result, tea could be loaded on board earlier and fresher, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">the clippers could set off in late May or early June – sometimes not even taking time to fill out the official paperwork</strong> – racing back to Britain...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"In such a hurry\" (vội vã đến mức) tương ứng với cụm \"not even taking time\" (thậm chí không thèm tốn thời gian). \"Failed to complete\" (không hoàn thành/bỏ qua) đồng nghĩa với việc không điền vào (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">not fill out</strong>). Thứ bị bỏ qua ở đây là giấy tờ thủ tục hành chính (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"274\">paperwork</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. tugs — {At the end of their journey, the ships needed the help of tugs.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Once there [at the River Thames], <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">they would be towed by tugs up the river and into the docks</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"At the end of their journey\" (vào cuối cuộc hành trình/khi về tới đích). Lúc này, các tàu cần sự trợ giúp/được kéo đi (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">towed</em>) bởi những chiếc tàu kéo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">tugs</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. money — {The crews were motivated by both money and their enthusiasm for the competition.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The cargo of the winning ship could earn a premium... and so the captain and crew were rewarded... <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">But the races were about more than just money: the crews... delighted in competing against each other. Without their enthusiasm, the races would never have happened</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đề bài liệt kê hai yếu tố thúc đẩy/tạo động lực (<em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">motivated</em>) cho các thủy thủ: một là sự hào hứng thi đấu (<em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">enthusiasm for the competition</em>), và yếu tố còn lại (nằm trước chữ <em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"184\">and</em>) chính là tiền bạc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">money</strong> / <em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"216\">rewarded / earn a premium</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('45695ec3-0e64-4183-a3cd-1ac738da3b8f', 'a55fc91d-a8ba-4693-a8ba-90dcc56656d3', 'fillup', 'Questions 8-13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 8-13 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p class="bold" style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>History of the Pyramid of Cestius</strong></span></p>
<p class="bold"><strong>Construction of Cestius’ pyramid</strong></p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">• It was made from {brick } marble and cement.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">• Its { shape} is different from the pyramids found in Egypt.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">• It was originally built in the {countryside} as tombs in the city were forbidden.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">• Emperor Aurelian ordered that a wall be built around it.</p>
<p class="bold"><strong>Restoration of Cestius’ pyramid in the 1660s</strong></p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">• In the 1660s, some broken {statues} were found next to it.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">• The {tunnel} inside the tomb suggests that robbers had been there.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">• The frescoes show mythological scenes and images of vases.</p>
<p class="bold"><strong>Restoration of Cestius’ pyramid today</strong></p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">• A Japanese businessman paid for its restoration.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">• Climbers are helping to remove signs of {pollution}.</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Construction of Cestius’ pyramid</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. brick — {It was made from brick, marble and cement.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Cestius’ pyramid had a <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">layer of white Carrara marble on the outside</strong> and was <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">constructed from brick held together by cement on the inside</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đề bài liệt kê 3 vật liệu xây dựng nên kim tự tháp bao gồm: <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">marble</em> (đá cẩm thạch), <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">cement</em> (xi măng) và từ còn thiếu ở đây là gạch (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">brick</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. shape — {Its shape is different from the pyramids found in Egypt.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“One of the things that strikes you when you look at the pyramid is how steep it is, <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">making its shape quite unlike that of typical Egyptian pyramids</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"quite unlike that of...\" (khá là không giống với...) đồng nghĩa với từ khác biệt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">different from</strong>). Yếu tố khác biệt được nhắc đến ở đây là hình dáng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">shape</strong>) của nó dốc hơn kim tự tháp Ai Cập thông thường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. countryside — {It was originally built in the countryside as tombs in the city were forbidden.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“At the time of its construction, <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">a strict Roman law prohibited tombs within the city, so the Pyramid of Cestius would have stood in countryside</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Forbidden\" đồng nghĩa với \"prohibited\" (bị cấm). Do luật cấm xây lăng mộ trong thành phố (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">within the city</em>), nên ban đầu kim tự tháp này phải được xây dựng ở vùng nông ngoại ô (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"189\">countryside</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Restoration of Cestius’ pyramid in the 1660s</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. statues — {In the 1660s, some broken statues were found next to it.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“During excavations [in the 1660s], workers cleared away trees and plants and found... as well as <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">fragments of bronze statues that once stood on either side</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Next to it\" (ở bên cạnh) tương ứng với cụm \"stood on either side\" (đứng ở hai bên). Từ \"fragments\" (mảnh vỡ/mảnh vụn) đóng vai trò paraphrase cho từ bị hỏng/vỡ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">broken</strong>). Do đó, từ cần điền là các bức tượng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"220\">statues</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. tunnel — {The tunnel inside the tomb suggests that robbers had been there.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...but they did <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">discover a tunnel, suggesting that robbers might have looted the tomb</strong> long ago.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Had been there\" (đã ở đó/từng ghé qua) tương ứng với hành động đã đến cướp bóc (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">looted</em>). Việc phát hiện ra một đường hầm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">tunnel</strong>) chính là bằng chứng cho thấy những kẻ trộm mộ đã từng đột nhập vào đây.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Restoration of Cestius’ pyramid today</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. pollution — {Climbers are helping to remove signs of pollution.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 10):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">“...the white exterior of the Pyramid of Cestius needs to be <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">cleaned regularly due to urban pollution</strong>. A <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">team of free-climbers will handle the task</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Remove signs of...\" (loại bỏ các dấu vết của...) tương ứng với hành động dọn dẹp/làm sạch (<em data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">cleaned</em>). Đội ngũ những người leo núi tự do (<em data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">free-climbers</em>) sẽ chịu trách nhiệm leo lên để làm sạch các vết bẩn do ô nhiễm đô thị (<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"235\">pollution</strong>) gây ra.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bf65f16c-9521-46c1-bb6a-970ecb5059fd', '262d1e76-dee5-40cd-bdc7-1f3c0caf0b75', 'matching', 'Questions 14-20', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has seven paragraphs, A-G.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p><strong>List of Headings</strong></p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Some of the problems that developed at Talbot Park"}, {"optionText": "ii. Where the residents lived while the work was being completed"}, {"optionText": "iii. The ethnic makeup of the new Talbot Park"}, {"optionText": "iv. The unexpectedly high standard of the housing"}, {"optionText": "v. Financial hardship in Talbot Park and a neighbouring community"}, {"optionText": "vi. The experiences of one family living at Talbot Park today"}, {"optionText": "vii. How to co-ordinate and assist the people who live at Talbot Park"}, {"optionText": "viii. A close community in the original Talbot Park development"}, {"optionText": "ix. Raising the money to pay for the makeover"}, {"optionText": "x. Details of the style of buildings used in the makeover"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<ul>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Paragraph A: iv (The unexpectedly high standard of the housing)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “‘There is no reason why state housing should look cheap in my view,’ says architect Neil Cotton… I was anticipating a backlash by those who objected to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">quality</strong> of what is provided…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kiến trúc sư Neil Cotton nhấn mạnh rằng tiêu chuẩn xây dựng tại đây cao đến mức ông lo ngại người dân sẽ phản đối vì nó trông quá sang trọng so với một dự án nhà ở xã hội (vốn thường bị coi là rẻ tiền).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Paragraph B: viii (A close community in the original Talbot Park development)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Initially, there was a <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">strong sense of neighborliness</strong>. Former residents recall how the garden played a big part in their childhoods… ‘We had respect for our neighbours…’”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn hồi tưởng về những năm 1960 khi Talbot Park còn là một cộng đồng gắn kết, nơi trẻ em chơi đùa cùng nhau và mọi người cư xử với nhau rất lễ độ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Paragraph C: i (Some of the problems that developed at Talbot Park)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…standards dropped and the neighbourhood began to look shabbier… buildings themselves were also deteriorating… petty crime was on the rise and the garden was considered unsafe.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Liệt kê các vấn đề xuất hiện từ cuối thập niên 70 như nhà cửa xuống cấp, sự thiếu hòa nhập của người nhập cư và tình hình an ninh mất kiểm soát.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Paragraph D: x (Details of the style of buildings used in the makeover)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The first priority was to mix up the housing by employing a variety of plans… free-standing houses, some semi-detached, some low level, multi-apartment blocks.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tập trung vào chi tiết thiết kế “mix and match” với sự đa dạng về kiểu dáng nhà ở để tránh sự đơn điệu và tạo bản sắc riêng cho cư dân.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,4,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Paragraph E: iii (The ethnic makeup of the new Talbot Park)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The population today is cosmopolitan: <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">50% Pacific Islanders, 20% Maori, 15% Asian, 10% New Zealand European</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cung cấp số liệu thống kê cụ thể về cơ cấu sắc tộc đa dạng của cư dân đang sống tại dự án mới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,5,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Paragraph F: v (Financial hardship in Talbot Park and a neighbouring community)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The area has a high density of households with incomes in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">$5,000 to $15,000 range</strong> and very few with an income over $70,000.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đưa ra số liệu cụ thể về thu nhập để làm nổi bật thực trạng khó khăn về kinh tế (financial hardship) của người dân tại khu vực này so với phần còn lại của thành phố.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,6,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Paragraph G: vii (How to co-ordinate and assist the people who live at Talbot Park)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…you have to actually <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">help them to get to know each other</strong> by organising morning teas and street barbecues.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mô tả cách quản lý không chỉ bằng kỷ luật (strict rules) mà còn bằng các hoạt động hỗ trợ cộng đồng để giúp cư dân sinh sống hòa thuận trong một môi trường đông đúc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('66c94357-9ab1-4a9d-ba55-379bba888b34', '262d1e76-dee5-40cd-bdc7-1f3c0caf0b75', 'matching', 'Questions 21–23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following people (Questions 21-23) and the list of ideas below.</p>
<p>Match each person with the correct idea, A-F.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, A-F, in boxes 21-23 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "Good tenant management involves supervision and regulation."}, {"optionText": "State housing must be built at minimum expense to the public."}, {"optionText": "Organising social events helps tenants to live close together."}, {"optionText": "Mixed-race communities require adaptable and responsive designs."}, {"optionText": "Complaints were expected about the high standard of the development."}, {"optionText": "Too many rules and regulations will cause resentment from tenants."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "James Lundy", "correctAnswer": "D", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Graham Bodman", "correctAnswer": "A", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Stuart Bracey", "correctAnswer": "C", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<ul>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. James Lundy: J (Mixed-race communities require adaptable and responsive designs.)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…important that the buildings were sufficiently <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">flexible to cater for the needs of people from a wide variety of cultural backgrounds</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lundy tin rằng thiết kế linh hoạt (flexible) là cần thiết để đáp ứng nhu cầu của các nhóm sắc tộc khác nhau (mixed-race/cultural backgrounds).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Graham Bodman: G (Good tenant management involves supervision and regulation.)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The focus is on <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">frequent inspections</strong> and <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">setting clear guidelines and boundaries</strong> regarding the sort of behaviour we expect from tenants.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ông nhấn mạnh việc kiểm soát thông qua giám sát (inspections) và các quy định (guidelines/rules).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Stuart Bracey: I (Organising social events helps tenants to live close together.)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…help them to get to know each other by <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">organising morning teas and street barbecues</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ông cho rằng các sự kiện xã hội (social events) là chìa khóa để cư dân sống gần nhau một cách hòa thuận.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('38d6729c-fc34-480f-a97f-c45cd5d2b03e', '262d1e76-dee5-40cd-bdc7-1f3c0caf0b75', 'fillup', 'Questions 24-26 ', '<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>The ‘mix and match’ strategy</strong></p>
<p>One aspect of the Talbot Park project that some critics are concerned about is that the higher {density} of accommodation would lead to the old social problems returning. To prevent this, a team of various {Architects} worked on the project to ensure the buildings were not uniform. Further, they created pleasant,functional interiors that could still be built within their { budget} Finally, the absence of walls means Talbot Park is characterised by openness, making it easier to regulate behaviour within the community.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<ul>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. density</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…new development has actually made the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">density</strong> of housing in Talbot Park greater…” (Đoạn D).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một số ý kiến lo ngại rằng mật độ cư dân cao (higher density) có thể gây ra các vấn đề xã hội cũ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. architects</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…employing a variety of plans by different <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">architects</strong>…” (Đoạn D).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để tránh sự đơn điệu, dự án đã thuê nhiều kiến trúc sư khác nhau cùng tham gia thiết kế.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. budget</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…ensure the project did not go over <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">budget</strong>.” (Đoạn D).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các kiến trúc sư sử dụng thiết kế tối giản công nghiệp để đảm bảo chi phí nằm trong ngân sách cho phép.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d7b076de-ab2c-4a0f-9320-3b87060a1755', 'a85cdea7-bfce-461c-9c67-6c420c6886d9', 'fillup', 'Questions 21-24', '<p id="p-rc_b7491987131485d8-78" data-path-to-node="11"><span class="citation-4154 citation-end-4154">Complete the summary below.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="8"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="11"><span class="citation-4153">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="11" data-index-in-node="35"><span class="citation-4153">ONE WORD ONLY</span></strong><span class="citation-4153 citation-end-4153"> from the passage for each answer.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="9"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="11"><span class="citation-4152 citation-end-4152">Write your answers in boxes 21-24 on yo<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="10"><!----></sup></span>ur answer sheet.</p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<p data-path-to-node="12"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">A New Approach to Knowledge</strong></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="13">John Ray was a scholar and self-taught botanist, whose work reflected the {philosophy} that was taking place during the 17th century in people’s way of thinking about the natural world. This new approach is the basis of the modern field of {science}. It represented a complete break from the ideas of Aristotle, which had dominated thinking up until that time.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="14">As Ray himself explained, his interest in plants was aroused after graduating, when he had to spend time outdoors after a period of {illness}. He taught himself, in addition to many Cambridge {students}, and began compiling his catalogue of plants, which was published in 1660.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. philosophy — {whose work reflected the philosophy that was taking place}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…traditional dependence on the teaching of the Greek philosopher Aristotle… had given way to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">new philosophy</strong>, based on experiment and observation…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Công việc của John Ray phản ánh một hệ tư tưởng/triết lý mới (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">philosophy</strong>) đang hình thành trong thế kỷ 17, thay thế cho các quan điểm cũ của Aristotle.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. science — {This new approach is the basis of the modern field of science.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…a new philosophy, based on experiment and observation of the real world, that we <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">now call science</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cách tiếp cận dựa trên quan sát thực tế này chính là nền tảng của ngành khoa học (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">science</strong>) hiện đại ngày nay.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. illness — {his interest in plants was aroused… after a period of illness.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Ray tells us that he suffered an <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">illness</strong> in his early twenties… While doing this [walking/riding for recovery], he became interested in the local flora…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Niềm đam mê thực vật của Ray trỗi dậy sau khi ông trải qua một đợt bạo bệnh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">illness</strong>) và được khuyên nên dành thời gian vận động ngoài trời để hồi phục.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. students — {He taught himself, in addition to many Cambridge students}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“By the mid-1650s, even the first-year <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">students</strong> at Trinity College were able to identify the plants… as they were being taught… by Ray.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngoài việc tự học, Ray còn truyền dạy kiến thức của mình cho rất nhiều sinh viên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">students</strong>) tại trường Cambridge (mặc dù đây không phải là nội dung giảng dạy chính quy thời đó).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f7f6f7c5-5a11-4ed7-bfad-5777659fb576', 'b2790d42-5a99-42e3-bf99-2b2d43408089', 'matching', 'Questions 14-20', '', '<p>Write the correct number, <strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="150">i–ix</strong>, in boxes 14-20 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_paragraph_information', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Ray’s account of his working methods"}, {"optionText": "ii. The botanical expert who inspired Ray"}, {"optionText": "iii. A succession of academic achievements"}, {"optionText": "iv. Ray’s informal tuition"}, {"optionText": "v. Ray’s appreciation of his contemporary academic culture"}, {"optionText": "vi. A childhood interest in plants"}, {"optionText": "vii. Plans for a bold new project"}, {"optionText": "viii. A description of the content of Ray’s first book"}, {"optionText": "ix. A change of direction for Ray"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Paragraph A — {v. Ray’s appreciation of his contemporary academic culture}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“John Ray was <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">well aware</strong> that he lived through… he <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">gave thanks</strong> that he had been born at a time when… had given way to a new philosophy… that we now call science.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Appreciation” (sự trân trọng/đánh giá cao) thể hiện qua việc Ray cảm thấy may mắn và biết ơn (gave thanks) khi được sống trong thời kỳ cách mạng khoa học, nơi tư duy của Aristotle được thay thế bằng quan sát thực tế.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Paragraph B — {iii. A succession of academic achievements}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“admitted to Cambridge University in 1644… graduated in 1648… appointed <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">Lecturer in Greek</strong> in 1651, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">Lecturer in Mathematics</strong> in 1653, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"151\">Lecturer in Humanities</strong> in 1655.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này liệt kê một chuỗi các cột mốc thành công trong học thuật (succession of academic achievements) của Ray: từ việc đỗ đại học cho đến khi được bổ nhiệm làm giảng viên ở nhiều bộ môn khác nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Paragraph C — {ix. A change of direction for Ray}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“developed the interest to which he would <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">devote the rest of his life: the study of the natural world</strong>. He explains this <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">conversion into a naturalist</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Change of direction” (thay đổi định hướng) chính là việc Ray chuyển từ nghiên cứu ngôn ngữ/toán học sang dành trọn đời cho tự nhiên học (conversion into a naturalist) sau một lần ốm phải đi dạo ngoài trời.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Paragraph D — {iv. Ray’s informal tuition}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…first-year students… were being taught (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">unofficially – none of this was part of their formal education</strong>) by Ray. Many of them… But a few of them took his efforts… much more seriously.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Informal tuition” (giảng dạy không chính thức) tương ứng với cụm “unofficially / not part of formal education”. Ray đã dạy các sinh viên về thực vật học ngoài giờ lên lớp chính quy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Paragraph E — {i. Ray’s account of his working methods}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“I had first to become familiar with the literature, to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">compare the plants</strong> that I found with the pictures… <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">search for similarities</strong> and saved a vast deal of labour…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Toàn bộ phần trích dẫn trong ngoặc kép là lời tự thuật của Ray (Ray’s account) về phương pháp làm việc (working methods): so sánh mẫu vật với hình vẽ, tìm kiếm sự tương đồng giữa các họ thực vật.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Paragraph F — {viii. A description of the content of Ray’s first book}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Ray’s Cambridge Catalogue of English Plants was <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">much more than a simple list</strong>… It gave the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">names of plants</strong>, included <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">information about where they grew</strong> and how common they were.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này mô tả chi tiết nội dung (description of the content) trong cuốn sách đầu tiên của Ray: không chỉ là danh sách tên mà còn có cả môi trường sống và mức độ phổ biến của cây.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Paragraph G — {vii. Plans for a bold new project}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Ray’s studies of plants were only the beginning of a <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">much larger ambition</strong>… imagine a more <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">comprehensive investigation of nature</strong>… classify living things according to careful observation…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Bold new project” (dự án mới táo bạo) tương ứng với “larger ambition” và “comprehensive investigation”. Ray dự định xây dựng một hệ thống phân loại vạn vật dựa trên đặc điểm chung thay vì chỉ nghiên cứu thực vật địa phương.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d0713014-43e4-4d18-a118-64ece4c2a68f', '784abe17-25a4-4988-bebd-1bbbba08ffff', 'radio', 'Questions 27–30', '', '<p>Choose <strong data-start="155" data-end="162">YES</strong> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, <strong data-start="218" data-end="224">NO</strong> if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, <strong data-start="280" data-end="293">NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Field and Wroe argue that findings at the Cuddie Springs site show that people lived in this area at the same time as megafauna"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Field and Wroe believe it is likely that smaller megafauna species survived the last Ice Age"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The writers believe that the dating of earth up to 1.7 m below the present surface at Cuddie Springs is unreliable"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some artefacts found at Cuddie Springs were preserved well enough to reveal their function"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. YES</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Drs Judith Field and Stephen Wroe of the University of Sydney, who excavated the site, claim that it provides unequivocal evidence of a long overlap of humans and megafauna...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói Field và Wroe lập luận rằng các phát hiện tại Cuddie Springs cho thấy con người và đại động vật sống cùng thời kỳ (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">at the same time</em>). Điều này trùng khớp hoàn toàn với cụm \"unequivocal evidence of a long overlap of humans and megafauna\" (bằng chứng rõ ràng về một sự chồng chéo/giao thoa thời gian dài giữa người và đại động vật) trong bài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“...and conclude that aridity leading up to the last Ice Age brought about their eventual demise.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nêu thông tin là Field và Wroe kết luận rằng sự khô hạn dẫn tới Kỷ băng hà cuối cùng đã gây ra sự tuyệt chủng (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">demise</em>) của đại động vật nói chung, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"175\">hoàn toàn không đề cập</strong> hay phân loại xem các loài đại động vật có kích thước nhỏ hơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"261\">smaller megafauna species</em>) có sống sót qua Kỷ băng hà hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. NO</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The dating of these layers is accurate: ages for the sediments were obtained through radiocarbon dating of charcoal fragments and luminescence dating of sand grains from the same levels...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi khẳng định các tác giả bài viết (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">the writers</em>) tin rằng việc đo niên đại của các lớp đất sâu đến 1.7m là không đáng tin cậy (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">unreliable</em>). Tuy nhiên, ngay đầu đoạn 3, tác giả lại khẳng định điều ngược lại: \"The dating of these layers is accurate\" (Việc đo niên đại của các lớp này là chính xác). Vì thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"361\">NO</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. YES</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Intriguingly, some of the stone tools show surface features indicating their use for processing plants, and a few even have well-preserved blood and hair residues suggesting they were used in butchering animals.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói một số cổ vật được bảo quản đủ tốt để tiết lộ chức năng của chúng (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">reveal their function</em>). Bài đọc viết một số công cụ đá có các đặc điểm bề mặt biểu thị chúng dùng để chế biến thực vật (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"211\">processing plants</em>) và một số vẫn lưu lại dấu vết máu và lông (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"273\">blood and hair residues</em>) chứng minh dùng để xẻ thịt động vật (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"335\">butchering animals</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e513d517-5fa6-4765-bc6f-12e00e167508', 'b0579c69-ec6c-4d40-8118-4f1c848840aa', 'matrix', 'Questions 20-23', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A-G</strong>, in boxes 20-23 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Ted Michaels", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Joergen Fenhann", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Joan Marc Simon", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Tim Burns", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Incineration does not encourage responsible attitudes to waste disposal.", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Recycling can sometimes create serious problems for the future.", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Greater consumerism leads to higher levels of waste.", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Proper systems are needed for the recycling of environmentally-friendly products.", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Landfill is better for the environment than incineration.", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "Incineration of waste is now relatively harmless to the environment.", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "Efforts to reduce waste may affect profits for some types of companies.", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Ted Michaels — {F. Incineration of waste is now relatively harmless to the environment.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">According to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">Ted Michaels</strong>, president of the US-based Energy Recovery Centre, ‘There has been constant evolution in combustion engineering… and the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">output from these facilities is now minuscule</strong>.’</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “output… is now minuscule” (lượng chất thải ra giờ đây là cực nhỏ/không đáng kể) tương ứng với việc việc đốt rác giờ đây tương đối vô hại (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">relatively harmless</strong>) đối với môi trường nhờ công nghệ hiện đại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Joergen Fenhann — {C. Greater consumerism leads to higher levels of waste.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">‘It’s a problem for the developed nations,’ says <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">Joergen Fenhann</strong>… ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">The more you develop, the more you produce, buy and throw away</strong>.’</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu nói “Càng phát triển, bạn càng sản xuất, mua sắm và vứt bỏ nhiều hơn” chính là sự khẳng định rằng chủ nghĩa tiêu dùng tăng cao (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">greater consumerism</strong>) dẫn đến mức độ rác thải lớn hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"198\">higher levels of waste</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Joan Marc Simon — {D. Proper systems are needed for the recycling of environmentally-friendly products.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">As <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">Simon</strong> points out, however, without the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">right mechanisms</strong> in place ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">nothing guarantees that this bottle will end up being properly collected and treated</strong> in the appropriate recycling facility’.</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Right mechanisms” tương ứng với “proper systems”. Simon lập luận rằng dù sản phẩm có thân thiện với môi trường đến đâu (như cái chai được thiết kế tốt), nếu không có hệ thống phù hợp để thu gom và xử lý thì cũng vô ích.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Tim Burns — {G. Efforts to reduce waste may affect profits for some types of companies.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">Tim Burns</strong>… says… ‘You can argue about… not buying it in the first place — if you do that, then <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">that’s money the retailers don’t get</strong>, so it’s not always clear-cut.’</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Retailers don’t get money” chính là việc ảnh hưởng đến lợi nhuận của các công ty bán lẻ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">affect profits</strong>). Tim Burns chỉ ra rằng việc giảm tiêu thụ/giảm rác thải sẽ khiến các nhà bán lẻ thất thu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('53fce5e9-254e-40a2-a1e5-7c091a95a4d9', 'b0579c69-ec6c-4d40-8118-4f1c848840aa', 'fillup', 'Questions 24-26', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 24-26 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>What recent history tells us about recycling</strong></span></p>
<p>Richard Fisher, a researcher from Cranfield University, points out that the pace of consumerism has increased more quickly than was predicted in the 1980s. There has, for example, been unexpected growth in waste from {electronic} products. He suggests that the need to protect the environment should be linked to basic values, and adds that it might be better if consumers had more influence over {business} and more direction was provided by {government}.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. electronic — {unexpected growth in waste from electronic products}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Consumerism has developed at a pace we never expected. Nobody would have said there would be so much <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">electronic</strong> waste.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Richard Fisher nhấn mạnh rằng không ai có thể ngờ tới lượng rác thải điện tử (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">electronic</strong>) lại lớn đến như vậy. Từ “unexpected growth” trong tóm tắt tương ứng với cụm “nobody would have said… so much” trong bài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. business — {it might be better if consumers had more influence over business}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“We need to look at whether it’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">business</strong> that drives consumers or the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">other way around</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cấu trúc “the other way around” (theo chiều ngược lại) ám chỉ việc người tiêu dùng dẫn dắt/có ảnh hưởng lên doanh nghiệp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">business</strong>), thay vì doanh nghiệp định hướng người tiêu dùng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. government — {more direction was provided by government}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“You need <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">government</strong> to play a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">leadership role</strong>, whereas countries such as the UK seem to be stepping away…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Leadership role” (vai trò lãnh đạo) đồng nghĩa với việc đưa ra định hướng và chỉ dẫn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">direction</strong>). Tác giả cho rằng chính phủ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">government</strong>) cần đóng vai trò chủ chốt này thay vì né tránh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5cf43a14-eadd-4ced-b5a2-374b7e47e9fa', 'dae4fb3f-4936-4818-9843-2ab028e37843', 'matrix', 'Questions 27–32', NULL, '<p data-start="99" data-end="186">The text has eight paragraphs, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>H</strong>. Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "evidence that a rock found on Earth originated on Mars", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "a plan to analyse material on Mars", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "the reason Mars is no longer similar to Earth", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "an observation suggesting that there is currently water on Mars", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "a claim that construction had taken place on Mars", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "a possibility that humans and Martians could share the same origins", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"124\" data-end=\"136\"><strong data-start=\"127\" data-end=\"136\">27. D</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-start=\"138\" data-end=\"177\"><strong>Vị trí</strong>: Đoạn D, câu đầu và câu thứ hai.</li>\n<li data-start=\"179\" data-end=\"389\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"189\" data-end=\"192\">“The first is known as ALH84001, a meteorite that was blasted into space when a large body struck Mars 15 million years ago and which spiralled across the solar system to crash into the Antarctic.”</li>\n<li data-start=\"391\" data-end=\"579\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D nói về thiên thạch ALH84001 có nguồn gốc từ sao Hỏa và rơi xuống Nam Cực. Đây chính là bằng chứng cho thấy một tảng đá được tìm thấy trên Trái Đất có xuất xứ từ sao Hỏa.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"586\" data-end=\"598\"><strong data-start=\"589\" data-end=\"598\">28. G</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-start=\"600\" data-end=\"624\"><strong>Vị trí: </strong>Đoạn G, câu đầu.</li>\n<li data-start=\"626\" data-end=\"816\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"636\" data-end=\"639\">“Current projects are hoping to clarify the question… aimed at conducting experiments to detect the presence of a substance called carbon 13 in soil and rock samples on Mars.”</li>\n<li data-start=\"818\" data-end=\"972\"><strong>Giải thích: </strong>Đoạn G nói rõ các dự án hiện tại sẽ tiến hành thí nghiệm phân tích mẫu đất và đá trên sao Hỏa → đúng với “a plan to analyse material on Mars”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"979\" data-end=\"991\"><strong data-start=\"982\" data-end=\"991\">29. E</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-start=\"993\" data-end=\"1019\"><strong>Vị trí</strong>: Đoạn E, phần giữa.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1021\" data-end=\"1151\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1031\" data-end=\"1034\">“Mars lost its magnetic field several billion years ago… Without that protection, Mars’s gases and water boiled off.”</li>\n<li data-start=\"1153\" data-end=\"1299\"><strong>Giải thích: </strong>Sao Hỏa mất từ trường → không giữ được khí quyển → nước và khí bay hơi. Đây là lý do vì sao sao Hỏa ngày nay không còn giống Trái Đất.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"1306\" data-end=\"1318\"><strong data-start=\"1309\" data-end=\"1318\">30. F</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-start=\"1320\" data-end=\"1345\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn F, phần đầu.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1347\" data-end=\"1433\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1357\" data-end=\"1360\">“water from underground reservoirs still gushes through Martian valleys…”</li>\n<li data-start=\"1435\" data-end=\"1557\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Câu này cho thấy có khả năng hiện tại vẫn còn nước dưới lòng đất trên sao Hỏa → phù hợp với “currently water”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"1564\" data-end=\"1576\"><strong data-start=\"1567\" data-end=\"1576\">31. A</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-start=\"1578\" data-end=\"1604\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn A, phần giữa.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1606\" data-end=\"1687\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1616\" data-end=\"1619\">“These canals… had been built by technologically advanced Martians…”</li>\n<li data-start=\"1689\" data-end=\"1812\"><strong>Giải thích: </strong>Có tuyên bố rằng người sao Hỏa đã xây dựng kênh đào → đây là “claim that construction had taken place on Mars”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"1819\" data-end=\"1831\"><strong data-start=\"1822\" data-end=\"1831\">32. H</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-start=\"1833\" data-end=\"1859\"><strong>Vị trí: </strong>Đoạn H, phần giữa.</li>\n<li data-start=\"1861\" data-end=\"1972\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"1871\" data-end=\"1874\">“If DNA is located, it would mean that life on Mars and on Earth may spring from the same source.”</li>\n<li data-start=\"1974\" data-end=\"2101\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nếu tìm thấy DNA, sự sống trên sao Hỏa và Trái Đất có thể cùng chung nguồn gốc → đúng với “share the same origins”.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('70f6e80c-291d-4ea2-b461-67d5f35f2612', 'dae4fb3f-4936-4818-9843-2ab028e37843', 'radio', 'Questions 33–36', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "the Martians were physically similar to humans"}, {"content": "the Martian environment resembled that of Earth"}, {"content": "members of the Martian race were extremely primitive"}, {"content": "the climatic conditions on Mars were very dry"}], "question": "The 18th-century astronomer William Herschel believed that"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "The appearance of some regions of Mars changed"}, {"content": "Evidence of organisms was found on Mars"}, {"content": "The Martian atmosphere was tested scientifically"}, {"content": "Earlier beliefs about Mars were disproven"}], "question": "What does the writer say happened in the 1960s?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "organisms can survive on Mars"}, {"content": "organisms on Earth are like those found on Mars"}, {"content": "Martian conditions resemble those in Earth’s volcanoes"}, {"content": "Martian crystals can survive acid conditions"}], "question": "The study of extremophiles suggests that"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "scientific discussion."}, {"content": "media reports"}, {"content": "a work of literature."}, {"content": "a magazine illustration"}], "question": "At the end of the 19h century, the public''s ideas about Martians changed because of"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"2108\" data-end=\"2173\"><strong data-start=\"2110\" data-end=\"2173\">33. Đáp án: the Martian environment resembled that of Earth</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2175\" data-end=\"2190\">Vị trí: Đoạn A.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2192\" data-end=\"2260\">Dẫn chứng:<br data-start=\"2202\" data-end=\"2205\">“its inhabitants enjoy a situation similar to our own.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2262\" data-end=\"2391\">Giải thích: Herschel tin rằng điều kiện trên sao Hỏa tương tự Trái Đất → không nói về ngoại hình người sao Hỏa, mà là môi trường.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2393\" data-end=\"2396\">\n<p data-start=\"2398\" data-end=\"2457\"><strong data-start=\"2400\" data-end=\"2457\">34. Đáp án: Earlier beliefs about Mars were disproven</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2459\" data-end=\"2474\">Vị trí: Đoạn C.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2476\" data-end=\"2568\">Dẫn chứng:<br data-start=\"2486\" data-end=\"2489\">“pictures not of a world covered in vegetation… but of cratered, arid deserts.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2570\" data-end=\"2681\">Giải thích: Những hình ảnh từ tàu thăm dò đã bác bỏ niềm tin trước đó rằng sao Hỏa có thảm thực vật và sự sống.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"2683\" data-end=\"2686\">\n<p data-start=\"2688\" data-end=\"2735\"><strong data-start=\"2690\" data-end=\"2735\">35. Đáp án: organisms can survive on Mars</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2737\" data-end=\"2752\">Vị trí: Đoạn D.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2754\" data-end=\"2857\">Dẫn chứng:<br data-start=\"2764\" data-end=\"2767\">“living organisms could survive Mars’s harshness… provided by the study of extremophiles…”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2859\" data-end=\"3002\">Giải thích: Vi khuẩn cực đoan (extremophiles) sống được trong môi trường khắc nghiệt trên Trái Đất → gợi ý sự sống có thể tồn tại trên sao Hỏa.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2859\" data-end=\"3002\"><strong>36</strong>. Đáp án: a work of literature. (một tác phẩm văn học)</p>\n<p data-start=\"2859\" data-end=\"3002\"><strong>Vị trí</strong>: Đoạn B.<br /><strong>Dẫn chứng</strong>: &#8220;The vision of an advanced culture&#8230; was taken up by the British writer H.G. Wells in 1898 in his masterpiece The War of the Worlds&#8230; Martians became synonymous with grotesque, threatening aliens, at least as far as the public was concerned.&#8221;<br /><strong>Giải thích</strong>: * Đoạn A nói về các thảo luận khoa học (scientific discussion) của William Herschel và Percival Lowell, nhưng đây là giai đoạn khởi đầu khi họ tin rằng người Sao Hỏa là những người hàng xóm tiến bộ.</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3b831222-80d7-481e-8f00-1fcde8ae261e', '5659ac7c-e9b4-4d3f-a0f6-3a9967b1cefd', 'fillup', 'Questions 21 – 24', '<p><span class="fontstyle0">Complete the summary below.</span></p>
<p><span class="fontstyle0">Choose </span><span class="fontstyle2"><strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> </span><span class="fontstyle0">from the passage for each answer.</span></p>
<p><span class="fontstyle0">Write your answers in boxes 21–24 on your answer sheet.</span> </p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span class="fontstyle0" style="font-size: 14pt;">The development of a modern fashion industry</span></strong></p>
<p><span class="fontstyle2">Up until the middle of the 19th century, people generally wore handmade clothes. After that the situation changed, and by the 20th century many clothes were mass-produced.This development was partly due to inventions like the {sewing machine}</span><span class="fontstyle2">. It was also the result of general changes in manufacturing systems, as well as the spread of shops like </span><span class="fontstyle2">{department stores}. The changes also led to the standardisation of sizes and {fixed prices}</span><span class="fontstyle2">. Today, despite the fact that the fashion industry originated in {Europe}</span><span class="fontstyle2">, it has become a truly international enterprise.</span> </p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. sewing machine — {This development was partly due to inventions like the sewing machine.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“By the beginning of the 20th century, with the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">development of new technologies such as the sewing machine</strong>, the factory system of production...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự phát triển của ngành thời trang sản xuất hàng loạt vào đầu thế kỷ XX là nhờ vào các công nghệ mới/phát minh mới (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">new technologies / inventions</em>). Bài đọc đưa ra ví dụ điển hình đầu tiên chính là máy may (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"218\">sewing machine</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. department stores — {It was also the result of general changes in manufacturing systems, as well as the spread of shops like department stores.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...the factory system of production, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">the growth of department stores</strong> and other retail outlets...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"the spread of shops like...\" (sự lan rộng/phổ biến của các cửa hàng như...) tương ứng với \"the growth of... and other retail outlets\" (sự phát triển của... và các cửa hàng bán lẻ khác). Loại cửa hàng đại diện ở đây là các cửa hàng bách hóa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"261\">department stores</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. fixed prices — {The changes also led to the standardisation of sizes and fixed prices.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...clothing had increasingly come to be <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">mass-produced in standard sizes and sold at fixed prices</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự thay đổi trong hệ thống sản xuất đã dẫn đến việc quần áo được sản xuất hàng loạt theo kích cỡ tiêu chuẩn (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">standard sizes / standardisation of sizes</em>) và được bán với mức giá cố định (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">fixed prices</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Europe — {Today, despite the fact that the fashion industry originated in Europe, it has become a truly international enterprise.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Although the fashion industry developed first in Europe, today it is highly globalised</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"originated in\" (bắt nguồn/khởi nguồn tại) đồng nghĩa với cụm \"developed first in\" (phát triển đầu tiên ở). \"A truly international enterprise\" (một doanh nghiệp mang tính quốc tế thực sự) là cách viết khác của \"highly globalised\" (toàn cầu hóa cao). Quốc gia/Khu vực cần điền là châu Âu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"307\">Europe</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('00cf8eb5-1838-48b8-8042-4f1dae6c5729', 'ea4132a1-03f4-422f-9f7e-1bb35678bead', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Places to visit with children</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Alma Park</strong></p>
<ul>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>Go to the zoo.</p>
</li>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>A family ticket is $ {65} .</p>
</li>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>The fastest bus takes about {40} minutes.</p>
</li>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>You can hold some animals and have a {photo} for a small fee.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The Entertainment Room</strong></p>
<ul>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>John {Rosie} is performing.</p>
</li>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>Performance run from Tuesday to {Saturday} .</p>
</li>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>There is a {discount} on tickets for Monday night’s preview.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The City</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Go to the city center {museum} to see a special exhibition.</p>
</li>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>Do origami – we’ll need to take a small {box} .</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Bunyabbie Island</strong></p>
<ul>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>Explore with a four-wheel drive.</p>
</li>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>Go snorkelling at Salty Lake – it’s on the {Ocean} side of the Island.</p>
</li>
<li data-list="bullet">
<p>You’re not allowed to {camp} on the island.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> Good afternoon can I help you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Yes I&#8217;m looking for some places to visit when my sister and her children come to stay. They arrive this weekend from overseas. I&#8217;m new to the area and don&#8217;t really know what to recommend. Do you have any ideas?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> What about going to Alma Park to visit the zoo?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Ooh I like the idea of that. Is it reasonably priced?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> Yes, it&#8217;s not a bad price. A standard adult ticket is normally $30 but there&#8217;s a special deal for families of $<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">(1) </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">65</span></strong>, which is a saving of $35.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> That&#8217;s a great deal. How do we get there from the city?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> You can go by bus.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Is it very far?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> The 385 will get you there in approximately <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(2) 40</strong></span><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"> </span></strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">minutes depending on traffic<strong>.</strong></span></span><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"> </span>There is another bus, the 388, but it takes 20 minutes longer, so it&#8217;s worth waiting a few more minutes for the more direct bus.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Okay. Are there any special things to do there? Can you feed the animals or anything like that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">They&#8217;ve stopped that but most tourists love the fact that you&#8217;re allowed to hold some of the animals and get your </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(3) photo</strong> </span><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">taken</span>. They just ask you to make a small payment to help with costs.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh, the kids would love that. My sister also likes going to the theatre. Is there anything good on at the moment? She especially likes comedies.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> There&#8217;s a place called the Entertainment Room in Ascot. I&#8217;ll just check their website&#8230; hmm yes, there&#8217;s a festival running at the moment with John<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"> </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">(4) Rosie</strong></span></span> as the main entertainer. He&#8217;s really funny.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> How do we spell that? Is it R O Z Y?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> No it&#8217;s R O S I E.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Got it. And when is it on next week?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> It says it starts on Tuesday with a special matinee show on the Wednesday. It was supposed to finish on Friday but because of the demand it&#8217;s been extended to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"168\">(5) Saturday</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> It must be good then. Is it expensive?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> I don&#8217;t think so let&#8217;s see&#8230; oh it says there&#8217;s a special preview show on a Monday and they&#8217;re offering a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">(6) discount</strong></span> on tickets that night.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> We&#8217;ll try and go then. I also wanted to spend a day in the city centre. The children will get bored just looking at the shops. Is there anything else for them to do?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> What&#8217;s the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">(7) museum</strong></span> like? It&#8217;s very popular with children and there&#8217;s a very hands-on exhibition on at the moment.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> They&#8217;d love that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> Sounds good and there&#8217;s a workshop on where they learn how to do origami.</p>\n<div class=\"attachment-container search-images\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<div class=\"image-container ng-star-inserted\" data-full-size-image-uri=\"https://encrypted-tbn3.gstatic.com/licensed-image?q=tbn:ANd9GcSsL7bIKNlQ84dHAGLL6OyQ4uin6slj-hS8b4sWHTzX6uY7IFajBVttnDQpypuI7FCzPvfjU5CVjdykaV21oxg-gtYjjP6Cv7RXfKTKDoLsa8isCjw\">\n<div class=\"overlay-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></div>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Will they need to bring anything special for that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> On this leaflet it says that things like scissors and all of the paper are provided. They just advise children to bring a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">(8) box</strong></span> to carry the completed origami home in. Just a little one will do.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> I&#8217;m also looking for a weekend activity. I&#8217;ve heard Bunyabbie Island is great. Would we need a car to get around the island?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> A 4-wheel drive is a great way to explore. You should also try snorkelling at Salty Lake.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Is that in the centre of the island near the mountain?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> No it&#8217;s on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">(9) Ocean</strong></span> side.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Okay I&#8217;ll get a map and check it out. I&#8217;d like to stay there at least one night and I quite like the idea of taking a tent and sleeping out in the open air. Are you allowed to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"183\">(10) camp</strong></span> there?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> That would be lovely, but I&#8217;m afraid that&#8217;s not allowed on the island to protect the wildlife.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('00d8c439-fc94-4d51-ab5f-cf4a8ac5fd4d', 'dae4fb3f-4936-4818-9843-2ab028e37843', 'radio', 'Questions 37–40', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Lowell believed that Martian technology was more developed than human technology."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": " YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Information gained from Viking probes remains unchallenged"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There is evidence that there has been significant climate change on Mars"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": " YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Spanish scientists plan to launch space probes if DNA is found on Mars"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Lowell believed that Martian technology was more developed than human technology.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: YES</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> “Martian folk are possessed of <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">inventions of which we have not dreamed</strong>,” he (Lowell) argued.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “inventions of which we have not dreamed” (những phát minh mà chúng ta chưa từng mơ tới) ám chỉ công nghệ của người Hỏa tinh tiên tiến hơn công nghệ của con người hiện tại.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Information gained from Viking probes remains unchallenged.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NO</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C &amp; D):</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9,1,1\">\n<li>Đoạn C nói Viking tuyên bố Mars chính thức chết: “Mars was declared officially dead”.</li>\n<li>Đoạn D bắt đầu bằng: “Since that time, <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">two critical pieces of evidence have been found on Earth which support the idea that Mars has life</strong>.” (Kể từ đó, hai bằng chứng quan trọng đã được tìm thấy… ủng hộ ý tưởng Mars có sự sống).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kết luận “Mars đã chết” của tàu Viking đã bị thách thức (challenged) bởi các bằng chứng mới về thiên thạch ALH84001 và vi khuẩn cực hạn. Do đó, thông tin từ Viking không còn là “duy nhất” và “không bị thách thức”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. There is evidence that there has been significant climate change on Mars.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: YES</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> “…the Martian surface, although <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">hostile and arid today</strong>, was <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">once lush and welcoming</strong>… dried-up riverbeds and old estuaries.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự thay đổi từ trạng thái “lush and welcoming” (tươi tốt và hiếu khách) sang “hostile and arid” (khắc nghiệt và khô cằn) cùng với sự biến mất của sông ngòi là minh chứng cho một sự biến đổi khí hậu đáng kể (significant climate change).</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Spanish scientists plan to launch space probes if DNA is found on Mars.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn H):</strong> Tác giả nhắc đến Professor Juan Pérez Mercader (người Tây Ban Nha) bàn luận về tầm quan trọng của DNA và nói rằng: “The discovery… would also mean <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">renewed purpose for manned space flight projects</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói việc tìm thấy DNA sẽ tạo ra mục đích mới cho các dự án “manned space flight” (chuyến bay có người lái), nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">không hề nhắc đến</strong> việc các nhà khoa học Tây Ban Nha có kế hoạch cụ thể nào để “phóng tàu thăm dò” (launch space probes) hay không. Thông tin này thiếu tính xác thực trong bài.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8709d66e-fe54-431f-a258-dde14413c612', '8b6d8b6e-0c63-4fe0-a93c-aed421196e0b', 'fillup', 'Questions 11–16', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
