', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 2</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sarah:</strong> Welcome to Student Life. <span class=\"citation-633 citation-end-633\">It’s spring, and many of you may be thinking about arranging work for the long vacation. So, on today’s program, Roger Anwell reports on a survey we conducted into the pleasures and problems of vacation jobs. Roger.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Roger:</strong> Thank you, Sarah. <span class=\"citation-632 citation-end-632\">Well, the first thing to say is that by far the majority of students we surveyed did just three types of jobs. All of these obviously had their advantages and disadvantages.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"2\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><span class=\"citation-631 citation-end-631\">Starting with stocktaking in supermarkets. The thing that students said they enjoyed most about this job wa<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"3\"><!----></sup></span>s the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">(11) travelling</strong>. They were often required to go to branches to do their stocktakes, <span class=\"citation-629 citation-630 citation-end-630\">and this was regarded as an interesting plus. The main negative, however, was that they tended to find the job tiring, with long hours spent on their feet and climbing high shelves. Now, one thing we did ask the students in our survey was whether<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"4\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-629 citation-end-629\"> they had any recommendations for other people taking on their job, and they said, perhaps not surprisin<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"5\"><!----></sup></span>gly, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"552\">(12) <span class=\"citation-628\">get good shoes</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-628 citation-end-628\">. That&#8217;s the only way you can keep going.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"6\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-627 citation-end-627\">Another job which lots of students did was office work, and the positive feature of this actually rather surprised me, until I remembered what a hot summer it was last year. Lots of students named air conditioning as the best thing about office work. The downside which many talked about wa<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"7\"><!----></sup></span>s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"292\">(13) wearing formal clothes</strong></span>. Obviously, this didn&#8217;t go down too well with students. The advice most people gave was to select a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"420\">(14) large office</strong></span>. That way you have more variety of social contacts, otherwise the work can get very boring.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">The third job which had attracted large numbers of students was as a theme park attendant. And again, I got a surprise here, because the big plus people talked about was <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">(15) good pay</strong></span>. It must have improved since my day, I must say! Anyway, the downside I did recognize—having to deal with difficult customers, especially in the heat when tempers get frayed. Not easy. And people said that it was a good idea to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"412\">(16) live nearby</strong></span> &#8217;cause there&#8217;s a lot of shift work and you don&#8217;t have to worry about transport at difficult times of the day.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Roger:</strong> <span class=\"citation-625 citation-626 citation-end-626\">So those were the findings from the survey on the most common student jobs. But not all student jobs have to be mundane and boring. One of the students who responded in our survey spoke at length about his ama<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"8\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-625 citation-end-625\">zing job as a zoo attendant.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"9\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><span class=\"citation-624\">Peter Marshall had read about work opportunities </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"49\"><span class=\"citation-624 citation-end-624\">(<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"10\"><!----></sup></span>17) on the zoo website (B)</strong> </span><span class=\"citation-623 citation-end-623\">and just went along with a friend to talk to someone in personnel. He was offered a job there and then—as easy as that! In previous years, he’d done singularly unexciting shop work, so he was very pleased to be doing such<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"11\"><!----></sup></span> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"299\">(18) original work (C: unusual)</strong></span>.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><span class=\"citation-621 citation-622 citation-end-622\">He ended up working for just under three months, which was actually slightly more than he had anticipated and meant that he had to miss part of university term time, but he said it was well worth it because he thinks he&#8217;s found his future career path as a result of this experience. He loved working on the educational side in part<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"12\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-621\">icular, </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"339\"><span class=\"citation-621 citation-end-621\">(<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"13\"><!----></sup></span>19) helping young kids understand about the animals (B)</strong></span></span> in their natural environment. He said it was the most intriguing thing he’d ever done.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">He tells us, though, that with final exams coming up, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">(20) he won&#8217;t be able to do any paid work (A)</strong></span> this coming vacation. So why don&#8217;t you apply? If you&#8217;re interested in getting further information about the findings of the survey&#8230;</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8eaf89fe-9adb-4ebe-9da1-9d70e4a3aa9b', '1d2bfef5-1e0e-4669-8cef-c27e5ede3e03', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p><strong>The Red Sea Urchin</strong></p>
<p><strong>Background</strong></p>
<p>The red sea urchin:</p>
<ul>
<li>feeds on <span class="fill-history-correct">{plants}</span>  </li>
<li>is covered in <span class="fill-history-correct">{spines}</span> that protect it</li>
<li>used to be regarded as a  {pest}  </li>
</ul>
<p>From 1970s onwards:</p>
<ul>
<li>it became clear that <span class="fill-history-correct">{Asia}</span> was an important market for red sea urchins</li>
<li>scientific interest increased because of a <span class="fill-history-correct">{decline}</span> in red sea urchin population</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Research findings</strong></p>
<p><em>Study based on biochemical techniques</em></p>
<p><strong>Red sea urchins</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>grow very slowly</li>
<li>live a very long time (maximum life span: up to <span class="fill-history-correct">{200 years old}</span>)</li>
<li>can be harvested only after 6-7 years</li>
<li>after 22 years, only grow <span class="fill-history-correct">{0.1 of a centimetre|0.1 of a centimeter|0.1 centimetre|0.1 centimeter}</span> per year</li>
</ul>
<p>Study measuring radio carbon</p>
<ul>
<li>no evidence of <span class="fill-history-correct">{ageing|aging}</span> when sea urchins die</li>
<li>they can still <span class="fill-history-correct">{breed}</span> and grow when very old</li>
<li>growth not connected to <span class="fill-history-correct">{ocean conditions}</span> or other external factors</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7218e8a8-fb4b-4b3d-b41a-7ca92503f264', '8b6d8b6e-0c63-4fe0-a93c-aed421196e0b', 'radio', 'Questions 17–20', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "from a collenge friend."}, {"content": "on the computer."}, {"content": "from a student job centre."}], "question": "Peter learned about the job"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "easy."}, {"content": "challenging."}, {"content": "unusual."}], "question": "Peter mainly enjoyed the job because it was"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "learning about the environment."}, {"content": "working with children."}, {"content": "caring for the animals."}], "question": "The job’s most interesting aspect was"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "won’t take a job."}, {"content": "will work at the zoo."}, {"content": "will work elsewhere."}], "question": "Peter has decided that next vacation he"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d3dede7e-3e3b-4722-9223-e1e4fb8f5f4c', '5d6e5cea-a4e9-4718-b0e0-a7ffffbefd9f', 'radio', ' Questions 21–24', NULL, '<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Choose the correct answers</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>PACIFIC TAPA CLOTH</strong></span></p>', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "the only tapa made today."}, {"content": "better quality than others."}, {"content": "put to a wider range of uses."}], "question": "Pacific tapa cloth is different from other types of tapa cloth because it is"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "It is also a source of food."}, {"content": "It is not native to the Pacific."}, {"content": "It can grow in any environment."}], "question": "What does Helen say about the paper mulberry tree?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "They could not find the right trees in New Zealand."}, {"content": "They were introduced to other fabrics by the Europeans."}, {"content": "They found a better material for making fabric."}], "question": "Why did Maori people of New Zealand stop making tapa?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "stuck together."}, {"content": "woven together."}, {"content": "sewn together."}], "question": "Large pieces of tapa are made from smaller pieces which are"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 3</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Come in Helen. How can I help you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> Well, I’m doing research for the anthropology assignment and I was hoping to check a few details.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Sure. You chose the topic of Pacific Island tapa cloth, didn’t you? What have you found out so far?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> Well, I was going to introduce my assignment by saying that the tapa cloth <span class=\"citation-764 citation-end-764\">is a fabric made from bark—just the outer layer of the trees. It’s particularly common in the Pacific Islands, but not exclusive to them. In fact, many other peoples around the world have made high quality cloth from bark. But what sets Pacif<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>ic tapa apart is the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"345\">(21) incredible variety of roles it’s played in this region (C)</strong>.</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, nice introduction. Though, I think you could be more specific regarding dates.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> Okay. So what about the raw materials used? Well, tapa cloth is made from several species of tree. In the Pacific, the paper mulberry tree is most common, but it doesn’t thrive in all conditions. In fact, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"212\">(22) it wasn’t originally found in the islands, but was carried in their canoes by the first migrants (B)</strong></span>. Tapa is also made from the breadfruit tree, which is convenient because its fruit is a staple food. The paper mulberry tree is only grown for tapa making, though.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, that’s good. Now, what about the Maori people here in New Zealand?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> But the Maori don’t make tapa now.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> That’s right, and you need to account for it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> <span class=\"citation-763 citation-end-763\">We know that when Maori migrated here from the other Pacific islands, they were prepared to make tapa because they brought the paper mulberry tree with them. The thing was, after they’d been in New Zealand a bit<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"2\"><!----></sup></span>, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"220\">(23) they found the flax plant, which is superior to tapa because it makes a stronger fabric (C)</strong>.</span></span> By the time Europeans arrived in the 18th century, Maori were making all their fabric from flax and had been for some time.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Okay. So with the production process itself?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> First, the inner bark is beaten with wooden hammers to soften the fibres. Then the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">(24) different pieces are glued together using an adhesive paste made from the arrowroot tuber (A)</strong></span>. This is the only way to fabricate large pieces of cloth because bark strands are too fine to be woven together and stitching isn’t strong enough.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> So now you need details about different countries. Where would you start?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> I think Samoa is the obvious place. It’s famous for its very fine cloth called siapo, which is hand painted with representations of the ancestors. Still today, at the most profound events in life such as births, funerals, weddings and the investiture of chiefs, Samoans wear siapo robes to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"297\">(25) add significance and meaning to the ceremony (C: Spiritual)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Okay. Then I could talk about Tonga.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> It seems to me that the great innovation in Tonga has been developing a simple, coarse cloth which is quick and easy to make. This is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">(26) suitable for all sorts of everyday functions around the house like bed covers, mosquito nets and curtains (B: Practical)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Good point. Now, what about Cook Islands tapa?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> Well, the soil there is poor quality, so the breadfruit tree is often used. One type of thick cloth called tikoru was wrapped around the poles and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"154\">(27) used to mark the entrances to places of worship (C: Spiritual)</strong></span>, so it was highly regarded in local culture.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> You might mention Fiji as well, which is interesting because tapa was actually <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">(28) used as a currency there (D: Commercial)</strong></span>. Fijians used to sail between the islands and exchange tapa for other commodities like canoes or pigs.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> I know that in Tahiti the tapa cloth is different because the patterns are in colour, which is considered more valuable than the usual brown patterns.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> You’re right about the Tahitians using coloured pigments, but they aren’t more valuable. The colours are only a decoration. People enjoy wearing bright robes, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"166\">(29) especially for dancing and competitive games, and do it just for fun (A: Recreational)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Helen:</strong> Oh, I’ll make a note of that. Well, the last place I was going to mention was Tikopia. Even today, it’s commonplace to see people wearing clothes made of tapa cloth. In many of the other islands, the tapa only comes out on special occasions, but here, you see <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"267\">(30) people working in the gardens wearing tapa (B: Practical)</strong>.</span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Sounds promising, Helen. I’ll look forward to reading your assignment.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e15b4685-8bcc-401e-a7d6-591a9a0be6ba', '4eeb856a-ca65-42d1-8b38-9ed76fcc9e10', 'radio', 'Questions 1–8', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information ,<strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information ,<strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information about this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Harvard and Yale were the first universities to benefit from philanthropy."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Merchants liked to donate to the same universities they attended themselves"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The first gift to the University of Auckland came in 1884."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The University of Otago often received larger gifts than Gillies’ gift to Auckland."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the 1930s the government wanted to close Auckland’s engineering school."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "After raising $6,500, Crookes returned to academic life"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the 1950s the best lecturers chose to work in Britain or Australia rather than Auckland."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A single philanthropist was responsible for the new Medical School."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Harvard and Yale were the first universities to benefit from philanthropy. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“This has been true from some of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">oldest universities such as Bologna, Oxford and Cambridge in the twelfth century, to relative newcomers like the universities of Harvard and Yale in the seventeenth century</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ ra rằng các trường đại học lâu đời ở thế kỷ XII (Bologna, Oxford, Cambridge) đã được hưởng lợi từ việc hiến tặng trước. Harvard và Yale được gọi là \"những trường đến sau\" (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"196\">relative newcomers</em>) ở thế kỷ XVII. Vì vậy, khẳng định Harvard và Yale là những trường <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"282\">đầu tiên</strong> (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"292\">the first</em>) nhận tài trợ là sai sự thật (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"332\">FALSE</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Merchants liked to donate to the same universities they attended themselves. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Wealthy merchants</strong> gave young institutions money, land, libraries and rare items.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc các thương nhân giàu có (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">wealthy merchants</em>) hiến tặng tiền bạc, đất đai, thư viện cho các trường đại học non trẻ. Tuy nhiên, bài viết <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"171\">hoàn toàn không đề cập</strong> đến việc họ có xu hướng quyên góp cho chính ngôi trường mà họ từng theo học (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"271\">the same universities they attended</em>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. The first of the gifts to the University of Auckland came in 1884. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">1884</strong> Mr Justice Gillies made history when he gave $3,000 to the then very young University of Auckland, and so <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">became its original philanthropist</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Chữ \"original\" mang nghĩa là đầu tiên, nguyên bản. Việc ông Gillies tặng tiền vào năm 1884 và trở thành nhà hảo tâm đầu tiên (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">original philanthropist</em>) đồng nghĩa với việc món quà đầu tiên đến vào năm 1884. Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"228\">TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. The University of Otago often received larger gifts than Gillies’ gift to Auckland. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Gillies’ gift was <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">more generous even than those regularly given to New Zealand’s older University of Otago</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc viết rằng món quà của Gillies thậm chí còn \"hào phóng hơn\" (<em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">more generous</em>) những món quà thường xuyên được tặng cho Đại học Otago. Do đó, việc câu hỏi nói Đại học Otago thường nhận được những món quà \"lớn hơn\" (<em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"231\">larger gifts</em>) món quà của Gillies là hoàn toàn ngược lại (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"289\">FALSE</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. In the 1930s the government wanted to close Auckland’s engineering school. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In that decade [1930s] a local engineer... launched a fund to save the engineering school in Auckland, <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">which the state was determined to see discontinued</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"The state\" đóng vai trò paraphrase cho \"the government\" (chính phủ/nhà nước). Cụm từ \"determined to see discontinued\" (quyết tâm muốn thấy nó bị đình chỉ/dừng hoạt động) đồng nghĩa với việc muốn đóng cửa ngôi trường đó (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"233\">wanted to close</strong>). Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"261\">TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. After raising $6,500, Crookes returned to academic life. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...and raised over $6,500 in three years.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nói Samuel Crookes là một cựu giảng viên (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">former lecturer</em>) và ông đã gây quỹ thành công hơn 6.500 đô-la trong 3 năm. Tuy nhiên, bài viết <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">không hề nhắc đến</strong> việc sau khi gây quỹ xong thì ông có quay trở lại con đường nghiên cứu/giảng dạy học thuật (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"270\">returned to academic life</em>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. In the 1950s the best lecturers chose to work in Britain or Australia rather than Auckland. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In Auckland the problem largely resulted from the fact that academic salaries had slipped well behind those available in Britain and Australia, so <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"168\">the strongest candidates tended to be recruited to those countries</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"The strongest candidates\" tương ứng với những giảng viên giỏi nhất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">the best lecturers</strong>). Do mức lương ở Auckland thấp hơn nhiều so với Anh và Úc, những người giỏi nhất này có xu hướng được tuyển dụng/chọn làm việc ở các quốc gia đó (<em data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"246\">tended to be recruited to those countries</em>). Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"300\">TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. A single philanthropist was responsible for the new Medical School. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“But when the new Medical School opened in 1968, it <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">attracted significant gifts for academic positions and equipment from an unusually wide range of donors, including individuals, trusts, charitable foundations, societies and community groups</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trường Y mới mở nhận được sự tài trợ từ một mạng lưới các nhà tài trợ vô cùng rộng lớn và đa dạng (<em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">an unusually wide range of donors</em>) bao gồm nhiều cá nhân, các quỹ tín thác, quỹ từ thiện, các hội đoàn và nhóm cộng đồng. Vì vậy, câu hỏi khẳng định chỉ có một nhà hảo tâm duy nhất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"293\">a single philanthropist</strong>) chịu trách nhiệm cho trường này là sai hoàn toàn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"368\">FALSE</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('31e6506d-0a3c-48b6-841c-9f52883a3566', 'b2790d42-5a99-42e3-bf99-2b2d43408089', 'checkbox', 'Questions 25 and 26', '', '<p data-path-to-node="2">Choose <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="7">TWO</strong> letters, <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="20">A–E</strong>.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="3">Write the correct letters in boxes <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="35">25</strong> and <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="42">26</strong> on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A. His teacher recommended that he should go to university."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. His school record was not exceptional in any way."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C. He was helped by a former student of Cambridge University."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D. His parents were both valued by the people in their local area."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E. He originally planned to take up his father’s occupation."}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. C. He was helped by a former student of Cambridge University. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…his talents were recognised by a church official, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">Samuel Covell</strong>, who had <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">graduated from Cambridge University in 1600</strong>… Through his influence, Ray was admitted to Cambridge University in 1644…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Samuel Covell là người đã tốt nghiệp Đại học Cambridge (former student). Chính nhờ tầm ảnh hưởng và sự giúp đỡ của ông mà Ray mới có cơ hội vào học tại ngôi trường danh giá này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. D. His parents were both valued by the people in their local area. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“His father was a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">village blacksmith</strong> [một thợ rèn làng – nghề được coi trọng thời đó], and his mother was also a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">respected member of the community</strong>, a healer who was an expert in folk medicine…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cả cha và mẹ của Ray đều là những người được cộng đồng coi trọng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">valued/respected</strong>). Mẹ ông là một thầy thuốc dân gian giỏi, còn cha ông là thợ rèn của làng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7bd10aef-5332-4bd5-93b9-7efc5a48eb23', '5d6e5cea-a4e9-4718-b0e0-a7ffffbefd9f', 'matrix', 'Questions 25–30', NULL, '<p>According to the speakers, what function has tapa cloth played in the following countries?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A-D</strong>, for questions <strong>25-30</strong>.</p>', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of options", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Samoa", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Tonga", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Cook Islands", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Fiji", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Tahiti", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Tikopia", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "recreational", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "practical", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "spiritual", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "commercial", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7cb5d3f2-0467-468f-ac19-79acc934c460', '62be4939-7830-4a04-9e32-5b4beaf75f2e', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-40', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text   ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text   ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<h3 data-path-to-node="3">HEALTH ON THE NIGHT SHIFT</h3>
<p data-path-to-node="4"><strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="0">Background:</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="5">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-19" data-path-to-node="5,0,0">The number of night workers experienced a(n) {huge increase| increase} because of the number <span class="citation-95 citation-end-95">of 24-hour shopping /services<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="1"><!----></sup></span></p>
<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-20" data-path-to-node="5,1,0"><span class="citation-94 citation-end-94">need to examine effects of changing work and sleep habits US and British research found these lead to health problems<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="2"><!----></sup></span></p>
<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>
</ul>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-21" data-path-to-node="6"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-93 citation-end-93">Main Causes:<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="3"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="6"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="13"><span class="citation-92">A)</span></strong><span class="citation-92"> {internal clock| the internal clock}</span><span class="citation-92 citation-end-92"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="4"><!----></sup></span><!----></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="7">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-22" data-path-to-node="7,0,0"><span class="citation-91 citation-end-91">regulates daily life<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="5"><!----></sup></span><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-23" data-path-to-node="7,1,0"><span class="citation-90 citation-end-90">connected to behavioural patt<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="6"><!----></sup></span>erns and cycles of {light and dark}<!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,2,0">programmes us to be awake and asleep at certain times</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="8"><strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="0">B) Sleep Debt</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="9">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,0,0">impossible to get enough sleep during daytime</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="10"><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">C) </strong>{unsocial hours| the unsocial hours}</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="11">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="11,0,0">different working / sleeping times, leading to "dislocation"</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="12"><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">Effects:</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="12"><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="9">A) Physical</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="13">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="13,0,0">higher incidence of {heart} and {stomach} problems </p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="13,1,0">more minor illnesses, suggesting that immunity of shift workers is affected</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="14"><strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="0">B) Psychological</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="15">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="15,0,0">most common: {depression}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="15,1,0">{mental abilities} are severely affected, e.g. decision-making, planning, which regulates our {performance}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="16"><strong data-path-to-node="16" data-index-in-node="0">C) Social</strong> Night shift work can lead to:</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="17">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="17,0,0">destruction of {family|family life} and other relationships, e.g. {friends}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="17,1,0">eventually, for individuals: social isolation</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-section-id=\"yj9eer\" data-start=\"106\" data-end=\"146\">SECTION 4 – HEALTH ON THE NIGHT SHIFT</h2>\n<p data-start=\"148\" data-end=\"235\">Section 4. You will hear an extract from a talk entitled <strong data-start=\"205\" data-end=\"234\">Health on the Night Shift</strong>.</p>\n<p data-start=\"237\" data-end=\"309\">First you have some time to look at questions 31 to 40 on pages 8 and 9.</p>\n<p data-start=\"311\" data-end=\"362\">Now listen carefully and answer questions 31 to 40.</p>\n<p data-start=\"364\" data-end=\"389\">Good afternoon everybody.</p>\n<p data-start=\"391\" data-end=\"599\">In this session, I want to continue looking at health issues relating to the workplace, and I''d like to focus today on night shift workers and the health problems that are associated with their working hours.</p>\n<p data-start=\"601\" data-end=\"964\">I''m sure you''re all aware that there has been a<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(31) </strong><strong data-start=\"649\" data-end=\"666\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">h</span>uge increase</strong></span> in the number of workers doing regular night shifts in recent years, mainly because of the number of shops and services now open 24 hours, seven days a week. And we need to look more closely at the consequences of changing work and sleep patterns like this, so that''s what I''d like us to do today.</p>\n<p data-start=\"966\" data-end=\"1163\">Now research that has been carried out in both the US and Britain on night working suggests that it leads to a lot of health problems for the workers, and they point to three main reasons for this.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1165\" data-end=\"1700\">The first one is what they call <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(32) the internal clock</span></strong>, and this is a basic sort of program in our brains. This tells us that at certain times we should feel hungry, at other times we should be awake, at other times we should be asleep, and so on. And it seems to be generally accepted by all the experts in the field that this clock is linked to, um, not just our behavioural habits, but to cycles of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(33) light and dark</strong></span>. And that means that we''re programmed to be awake when it''s light, i.e. during the day, and asleep when it''s dark.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1702\" data-end=\"2200\">The second thing is that night workers are continually fighting against what is termed a sleep debt. And by this the researchers mean that, um, it''s just practically impossible for them to get a sufficient amount of sleep in daylight hours. In fact, studies suggest that on average night workers only get between five and six hours of sleep, rather than the eight they need. And the effects of not getting enough sleep can also lead to all sorts of problems, and we''ll talk about those in a minute.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2202\" data-end=\"2469\">The third cause of these problems is <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">34</span>) the unsocial hours</span></strong> that night workers have to keep, the fact that they are working when their families, their friends are sleeping and vice versa. And, um, that kind of dislocation from their social group can be very damaging.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2471\" data-end=\"2530\">Okay, so let''s take a closer look at some of these effects.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2532\" data-end=\"2983\">And if we have a look at the physical effects first, we can see that studies on long-term shift workers found that they were much more likely to get <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(35) heart</strong></span> problems than day workers. In addition, there seems to be a very high incidence of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(35) stomach</strong></span> problems, for example ulcers, among night shift workers. And although this may be partly due to the wrong sort of diet, you know, snacking on fast food, it can''t be just explained by eating habits.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2985\" data-end=\"3330\">And finally, there is evidence to suggest that night shift workers also get ill more frequently with minor problems like colds and infections. The frequency of these illnesses is much higher than among day workers, and this indicates that night working can damage immunity to illness. And of course, this leads to a lot of absence from work too.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3332\" data-end=\"3644\">However, although the physical impact of working nights can be severe, uh, perhaps the real problems are psychological ones. And the most common problem is <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(36) depression</strong></span>. This seems to be the inevitable result of the constant feeling of tiredness and a lack of energy that night workers universally complain of.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3646\" data-end=\"4055\">Secondly, there is a lot of evidence from accident statistics to suggest that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(37) mental abilities</strong></span> are badly affected, and that means, for example, decision-making ability and planning ability. And these are what control our<strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(38) performance</span></strong>. For example, we can see that the highest number of errors on the roads occur between 3:00 a.m. and 5:00 a.m., the point in our internal clock when we feel most sleepy.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4057\" data-end=\"4177\">Okay, finally, there are the social problems where night working impacts on the family and social life of the employees.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4179\" data-end=\"4349\">The first one is obviously the break up of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(39) family life</strong></span>. And here we can see from the divorce statistics that this occurs more frequently in the case of night workers.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4351\" data-end=\"4747\">But there''s also the breakdown of other relationships, not just within the family but among the peer group. Uh, night workers tend to lose touch with<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (40) friends</strong></span>, and these relationships, especially for the long-term night workers, are very difficult to rebuild. And so this eventually leads to social isolation for the individual, and of course that has consequences for the whole community too.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4749\" data-end=\"4847\">So we can begin to see the real cost of night working. What we need to do now is to look at how...</p>\n<p data-start=\"4849\" data-end=\"4928\">That is the end of Section 4. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4930\" data-end=\"5048\">That is the end of the listening test. You now have 10 minutes to transfer your answers to the listening answer sheet.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8d5a9fb5-6882-4f42-8597-09ea554c09f7', 'de6a1cd5-af53-4f9b-a3f1-cbfd3ad5d816', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
