<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text   ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<h3 data-path-to-node="3">HEALTH ON THE NIGHT SHIFT</h3>
<p data-path-to-node="4"><strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="0">Background:</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="5">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-19" data-path-to-node="5,0,0">The number of night workers experienced a(n) {huge increase| increase} because of the number <span class="citation-95 citation-end-95">of 24-hour shopping /services<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="1"><!----></sup></span></p>
<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-20" data-path-to-node="5,1,0"><span class="citation-94 citation-end-94">need to examine effects of changing work and sleep habits US and British research found these lead to health problems<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="2"><!----></sup></span></p>
<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>
</ul>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-21" data-path-to-node="6"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-93 citation-end-93">Main Causes:<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="3"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="6"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="13"><span class="citation-92">A)</span></strong><span class="citation-92"> {internal clock| the internal clock}</span><span class="citation-92 citation-end-92"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="4"><!----></sup></span><!----></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="7">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-22" data-path-to-node="7,0,0"><span class="citation-91 citation-end-91">regulates daily life<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="5"><!----></sup></span><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_f2d3149be19a69cd-23" data-path-to-node="7,1,0"><span class="citation-90 citation-end-90">connected to behavioural patt<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="6"><!----></sup></span>erns and cycles of {light and dark}<!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="7,2,0">programmes us to be awake and asleep at certain times</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="8"><strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="0">B) Sleep Debt</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="9">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="9,0,0">impossible to get enough sleep during daytime</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="10"><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">C) </strong>{unsocial hours| the unsocial hours}</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="11">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="11,0,0">different working / sleeping times, leading to "dislocation"</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="12"><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">Effects:</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="12"><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="9">A) Physical</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="13">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="13,0,0">higher incidence of {heart} and {stomach} problems </p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="13,1,0">more minor illnesses, suggesting that immunity of shift workers is affected</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="14"><strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="0">B) Psychological</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="15">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="15,0,0">most common: {depression}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="15,1,0">{mental abilities} are severely affected, e.g. decision-making, planning, which regulates our {performance}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="16"><strong data-path-to-node="16" data-index-in-node="0">C) Social</strong> Night shift work can lead to:</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="17">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="17,0,0">destruction of {family|family life} and other relationships, e.g. {friends}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="17,1,0">eventually, for individuals: social isolation</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-section-id=\"yj9eer\" data-start=\"106\" data-end=\"146\">SECTION 4 – HEALTH ON THE NIGHT SHIFT</h2>\n<p data-start=\"148\" data-end=\"235\">Section 4. You will hear an extract from a talk entitled <strong data-start=\"205\" data-end=\"234\">Health on the Night Shift</strong>.</p>\n<p data-start=\"237\" data-end=\"309\">First you have some time to look at questions 31 to 40 on pages 8 and 9.</p>\n<p data-start=\"311\" data-end=\"362\">Now listen carefully and answer questions 31 to 40.</p>\n<p data-start=\"364\" data-end=\"389\">Good afternoon everybody.</p>\n<p data-start=\"391\" data-end=\"599\">In this session, I want to continue looking at health issues relating to the workplace, and I''d like to focus today on night shift workers and the health problems that are associated with their working hours.</p>\n<p data-start=\"601\" data-end=\"964\">I''m sure you''re all aware that there has been a<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(31) </strong><strong data-start=\"649\" data-end=\"666\">huge increase</strong></span> in the number of workers doing regular night shifts in recent years, mainly because of the number of shops and services now open 24 hours, seven days a week. And we need to look more closely at the consequences of changing work and sleep patterns like this, so that''s what I''d like us to do today.</p>\n<p data-start=\"966\" data-end=\"1163\">Now research that has been carried out in both the US and Britain on night working suggests that it leads to a lot of health problems for the workers, and they point to three main reasons for this.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1165\" data-end=\"1700\">The first one is what they call <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(32) the internal clock</span></strong>, and this is a basic sort of program in our brains. This tells us that at certain times we should feel hungry, at other times we should be awake, at other times we should be asleep, and so on. And it seems to be generally accepted by all the experts in the field that this clock is linked to, um, not just our behavioural habits, but to cycles of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(33) light and dark</strong></span>. And that means that we''re programmed to be awake when it''s light, i.e. during the day, and asleep when it''s dark.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1702\" data-end=\"2200\">The second thing is that night workers are continually fighting against what is termed a sleep debt. And by this the researchers mean that, um, it''s just practically impossible for them to get a sufficient amount of sleep in daylight hours. In fact, studies suggest that on average night workers only get between five and six hours of sleep, rather than the eight they need. And the effects of not getting enough sleep can also lead to all sorts of problems, and we''ll talk about those in a minute.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2202\" data-end=\"2469\">The third cause of these problems is <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(34) the unsocial hours</span></strong> that night workers have to keep, the fact that they are working when their families, their friends are sleeping and vice versa. And, um, that kind of dislocation from their social group can be very damaging.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2471\" data-end=\"2530\">Okay, so let''s take a closer look at some of these effects.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2532\" data-end=\"2983\">And if we have a look at the physical effects first, we can see that studies on long-term shift workers found that they were much more likely to get <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(35) heart</strong></span> problems than day workers. In addition, there seems to be a very high incidence of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(35) stomach</strong></span> problems, for example ulcers, among night shift workers. And although this may be partly due to the wrong sort of diet, you know, snacking on fast food, it can''t be just explained by eating habits.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2985\" data-end=\"3330\">And finally, there is evidence to suggest that night shift workers also get ill more frequently with minor problems like colds and infections. The frequency of these illnesses is much higher than among day workers, and this indicates that night working can damage immunity to illness. And of course, this leads to a lot of absence from work too.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3332\" data-end=\"3644\">However, although the physical impact of working nights can be severe, uh, perhaps the real problems are psychological ones. And the most common problem is <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(36) depression</strong></span>. This seems to be the inevitable result of the constant feeling of tiredness and a lack of energy that night workers universally complain of.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3646\" data-end=\"4055\">Secondly, there is a lot of evidence from accident statistics to suggest that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(37) mental abilities</strong></span> are badly affected, and that means, for example, decision-making ability and planning ability. And these are what control our<strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(38) performance</span></strong>. For example, we can see that the highest number of errors on the roads occur between 3:00 a.m. and 5:00 a.m., the point in our internal clock when we feel most sleepy.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4057\" data-end=\"4177\">Okay, finally, there are the social problems where night working impacts on the family and social life of the employees.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4179\" data-end=\"4349\">The first one is obviously the break up of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(39) family life</strong></span>. And here we can see from the divorce statistics that this occurs more frequently in the case of night workers.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4351\" data-end=\"4747\">But there''s also the breakdown of other relationships, not just within the family but among the peer group. Uh, night workers tend to lose touch with<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (40) friends</strong></span>, and these relationships, especially for the long-term night workers, are very difficult to rebuild. And so this eventually leads to social isolation for the individual, and of course that has consequences for the whole community too.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4749\" data-end=\"4847\">So we can begin to see the real cost of night working. What we need to do now is to look at how...</p>\n<p data-start=\"4849\" data-end=\"4928\">That is the end of Section 4. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4930\" data-end=\"5048\">That is the end of the listening test. You now have 10 minutes to transfer your answers to the listening answer sheet.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0f96c488-2f38-44e8-8b10-4c571bc44bce', 'a85cdea7-bfce-461c-9c67-6c420c6886d9', 'checkbox', 'Questions 25 and 26', '', '<p data-path-to-node="2">Choose <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="7">TWO</strong> letters, <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="20">A–E</strong>.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="3">Write the correct letters in boxes <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="35">25</strong> and <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="42">26</strong> on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A. His teacher recommended that he should go to university."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. His school record was not exceptional in any way."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C. He was helped by a former student of Cambridge University."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D. His parents were both valued by the people in their local area."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E. He originally planned to take up his father’s occupation."}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. C. He was helped by a former student of Cambridge University. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…his talents were recognised by a church official, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">Samuel Covell</strong>, who had <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">graduated from Cambridge University in 1600</strong>… Through his influence, Ray was admitted to Cambridge University in 1644…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Samuel Covell là người đã tốt nghiệp Đại học Cambridge (former student). Chính nhờ tầm ảnh hưởng và sự giúp đỡ của ông mà Ray mới có cơ hội vào học tại ngôi trường danh giá này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. D. His parents were both valued by the people in their local area. — {ĐÚNG}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“His father was a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">village blacksmith</strong> [một thợ rèn làng – nghề được coi trọng thời đó], and his mother was also a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">respected member of the community</strong>, a healer who was an expert in folk medicine…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cả cha và mẹ của Ray đều là những người được cộng đồng coi trọng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">valued/respected</strong>). Mẹ ông là một thầy thuốc dân gian giỏi, còn cha ông là thợ rèn của làng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9054d509-f590-4453-a44f-0bdb31a70959', 'efb5f39e-f8d1-4ef7-ac9e-3006d952162f', 'radio', 'Questions 27-31', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter,<strong> A, B, C</strong> or <strong>D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Traditional negotiating practices should be used to supplement the software."}, {"option_text": "B. Success of the software depends on the accuracy of the assigned values."}, {"option_text": "C. This software anticipates the outcome of future events."}, {"option_text": "D. Future business negotiations will be dominated by this software."}], "question": "What does the writer suggest about game theory software in the first paragraph?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. participants are honest about how they feel."}, {"option_text": "B. there is a good understanding of the client''s culture."}, {"option_text": "C. people strongly dislike the other party."}, {"option_text": "D. profit is the primary motivator."}], "question": "Reinier van Oosten says predicting what people will do works best if"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. buy big licences."}, {"option_text": "B. negotiate with the other parties directly."}, {"option_text": "C. make one big offer at the end of the auction."}, {"option_text": "D. purchase a mix of licences."}], "question": "After using game theory software in 2006, Dr Milgrom instructed his clients to"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. show the impact new competitors have on business."}, {"option_text": "B. highlight the importance of location on business success."}, {"option_text": "C. demonstrate that businesses must follow a strategy."}, {"option_text": "D. clarify how pricing affects sales."}], "question": "The writer refers to Stephen Black''s ice-cream seller example in order to"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. a solution is proposed by one of the interested parties."}, {"option_text": "B. mediators or computers take over the bargaining process."}, {"option_text": "C. both parties follow the rules of negotiating."}, {"option_text": "D. sufficient time is allowed for the bargaining process."}], "question": "Ponsati believes business negotiations are more likely to progress if"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. What does the writer suggest about game theory software in the first paragraph? — {C. This software anticipates the outcome of future events.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…can <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">make forecasts</strong>… to work out how <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">events will unfold</strong>… and hence <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">predicts the course of events</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Forecasts”, “how events will unfold” (sự việc sẽ diễn ra như thế nào) và “predicts” (dự đoán) đều đồng nghĩa với cụm “<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">anticipates the outcome of future events</strong>” (dự đoán kết quả của các sự kiện trong tương lai).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. Reinier van Oosten says predicting what people will do works best if — {D. profit is the primary motivator.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“However, sorting out people’s motivations is <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">much easier when making money is the main object</strong>. Accordingly, modelling behaviour using game theory is proving <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">especially useful when applied to economics</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Van Oosten cho rằng dự đoán sẽ không chính xác nếu con người hành động theo cảm xúc. Ngược lại, việc dự đoán sẽ hiệu quả nhất khi mục tiêu chính là tiền bạc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">making money is the main object</strong>), tương ứng với việc lợi nhuận là động lực chính (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"252\">profit is the primary motivator</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. After using game theory software in 2006, Dr Milgrom instructed his clients to — {D. purchase a mix of licences.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Milgrom’s clients were then directed to obtain a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">collection of smaller, less expensive licences instead</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thay vì mua các giấy phép lớn bị định giá quá cao, phần mềm chỉ dẫn khách hàng mua một tập hợp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">collection</strong>) các giấy phép nhỏ hơn. Từ “collection” trong bài tương ứng với từ “<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"187\">mix</strong>” (sự kết hợp/pha trộn) trong đáp án.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. The writer refers to Stephen Black’s ice-cream seller example in order to — {A. show the impact new competitors have on business.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Introduce a <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">third seller</strong>, however, and the stifling <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">equilibrium is broken</strong> as relocations and pricing changes <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">energise the market</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ví dụ về người bán kem thứ ba cho thấy khi có thêm một đối thủ cạnh tranh mới (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">third seller/new competitors</strong>), trạng thái bế tắc bị phá vỡ và thị trường trở nên năng động hơn. Tác giả dùng ví dụ này để minh họa tầm ảnh hưởng của đối thủ mới đối với hoạt động kinh doanh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. Ponsati believes business negotiations are more likely to progress if — {B. mediators or computers take over the bargaining process.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Ponsati’s idea was that if a <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">human mediator</strong> was not trusted, affordable, or available, a <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">computer could do the job instead</strong>… such ‘mediation machines’ could be employed to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"185\">push negotiations forward</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ponsati cho rằng đàm phán dễ bế tắc nếu không ai chịu tiết lộ mức giá tối đa. Giải pháp là sử dụng người hòa giải (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">mediators</strong>) hoặc máy móc/phần mềm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">computers</strong>) để nắm giữ thông tin bí mật và đưa ra đề xuất giúp đàm phán tiến triển (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"244\">progress/push forward</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('28dfebab-8bde-451f-96bf-62bc49b6fc50', '7f431135-bc3d-4ad3-8e56-1886656104df', 'fillup', 'Questions 21 – 24', '<p><span class="fontstyle0">Complete the summary below.</span></p>
<p><span class="fontstyle0">Choose </span><span class="fontstyle2"><strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> </span><span class="fontstyle0">from the passage for each answer.</span></p>
<p><span class="fontstyle0">Write your answers in boxes 21–24 on your answer sheet.</span> </p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span class="fontstyle0" style="font-size: 14pt;">The development of a modern fashion industry</span></strong></p>
<p><span class="fontstyle2">Up until the middle of the 19th century, people generally wore handmade clothes. After that the situation changed, and by the 20th century many clothes were mass-produced.This development was partly due to inventions like the {sewing machine}</span><span class="fontstyle2">. It was also the result of general changes in manufacturing systems, as well as the spread of shops like </span><span class="fontstyle2">{department stores}. The changes also led to the standardisation of sizes and {fixed prices}</span><span class="fontstyle2">. Today, despite the fact that the fashion industry originated in {Europe}</span><span class="fontstyle2">, it has become a truly international enterprise.</span> </p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. sewing machine — {This development was partly due to inventions like the sewing machine.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“By the beginning of the 20th century, with the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">development of new technologies such as the sewing machine</strong>, the factory system of production...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự phát triển của ngành thời trang sản xuất hàng loạt vào đầu thế kỷ XX là nhờ vào các công nghệ mới/phát minh mới (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">new technologies / inventions</em>). Bài đọc đưa ra ví dụ điển hình đầu tiên chính là máy may (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"218\">sewing machine</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. department stores — {It was also the result of general changes in manufacturing systems, as well as the spread of shops like department stores.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...the factory system of production, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">the growth of department stores</strong> and other retail outlets...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"the spread of shops like...\" (sự lan rộng/phổ biến của các cửa hàng như...) tương ứng với \"the growth of... and other retail outlets\" (sự phát triển của... và các cửa hàng bán lẻ khác). Loại cửa hàng đại diện ở đây là các cửa hàng bách hóa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"261\">department stores</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. fixed prices — {The changes also led to the standardisation of sizes and fixed prices.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...clothing had increasingly come to be <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">mass-produced in standard sizes and sold at fixed prices</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự thay đổi trong hệ thống sản xuất đã dẫn đến việc quần áo được sản xuất hàng loạt theo kích cỡ tiêu chuẩn (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">standard sizes / standardisation of sizes</em>) và được bán với mức giá cố định (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">fixed prices</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Europe — {Today, despite the fact that the fashion industry originated in Europe, it has become a truly international enterprise.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Although the fashion industry developed first in Europe, today it is highly globalised</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"originated in\" (bắt nguồn/khởi nguồn tại) đồng nghĩa với cụm \"developed first in\" (phát triển đầu tiên ở). \"A truly international enterprise\" (một doanh nghiệp mang tính quốc tế thực sự) là cách viết khác của \"highly globalised\" (toàn cầu hóa cao). Quốc gia/Khu vực cần điền là châu Âu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"307\">Europe</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6532150f-89e0-4f5d-b312-b024d47186e7', '8828f744-4029-443b-817c-ac50888ac301', 'fillup', 'Questions 5–8', '<p data-section-id="1lzk6qv" data-start="615" data-end="646">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p data-start="648" data-end="706">Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p data-section-id="1bqdvh1" data-start="767" data-end="795"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Making buildings with wood</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="797" data-end="950">Wood is a traditional building material, but current environmental concerns are encouraging {architects} to use wood in modern construction projects.</p>
<p data-start="952" data-end="1636">Using wood, however, has its challenges. For example, as {moisture} in the atmosphere enters wood, it increases in size. In addition, wood is prone to pests and the risk of fire is greater. However, wood can be turned into a better construction material if it is treated and combined with other materials. In one process, {layers} of solid wood are glued together to create building blocks. These blocks are lighter than concrete and steel but equal them in strength. Experts say that wooden buildings are an improvement on those made of concrete and steel in terms of the {speed} by which they can be constructed and how much noise is generated by the process.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. architects — {...current environmental concerns are encouraging architects to use wood...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“...but climate change is driving architects to turn to treated timber as a possible resource.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ \"environmental concerns\" (mối lo ngại về môi trường) đồng nghĩa với \"climate change\" (biến đổi khí hậu). Từ \"encouraging\" (khuyến khích/thúc đẩy) đồng nghĩa với động từ \"driving\". Đối tượng được thúc đẩy chuyển sang dùng gỗ chính là các kiến trúc sư (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"266\">architects</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. moisture — {For example, as moisture in the atmosphere enters wood...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Wood expands as it absorbs moisture from the air and is susceptible to pests, not to mention fire.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm \"in the atmosphere\" (trong khí quyển) đồng nghĩa với \"from the air\" (từ không khí). Hiện tượng gỗ bị tăng kích thước, phình to ra (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">expands / increases in size</em>) là do nó hấp thụ độ ẩm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"200\">moisture</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. layers — {In one process, layers of solid wood are glued together...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“An adhesive is used to stick layers of solid-sawn timber together, crosswise, to form building blocks.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ \"glued together\" (được gắn keo lại với nhau) đồng nghĩa với cụm từ \"an adhesive is used to stick... together\". Thứ được dán lại với nhau từ các khối gỗ xẻ đặc chính là các lớp gỗ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"195\">layers</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. speed — {...in terms of the speed by which they can be constructed...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Construction experts say that wooden buildings can be constructed at a greater speed than ones of concrete and steel...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"at a greater speed\" (ở một tốc độ lớn hơn) tương ứng với từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">speed</strong> cần điền vào chỗ trống nhằm thể hiện khía cạnh ưu điểm về tiến độ thi công nhanh của nhà gỗ so với nhà bê tông cốt thép.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d83892e4-1de7-46eb-9408-49e0dbd40168', 'b00a168f-5b03-41d5-8d79-4c31b644c48b', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The amount of research on giraffes in their natural environment has increased lately"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Megan Strauss disapproves of keeping giraffes in zoos"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The number of giraffes in Africa has nearly doubled"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Female giraffes tend to live longer than males"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mother giraffes sometimes use their legs to defend their young"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Younger bulls hold their necks higher in the presence of more powerful males"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Male giraffes have been observed fighting"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. TRUE — The amount of research on giraffes in their natural environment has increased lately.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“All that is changing fast, as a growing number of researchers seek to understand the biology and complex behavior of this graceful giant in its native habitat.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói số lượng nghiên cứu về hươu cao cổ trong môi trường tự nhiên tăng lên gần đây (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">increased lately</em>). Bài đọc xác nhận mọi thứ đang thay đổi nhanh chóng với số lượng các nhà nghiên cứu ngày càng tăng (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"221\">a growing number of researchers</em>) đang tìm cách thấu hiểu chúng tại môi trường sống bản địa (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"313\">native habitat / natural environment</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. NOT GIVEN — Megan Strauss disapproves of keeping giraffes in zoos.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“''When I first became interested in giraffes in 2008 and started looking through the scientific literature, I was really surprised to see how little had been done,'' said Megan Strauss...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ trích dẫn lời Megan Strauss bày tỏ sự ngạc nhiên khi thấy có quá ít nghiên cứu khoa học về loài này ngoài tự nhiên vào năm 2008, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">hoàn toàn không có thông tin</strong> nào nói về việc cô ấy phản đối hay không ủng hộ (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"235\">disapproves</em>) việc nuôi nhốt hươu cao cổ trong vườn thú.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. FALSE — The number of giraffes in Africa has nearly doubled.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The giraffe is not listed as endangered, but researchers point to evidence that in the past 15 years, the population has fallen some 40 percent.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi khẳng định số lượng hươu cao cổ ở Châu Phi đã tăng gần gấp đôi (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">nearly doubled</em>). Ngược lại, bài đọc đưa ra bằng chứng rằng trong 15 năm qua, quần thể của chúng đã bị giảm khoảng 40% (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">fallen some 40 percent</em>). Thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"272\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. NOT GIVEN — Female giraffes tend to live longer than males.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Female giraffes can live 20 years or more, and it makes sense they might rely on each other for clues to the best feeding grounds...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có cung cấp số liệu hươu cao cổ cái có thể sống từ 20 năm trở lên (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">live 20 years or more</em>), nhưng trong toàn bộ bài viết <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">không hề có sự so sánh</strong> tuổi thọ giữa con cái và con đực xem con nào có xu hướng sống lâu hơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"234\">live longer</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. TRUE — Mother giraffes sometimes use their legs to defend their young.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Giraffe calves are extremely vulnerable to predators, and though mothers will fight valiantly to keep their young alive — kicking forward and backward — half of all calves are killed in their first year of life.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói hươu cao cổ mẹ đôi khi dùng chân để bảo vệ con (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">use their legs to defend</em>). Bài đọc viết rằng các bà mẹ sẽ chiến đấu quả cảm để giữ con sống sót bằng hành động \"đá về phía trước và phía sau\" (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"215\">kicking forward and backward</strong>). Hành động đá (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"260\">kicking</em>) này chính là việc sử dụng chân.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. FALSE — Younger bulls hold their necks higher in the presence of more powerful males.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“But should a dominant older bull come into view, the younger males instantly try to make themselves look small and innocent.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói hươu cao cổ đực trẻ tuổi sẽ giữ cổ cao hơn khi có mặt các con đực quyền lực hơn. Ngược lại, bài đọc chỉ ra rằng nếu một con đực lớn thống trị xuất hiện (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"177\">dominant older bull come into view / more powerful males</em>), các con đực trẻ ngay lập tức cố gắng làm cho bản thân trông nhỏ bé và ngây thơ đi (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"319\">try to make themselves look small</em>). Thông tin bị trái ngược nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"393\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. TRUE — Male giraffes have been observed fighting.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Clashes have been witnessed between adults when each bull repeatedly ''necks'' the other, using his massive neck to slam his head against his rival.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói các con hươu cao cổ đực được quan sát thấy đang đánh nhau (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">observed fighting</em>). Bài đọc xác nhận các cuộc đụng độ đã được chứng kiến (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">Clashes have been witnessed</em>) khi chúng dùng chiếc cổ khổng lồ để quật đầu vào đối thủ (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"244\">slam his head against his rival</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b169f638-1925-4820-9cd1-c3b21efae17a', 'b00a168f-5b03-41d5-8d79-4c31b644c48b', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the table below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<div dir="ltr" align="left">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-color: #000000; border-style: solid; height: 614.983px; width: 92.8428%;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 20.6989%;" width="154"><col style="width: 56.3172%;" width="419"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 63.9931px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Physical features</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Study findings</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 65px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Skin/Coat</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Provides {camouflage} when standing near trees</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 63.9931px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Eyes</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Let them look out for lions</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 65px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Mouth</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Can be used like {hands} to get leaves</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 120px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Neck</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">About equal in length to the legs</p>
<p dir="ltr">Length develops in childhood to provide an easier {birth} for mothers</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 85px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Cardiovascular system</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Extra strong {veins} keep blood from spilling into other tissue</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 65px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">{heart}</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Normal size for such a large animal</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 86.9965px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Nerves</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr">Slower reaction time because {signals} need to go farther to the brain</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. camouflage — {Provides camouflage when standing near trees}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The coat has dark patches separated by light hair, which serves as camouflage, allowing them to blend in with the light and shade patterns of the acacia trees...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lớp lông của hươu cao cổ đóng vai trò như là sự ngụy trang (<strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">camouflage</strong>), giúp chúng hòa mình vào hoa văn sáng tối của cây keo nhằm ẩn nấp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. hands — {Can be used like hands to get leaves}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“In addition, a giraffe''s extraordinary mouth has lips and tongue that can together grasp a branch and then pluck away the leaves while avoiding thorns, almost as humans would grab with their hands.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bộ phận môi và lưỡi của hươu cao cổ có thể cùng nhau phối hợp để bứt lá giống như con người cầm nắm bằng đôi tay (<strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">hands</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. birth — {Length develops in childhood to provide an easier birth for mothers}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The growth of the neck largely takes place during early childhood, as giraffe mothers would have a difficult time giving birth to young with longer necks.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự phát triển chiều dài cổ diễn ra ở giai đoạn thơ ấu vì nếu con non sinh ra có cổ quá dài, hươu mẹ sẽ gặp khó khăn trong quá trình sinh đẻ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"153\">birth / giving birth</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. veins — {Extra strong veins keep blood from spilling into other tissue}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The outside of a giraffe''s veins are extremely thick, to prevent blood leaking into surrounding tissue.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thành bên ngoài của các tĩnh mạch (<strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">veins</strong>) rất dày giúp ngăn chặn máu bị rò rỉ/tràn vào các mô xung quanh (<em data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">keep blood from spilling / prevent blood leaking into surrounding tissue</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. heart — {heart: Normal size for such a large animal}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Researchers were also surprised to find that a giraffe does not have an unusually large heart.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cột đặc điểm đang nói về một bộ phận cơ thể có kích thước bình thường chứ không to bất thường. Bài đọc chỉ ra bộ phận gây bất ngờ vì không hề lớn bất thường chính là trái tim (<strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"188\">heart</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. signals — {Slower reaction time because signals need to go farther to the brain}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“This is because signals from the nerves travel at about the same speed in giraffes as in rats or other mammals. Given the greater distance they have to travel in the giraffe to reach the brain...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thời gian phản ứng của hươu cao cổ bị chậm đi là do các tín hiệu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">signals</strong>) từ dây thần kinh phải di chuyển một quãng đường dài hơn nhiều để đến được não bộ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5883abe4-e375-47ec-9c76-f2af7e7a371f', 'efb5f39e-f8d1-4ef7-ac9e-3006d952162f', 'radio', 'Questions 32-35', '', '<p><span class="citation-2923">Choose</span><strong data-path-to-node="12,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-2923"> YES</span></strong><span class="citation-2923 citation-end-2923"> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer,<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="3"><!----></sup></span><strong data-path-to-node="12,1,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-2922">NO</span></strong><span class="citation-2922 citation-end-2922"> if the statement cont<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="4"><!----></sup></span>radicts the claims of the writer,<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><strong data-path-to-node="12,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Game theory software may be unhelpful when dealing with political issues."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Dr Milgrom was confident about applying his software to an auction in 2006."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Dr Ponsati believes ''mediation machines'' are an inappropriate method of negotiation in areas other than business."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Military organisations refuse to accept that software based on game theory could prevent wars."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Game theory software may be unhelpful when dealing with political issues. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…feeding software with accurate data on all the players involved is <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">especially tricky for political matters</strong>… Reinier van Oosten… notes that <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"167\">predictions may become unreliable</strong> when people unexpectedly give in to ‘non-rational emotions’…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “especially tricky” (đặc biệt khó khăn) và “unreliable” (không đáng tin cậy) đồng nghĩa với việc phần mềm có thể “không giúp ích nhiều” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"153\">unhelpful</strong>) trong các vấn đề chính trị do yếu tố cảm xúc chi phối.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Dr Milgrom was confident about applying his software to an auction in 2006. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">He was apprehensive at first</strong>, but the result was a triumph.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói ông ấy “tự tin” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">confident</strong>), nhưng bài đọc lại dùng từ “<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">apprehensive</strong>” (lo lắng, e ngại). Vì hai thông tin này trái ngược nhau hoàn toàn nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">NO</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Dr Ponsati believes ‘mediation machines’ are an inappropriate method of negotiation in areas other than business. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Could mediation which has been achieved using software… spread from auction bids… to <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">resolving political and military disputes</strong>? Today’s game theory software is <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"185\">not yet sufficiently advanced</strong> to mediate between warring countries.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc hiện nay phần mềm chưa đủ tiên tiến để hòa giải các cuộc xung đột quốc gia, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\">không hề nói</strong> Dr Ponsati tin rằng đó là một phương pháp “không phù hợp” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"191\">inappropriate</strong>). Thực tế, bà còn kỳ vọng vào khả năng của nó trong tương lai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Military organisations refuse to accept that software based on game theory could prevent wars. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“According to some game theorists, opponents could learn how a war would turn out, skip the fighting and strike a deal.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả có nêu ý tưởng của các nhà lý thuyết trò chơi về việc dùng phần mềm để ngăn chặn chiến tranh, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">không có thông tin</strong> nào nói về phản ứng của các tổ chức quân sự (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"184\">military organisations</strong>) hay việc họ “từ chối chấp nhận” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"241\">refuse to accept</strong>) điều này.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('29c2402e-fc5f-42df-aadd-3885c37874bf', 'efb5f39e-f8d1-4ef7-ac9e-3006d952162f', 'matching', 'Questions 36-40', '', '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, <strong>A-F</strong>, below.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A-F</strong>, in boxes 36-40 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_sentence_endings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "something is thought to be worth more than it really is."}, {"optionText": "discussions between the parties begin to break down."}, {"optionText": "too much information is given to the other parties early on."}, {"optionText": "businesses consider possible future developments."}, {"optionText": "people allow their feelings to influence decisions."}, {"optionText": "a solution requires face-to-face negotiation."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "According to Reinier van Oosten, game theory software fails when-", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": "Dr Milgrom''s software is successful in detecting if", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "Dr Black''s game theory software is a helpful tool when", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "According to Dr Ponsati, negotiators fall behind if", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"questionPart": "Dr Ponsati''s mediation machine is useful when", "correctAnswer": "B"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. According to Reinier van Oosten, game theory software fails when — {E. people allow their feelings to influence decisions.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…predictions may become <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">unreliable</strong> when people unexpectedly give in to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">‘non-rational emotions’</strong>, such as hatred…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Phần mềm “thất bại” (fails/unreliable) khi con người để cho “cảm xúc không lý trí” (non-rational emotions/feelings) như sự thù hận chi phối quyết định của mình.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Dr Milgrom’s software is successful in detecting if — {A. something is thought to be worth more than it really is.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…the software estimated the secret values bidders placed on specific licences, and determined that certain <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">big licences were being overvalued</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Phần mềm của Milgrom phát hiện ra các giấy phép lớn đang bị “định giá quá cao” (overvalued), tương ứng với việc chúng được cho là “có giá trị hơn thực tế” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"168\">worth more than it really is</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Dr Black’s game theory software is a helpful tool when — {D. businesses consider possible future developments.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…the use of modelling makes clients <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">more inclined to look at future repercussions</strong> when making business decisions, Black says.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Phần mềm của Dr Black giúp khách hàng cân nhắc các “hệ quả trong tương lai” (future repercussions), tương ứng với cụm “<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">future developments</strong>” (những phát triển trong tương lai) khi đưa ra quyết định kinh doanh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. According to Dr Ponsati, negotiators fall behind if — {C. too much information is given to the other parties early on.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">first side to disclose the maximum amount</strong> that it is willing to pay <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">loses considerable bargaining power</strong>. Without leverage, it can be <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">pushed backwards</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Người đàm phán sẽ “bị tụt lại phía sau/yếu thế” (fall behind/pushed backwards) nếu là bên đầu tiên tiết lộ giá tối đa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">disclose the maximum amount</strong>) quá sớm (early on).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Dr Ponsati’s mediation machine is useful when — {B. discussions between the parties begin to break down.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“But if neither side reveals the concessions… <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">negotiations can become very slow or collapse</strong>. However, difficult negotiations can often be <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">pushed along by neutral mediators</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Máy hòa giải (mediation machine) hữu ích khi các cuộc đàm phán trở nên trì trệ hoặc “đổ vỡ” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">collapse/break down</strong>), giúp thúc đẩy quá trình này tiến triển lại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5298fca7-4928-4a7d-b284-1c96962106f5', '8828f744-4029-443b-817c-ac50888ac301', 'matrix', 'Questions 1–4', '', '<p data-start="66" data-end="119">Which section contains the following information?</p>
<p data-start="121" data-end="194">Write the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>H</strong></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "an explanation of the industrial processes that create potential raw materials for concrete", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "a reference to the various locations where high-rise wooden buildings can be found", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "an indication of how widely available the raw materials of concrete are", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "the belief that more high-rise wooden buildings are needed before wood can be regarded as a viable construction material", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. G — an explanation of the industrial processes that create potential raw materials for concrete</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Fly ash, a byproduct of coal-burning power plants, can be incorporated into concrete mixes... Iron-ore slag, a byproduct of the iron-ore smelting process, can be used in a similar way.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn G giải thích về quy trình công nghiệp tạo ra các nguyên liệu thô tiềm năng thay thế xi măng trong hỗn hợp bê tông: tro bay là phụ phẩm của nhà máy nhiệt điện đốt than (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"185\">byproduct of coal-burning power plants</em>), và xỉ quặng sắt là phụ phẩm của quá trình luyện kim quặng sắt (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"289\">byproduct of the iron-ore smelting process</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. D — a reference to the various locations where high-rise wooden buildings can be found</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Vancouver, Vienna and Brumunddal in Norway are all home to constructed tall, wooden buildings.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Various locations\" (các địa điểm khác nhau) và \"high-rise wooden buildings\" (tòa nhà gỗ cao tầng) được chỉ đích danh qua chuỗi địa danh: thành phố Vancouver (Canada), Vienna (Áo) và Brumunddal ở Na Uy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. C — an indication of how widely available the raw materials of concrete are</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Not only are the ingredients of concrete relatively cheap and found in abundance in most places around the globe...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"How widely available\" (mức độ sẵn có rộng rãi) tương ứng hoàn toàn với cụm từ các thành phần của bê tông được tìm thấy với số lượng vô cùng phong phú, dồi dào ở hầu hết mọi nơi trên khắp quả địa cầu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"213\">found in abundance in most places around the globe</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. F — the belief that more high-rise wooden buildings are needed before wood can be regarded as a viable construction material</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“But even treated wood has its limitations and only when a wider range of construction projects has been proven in practice will it be possible to see wood as a real alternative to concrete in constructing tall buildings.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"More high-rise wooden buildings are needed\" (cần thêm nhiều tòa nhà gỗ cao tầng) tương ứng với điều kiện phải có một loạt các dự án xây dựng rộng lớn hơn được chứng minh trong thực tế (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"198\">a wider range of construction projects has been proven in practice</em>) thì mới có thể coi gỗ là vật liệu thay thế khả thi thực sự (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"326\">real alternative / viable construction material</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e998420f-ab64-4bfa-a85c-1bb6e6b856c0', '8828f744-4029-443b-817c-ac50888ac301', 'matrix', 'Questions 9–13', '', '<p data-start="1747" data-end="1810"><strong data-start="1747" data-end="1810">Match each statement with the correct person, A, B, C or D.</strong></p>
<p data-start="1812" data-end="1895">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="1838" data-end="1854">A, B, C or D</strong></p>
<p data-start="1897" data-end="1942"><strong data-start="1897" data-end="1903">NB</strong> You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of People", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The environmental advantage of cement alternatives may not be as great as initially assumed", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "It would be hard to create a construction alternative to concrete that offers so many comparable benefits", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Worries about the environment have led to increased interest in wood as a construction material", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Expense has been a factor in the negative response to the development of new cements", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "The environmental damage caused by concrete is due to it being produced in large quantities", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Chris Cheeseman", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Markus Mannström", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Anna Surgenor", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Felix Preston and Johanna Lehne", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. C (Anna Surgenor) — The environmental advantage of cement alternatives may not be as great as initially assumed.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“If they are transported over long distances, using fossil fuels, the use of alternative materials might not make sense from an overall carbon reduction perspective.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Anna Surgenor lập luận rằng nếu các vật liệu thay thế xi măng phải vận chuyển bằng đường biển/đường bộ từ khoảng cách rất xa và tiêu tốn nhiên liệu hóa thạch, thì lợi ích giảm thiểu carbon tổng thể sẽ không còn ý nghĩa nữa. Tức là lợi thế môi trường không lớn như lầm tưởng ban đầu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. A (Chris Cheeseman) — It would be hard to create a construction alternative to concrete that offers so many comparable benefits.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Making anything with similar properties is going to be very difficult.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sau khi phân tích hàng loạt lợi điểm vượt trội của bê tông như giá rẻ, dồi dào, dễ đổ khuôn và có độ giãn nở nhiệt tương đồng với thép, Giáo sư Chris Cheeseman khẳng định việc tạo ra bất kỳ thứ gì có đặc tính tương tự sẽ là một thử thách cực kỳ gian nan (<em data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"267\">very difficult / hard to create</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. B (Markus Mannström) — Worries about the environment have led to increased interest in wood as a construction material.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“...the company is seeing increasing demand globally for building in wood, with climate change concerns the key driver.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Worries about the environment\" (lo ngại về môi trường) tương ứng với cụm từ \"climate change concerns\" (mối bận tâm về biến đổi khí hậu). Markus Mannström xác nhận đây chính là động lực cốt lõi (<em data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"207\">key driver</em>) dẫn tới nhu cầu xây dựng bằng gỗ tăng cao trên toàn cầu (<em data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"276\">increasing demand</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. D (Felix Preston and Johanna Lehne) — Expense has been a factor in the negative response to the development of new cements.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“At present, these alternatives are rarely as cost-effective as conventional cement, and they face raw-material shortages and resistance from customers.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hai nhà nghiên cứu Felix Preston và Johanna Lehne chỉ ra rằng các loại xi măng cải tiến hiếm khi có hiệu quả về mặt chi phí (<em data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"137\">rarely as cost-effective</em>) so với xi măng truyền thống, dẫn đến sự phản đối/kháng cự từ phía khách hàng (<em data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"241\">resistance from customers / negative response</em>). Chi phí (<em data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"298\">expense</em>) chính là rào cản lớn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. A (Chris Cheeseman) — The environmental damage caused by concrete is due to it being produced in large quantities.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“‘Concrete is not a high-carbon product. Cement is high carbon, but concrete is not. But it is the scale on which it is used that makes it high carbon.’”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Giáo sư Chris Cheeseman làm rõ một bản chất: bản thân bê tông không phải là sản phẩm có hàm lượng carbon cao, mà chính vì quy mô, sản lượng khổng lồ mà nó được sản xuất và sử dụng trên toàn thế giới (<em data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"212\">the scale on which it is used / produced in large quantities</em>) mới là tác nhân biến nó thành nguồn gây hại lớn cho môi trường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d2c2dd73-d656-47d5-988d-92ebfa7f67dc', 'bd160f6a-2966-494c-b0cd-f91ded4a3eb2', 'matching', 'Questions 14–20', '', '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "optionsTitle": "List of Headings", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. A period in cold conditions before the technology is assessed"}, {"optionText": "ii. Marketing issues lead to failure"}, {"optionText": "iii. Good and bad aspects of steam technology are passed on"}, {"optionText": "iv. A possible solution to the issues of today"}, {"optionText": "v. Further improvements lead to commercial orders"}, {"optionText": "vi. Positive publicity at last for this quiet, clean, fast vehicle"}, {"optionText": "vii. A disappointing outcome for customers"}, {"optionText": "viii. A better option than the steam car arises"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Paragraph A — iii {Good and bad aspects of steam technology are passed on}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“But these early cars inherited steam’s weaknesses along with its strengths.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tiêu đề \"iii\" nói về các khía cạnh tốt và xấu của công nghệ hơi nước được truyền lại. Điều này trùng khớp hoàn toàn với câu chủ đề của đoạn A: những chiếc xe đời đầu này thừa hưởng cả điểm yếu lẫn điểm mạnh từ công nghệ hơi nước (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"242\">inherited steam’s weaknesses along with its strengths</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Paragraph B — viii {A better option than the steam car arises}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“A new technology called the Internal Combustion Engine soon appeared, which offered the ability to drive down the road just moments after starting up.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tiêu đề \"viii\" đề cập đến việc xuất hiện một lựa chọn tốt hơn xe hơi nước. Đoạn B mô tả sự ra đời của Động cơ đốt trong (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">Internal Combustion Engine</em>) với ưu điểm vượt trội là khởi động xong đi được ngay chứ không phải chờ 20 phút như xe hơi nước.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Paragraph C — vi {Positive publicity at last for this quiet, clean, fast vehicle}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“...it drew the attention of automobile trade magazines due to its numerous improvements over previous steam cars.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tiêu đề \"vi\" nói về việc cuối cùng phương tiện yên tĩnh, sạch và nhanh này cũng được quảng bá tích cực. Đoạn C mô tả mẫu xe Model B thu hút sự chú ý của các tạp chí thương mại ô tô (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">drew the attention of automobile trade magazines</em>) nhờ vận hành êm ái (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"264\">virtual silence</em>) và tăng tốc cực nhanh (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"304\">amazingly swift</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Paragraph D — v {Further improvements lead to commercial orders}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“By the following April, the General Engineering Company had received 5,390 deposits for Doble Detroits, which were scheduled for delivery in early 1918.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tiêu đề \"v\" đề cập đến việc các cải tiến tiếp theo dẫn tới các đơn đặt hàng thương mại. Đoạn D kể về mẫu Model C với tính năng khởi động bằng chìa khóa trong cabin và kết quả là công ty nhận được 5,390 đơn đặt cọc mua xe (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"234\">5,390 deposits / commercial orders</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Paragraph E — vii {A disappointing outcome for customers}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Those buyers who received the handful of complete cars complained that the vehicles were sluggish and erratic, sometimes going in reverse when they should go forwards.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tiêu đề \"vii\" nói về kết quả gây thất vọng cho khách hàng. Đoạn E mô tả việc những người mua nhận xe đã phàn nẫm rằng xe chạy chậm chạp, thất thường và động cơ dính đầy lỗi nghiêm trọng (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">complained / disappointing outcome</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Paragraph F — i {A period in cold conditions before the technology is assessed}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“After sitting overnight in freezing temperatures, the car was pushed out into the road and left to sit for over an hour in the frosty morning air.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tiêu đề \"i\" nói về một khoảng thời gian nằm trong điều kiện lạnh giá trước khi công nghệ được đánh giá. Đoạn F mô tả chiếc Model E được để qua đêm trong nhiệt độ đóng băng và nằm hơn một tiếng trong không khí sương giá buổi sáng (<em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"242\">freezing temperatures / frosty morning air</em>) trước khi tiến hành vặn khóa kiểm tra bộ tăng áp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Paragraph G — iv {A possible solution to the issues of today}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Under the current pressure to improve automotive performance and reduce emissions, it is not unthinkable that the steam car may rise again.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tiêu đề \"iv\" nói về một giải pháp khả thi cho các vấn đề ngày nay. Đoạn G thảo luận về bối cảnh áp lực giảm thiểu khí thải môi trường hiện nay, việc một chiếc xe hơi nước đời cũ vẫn chạy sạch vượt qua luật khí thải nghiêm ngặt của California mở ra triển vọng công nghệ này có thể trỗi dậy một lần nữa (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"314\">rise again / possible solution</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('86b0e34f-1165-4278-ae80-5dc0a8648255', 'bd160f6a-2966-494c-b0cd-f91ded4a3eb2', 'radio', 'Questions 21–23', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B</strong>, <strong>C </strong>or <strong>D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Its success was short-lived"}, {"option_text": "B. Not enough cars were made"}, {"option_text": "C. Car companies found them hard to sell"}, {"option_text": "D. People found them hard to drive"}], "question": "What point does the writer make about the steam car in Paragraph B?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. constructed all the parts themselves"}, {"option_text": "B. made written notes at each stage of the construction"}, {"option_text": "C. needed several attempts to achieve a competitive model"}, {"option_text": "D. sought the advice of experienced people in the car industry"}], "question": "When building their first steam car, the Doble brothers"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. moved production to a different city"}, {"option_text": "B. raised financial capital"}, {"option_text": "C. employed an additional worker"}, {"option_text": "D. abandoned their earlier designs"}], "question": "In order to produce the Model C, the Doble brothers"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. A — Its success was short-lived.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“But the glory days of steam cars were few.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nhấn mạnh \"những ngày tháng hoàng kim của xe hơi nước rất ít ỏi\" (<em data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">glory days... were few</em>), đồng nghĩa với việc sự thành công của nó diễn ra trong một khoảng thời gian rất ngắn ngủi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"202\">short-lived</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. C — needed several attempts to achieve a competitive model.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Though it did not run well, the Doble brothers went on to build a second and third prototype in the following years.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi chế tạo chiếc xe đầu tiên, nó chạy không tốt. Anh em nhà Doble đã phải tiếp tục chế tạo nguyên mẫu thứ hai và thứ ba (<em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">build a second and third prototype</em>) thì mới tạo ra được mẫu Model B thành công và vượt trội. Ý này tương ứng với việc cần nhiều lần thử nghiệm để đạt được một mô hình có sức cạnh tranh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"320\">needed several attempts</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. B — raised financial capital.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“The following year Abner Doble drove the Model B from Massachusetts to Detroit in order to seek investment for his automobile design, which he used to open the General Engineering Company.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để sản xuất mẫu Model C, Abner Doble đã phải lái xe đến Detroit nhằm mục đích tìm kiếm nguồn vốn đầu tư (<em data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">seek investment</em>), sau đó dùng số tiền này để mở công ty. Hành động này chính là huy động vốn tài chính (<strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"221\">raised financial capital</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('40945d93-411c-49ed-8999-ed377ae73756', 'bd160f6a-2966-494c-b0cd-f91ded4a3eb2', 'fillup', 'Questions 24–26', '<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="fb6eddf3-3225-4688-a44d-381ddea05546" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling">
<p data-section-id="1lzk6qv" data-start="1653" data-end="1684">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p data-start="1686" data-end="1755">Choose <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.999%; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8778%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="border-color: #000000;">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="fb6eddf3-3225-4688-a44d-381ddea05546" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling">
<p style="text-align: center;" data-section-id="koiaet" data-start="1757" data-end="1770"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>The Model E</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="1772" data-end="2028">The Model E was road-tested in 1924 by the Automobile Club of America. They found it easy to drive, despite its weight, and it impressed the spectators. A later version of the Model E raised its <strong data-start="1967" data-end="1984">{speed}</strong>, while keeping its emissions extremely low.</p>
<p data-start="2030" data-end="2448" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">The steam car was too expensive for many people and its design was constantly being altered. Under <strong data-start="2129" data-end="2146">{50 | fifty}</strong> cars were produced before the company went out of business. However, even today, there are Model Es on the road in the US. They are straightforward to maintain, and they satisfy California''s <strong data-start="2338" data-end="2355">{strict}</strong> emissions laws. Perhaps today''s technology and materials would help us revive the steam car.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p data-section-id="koiaet" data-start="1757" data-end="1770"> </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. speed — {...raised its speed, while keeping its emissions extremely low.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“As the new Doble steamer was further developed and tested, its maximum speed was pushed to over a hundred miles per hour...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn tóm tắt nói về một phiên bản cải tiến sau này của Model E đã làm gia tăng cái gì của nó. Bài đọc chỉ ra \"tốc độ tối đa của nó được đẩy lên hơn 100 dặm/giờ\" (<em data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">maximum speed was pushed to...</em>), tức là làm tăng tốc độ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"231\">speed</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. 50 / fifty — {Under 50 / fifty cars were produced before the company went out of business.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“By the time the company folded in 1931, fewer than fifty of the amazing Model E steam cars had been produced.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ \"folded\" (phá sản/đóng cửa) trong bài đồng nghĩa với cụm \"went out of business\". Từ \"under\" (dưới/ít hơn) trong câu hỏi đồng nghĩa với từ \"fewer than\". Số lượng xe được sản xuất là dưới <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"201\">50</strong> (hoặc <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"210\">fifty</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. strict — {...and they satisfy California''s strict emissions laws.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Astonishingly, an unmodified Doble Model E runs cleaner enough to pass the emissions laws in California today, and they are pretty strict.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn tóm tắt cần một tính từ bổ nghĩa cho luật khí thải của bang California. Bài đọc viết luật khí thải ở đây \"pretty strict\" (khá là nghiêm khắc). Từ cần điền giữ nguyên là tính từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">strict</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d6a0230f-1a26-48d2-8d70-dd76c0c3ca72', '7f431135-bc3d-4ad3-8e56-1886656104df', 'checkbox', 'Questions 25 and 26', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> letters, <strong>A–E</strong>.</p>
<p>Write the correct letters in boxes 25 and 26 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> of the following statements does the writer make about garment assembly? </p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A The majority of sewing is done by computer-operated machines."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B Highly skilled workers are the most important requirement."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C Most businesses use other companies to manufacture their products."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D Fasteners and labels are attached after the clothes have been made up."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E Manufacturers usually produce one range of women’s clothing annually"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. C. Most businesses use other companies to manufacture their products.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_08cca3af44f65315-23\" data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<span class=\"citation-157\">Some companies use their own production facilities for some or all of the manufacturing process, </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\"><span class=\"citation-157 citation-end-157\">but the majority rely on separately owned manufacturing firms or contractors to produce garments to their specifications<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span></strong>.”</em></p>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định \"phần lớn các công ty\" (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">the majority</em>) dựa vào các hãng sản xuất độc lập hoặc bên nhà thầu (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">separately owned manufacturing firms or contractors</em>) để sản xuất quần áo theo yêu cầu. Ý này trùng khớp hoàn toàn với câu C: \"Hầu hết các doanh nghiệp (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"274\">Most businesses</em>) sử dụng các công ty khác (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"317\">other companies</em>) để sản xuất sản phẩm của họ\".</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. D. Fasteners and labels are attached after the clothes have been made up.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Assembled items then go through various processes collectively known as ‘finishing’. These include the addition of decorative elements, fasteners, brand-name labels</strong> and other labels...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Quá trình \"made up\" (ráp/khâu may xong xuôi quần áo) tương ứng với từ \"assembled items\" (các món đồ đã được lắp ráp/may xong). Sau công đoạn này, chúng mới trải qua các bước hoàn thiện (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"198\">finishing</em>) bao gồm việc đính thêm cúc/khóa kéo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"246\">fasteners</strong>) và nhãn mác (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"270\">labels</strong>). Do đó câu D là một khẳng định hoàn toàn chính xác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('83f59a64-3d51-476e-af12-4beb659626c5', 'a77c1d73-9329-47d3-940a-9e8d1944b39a', 'matching', 'Questions 31–35', '', '<h3 data-section-id="10k0eva" data-start="20" data-end="83">Complete the summary using the list of phrases, A–I, below.</h3>
<p data-start="85" data-end="156"><strong data-start="85" data-end="156">Write the correct letter, A–I</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<h1 data-section-id=\"3zb1ea\" data-start=\"158\" data-end=\"183\">Is streaming effective?</h1>\n<p data-start=\"185\" data-end=\"731\">According to Professor John Hattie of the Melbourne Education Research Institute, there is very little indication that streaming leads to <strong data-start=\"323\" data-end=\"342\">{H. higher achievements}</strong>. He points out that, in schools which use streaming, the most significant impact is on those students placed in the <strong data-start=\"459\" data-end=\"478\">{D. bottom sets}</strong>, especially where a large proportion of them have <strong data-start=\"529\" data-end=\"548\">{F. disadvantaged backgrounds}</strong>. Meanwhile, for the <strong data-start=\"569\" data-end=\"588\">{E. brightest pupils}</strong>, there appears to be only minimal advantage. A further issue is that teachers tend to have <strong data-start=\"680\" data-end=\"699\">{I. positive impressions}</strong> of students in streamed groups.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. wrong classes"}, {"optionText": "B. lower expectations"}, {"optionText": "C. average learners"}, {"optionText": "D. bottom sets"}, {"optionText": "E. brightest pupils"}, {"optionText": "F. disadvantaged backgrounds"}, {"optionText": "G. weaker students"}, {"optionText": "H. higher achievements"}, {"optionText": "I. positive impressions"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. H (higher achievements) — {...there is very little indication that streaming leads to higher achievements.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Professor John Hattie, director of the Melbourne Education Research Institute, notes that ‘tracking has minimal effects on learning outcomes’.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói có rất ít biểu hiện cho thấy việc chia lớp theo trình độ dẫn tới cái gì. Bài đọc trích lời Giáo sư Hattie rằng việc chia lớp (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">tracking/streaming</em>) chỉ có tác động cực kỳ tối thiểu lên kết quả học tập (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"224\">learning outcomes</em>). \"Minimal effects on learning outcomes\" tương ứng với việc nó không giúp dẫn tới thành tích học tập cao hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"352\">higher achievements</strong> - phương án H).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. D (bottom sets) — {...the most significant impact is on those students placed in the bottom sets...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“What is more, streaming appears to significantly – and negatively – affect those students assigned to the lowest sets.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác động đáng kể nhất của việc phân lớp nằm ở nhóm học sinh bị xếp vào các lớp có trình độ thấp nhất (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">assigned to the lowest sets</em>). Từ đồng nghĩa phù hợp hoàn toàn trong bảng từ là <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"193\">bottom sets</strong> (phương án D).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. F (disadvantaged backgrounds) — {...especially where a large proportion of them have disadvantaged backgrounds.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“These students tend to have much higher representation of low socioeconomic class.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhóm học sinh ở các lớp trình độ thấp này thường có tỷ lệ đại diện rất cao từ tầng lớp kinh tế - xã hội thấp (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">low socioeconomic class</em>). Cụm từ học thuật này tương ứng với cụm từ chỉ hoàn cảnh khó khăn, nghèo hèn trong bảng từ là <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"241\">disadvantaged backgrounds</strong> (phương án F).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. E (brightest pupils) — {Meanwhile, for the brightest pupils, there appears to be...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Less significant is the small benefit for those lucky clever students in the higher sets.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngược lại, đối với những học sinh thông minh, may mắn ở các lớp nhóm trên (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">lucky clever students in the higher sets</em>), lợi ích thu lại cũng rất nhỏ. Cụm từ \"lucky clever students\" tương đương với cụm từ chỉ những học sinh sáng giá, thông minh nhất trong bảng từ là <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"276\">brightest pupils</strong> (phương án E).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. B (lower expectations) — {A further issue is that teachers tend to have lower expectations of students...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Streaming students by diagnosed achievement automatically limits what the teacher feels the student is capable of.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc phân tách học sinh dựa trên thành tích vô hình trung sẽ làm giới hạn những gì mà giáo viên nghĩ học sinh đó có thể làm được (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"142\">limits what the teacher feels the student is capable of</em>). Điều này nghĩa là giáo viên sẽ có xu hướng đặt kỳ vọng thấp hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"265\">lower expectations</strong> - phương án B) đối với học sinh.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><em data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Lưu ý: Bảng đáp án bạn cung cấp ghi phương án I - \"positive impressions\", tuy nhiên xét theo cấu trúc đối chiếu trực tiếp của bài đọc Cambridge, đáp án chuẩn xác về mặt ngữ nghĩa khảo thí bắt buộc phải là <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"206\">B - lower expectations</strong> vì phân lớp trình độ thấp sẽ làm thu hẹp/giảm kỳ vọng của giáo viên).</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bc9231d7-c973-4865-bb57-4b8018a56704', 'a77c1d73-9329-47d3-940a-9e8d1944b39a', 'radio', 'Questions 36–40', '', '<p>Choose <strong data-start="1112" data-end="1119">YES</strong> – if the statement agrees with the views of the writer, <strong data-start="1177" data-end="1183">NO</strong> – if the statement contradicts the views of the writer, <strong data-start="1241" data-end="1254">NOT GIVEN</strong> – if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Vygotsky model of education supports the concept of a mixed-ability class"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some teachers are uncertain about allowing students to take on MKO roles in the classroom"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It can be rewarding to teach knowledge which you have only recently acquired"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The priority should be to ensure that the highest-achieving students attain their goals"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Taking part in collaborative outdoor activities with teachers and classmates can improve student outcomes in the classroom"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. NO — The Vygotsky model of education supports the concept of a mixed-ability class.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“If we accept this model, it follows that streaming students with similar ZPDs would be an efficient and effective solution.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi khẳng định mô hình của Vygotsky ủng hộ khái niệm lớp học đa trình độ (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">supports mixed-ability</em>). Ngược lại, bài đọc chỉ ra rằng nếu đi theo mô hình Vygotsky (hướng tới vùng phát triển gần ZPD), logic kéo theo sẽ là việc phân tách học sinh có cùng trình độ (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"275\">streaming students</em>) mới là giải pháp hiệu quả và tối ưu. Vì thông tin mâu thuẫn trực diện nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"379\">NO</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. NOT GIVEN — Some teachers are uncertain about allowing students to take on MKO roles in the classroom.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“While teachers are traditionally the MKOs in classrooms, the value of knowledgeable student peers must not go unrecognised either.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ đề cập đến việc bên cạnh giáo viên, giá trị làm MKO (người am hiểu hơn) của các bạn học cùng trang lứa cũng cần phải được ghi nhận, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">hoàn toàn không có thông tin</strong> nào nói về việc một số giáo viên cảm thấy không chắc chắn hoặc phân vân (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"262\">uncertain</em>) về việc cho học sinh đảm nhận vai trò này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. YES — It can be rewarding to teach knowledge which you have only recently acquired.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“There is also something exciting about passing on skills and knowledge that you yourself have just mastered – a certain pride and zeal...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói việc dạy lại những kiến thức mà bạn vừa mới tiếp thu được (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">only recently acquired</em>) đem lại cảm giác thỏa mãn, xứng đáng (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">rewarding</em>). Điều này trùng khớp hoàn toàn với bài viết: có điều gì đó rất thú vị, hào hứng (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"237\">something exciting / a certain pride and zeal</em>) khi truyền đạt lại kỹ năng và kiến thức mà chính bạn vừa mới làm chủ được (<strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"359\">just mastered</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. NO — The priority should be to ensure that the highest-achieving students attain their goals.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“And today, more than ever, we need to value and flourish – not suffer at the expense of a few bright stars.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói ưu tiên hàng đầu nên là đảm bảo nhóm học sinh có thành tích cao nhất đạt được mục tiêu (<em data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">priority should be... highest-achieving students</em>). Ngược lại, tác giả khẳng định ngày nay chúng ta cần trân trọng sự đa dạng để tất cả cùng phát triển, chứ không phải chịu đựng sự hy sinh vì lợi ích của một vài ngôi sao sáng (<em data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"338\">not suffer at the expense of a few bright stars</em>). Thông tin bị trái ngược nên chọn <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"421\">NO</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. NOT GIVEN — Taking part in collaborative outdoor activities with teachers and classmates can improve student outcomes in the classroom.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Once a year, I go on a hike with my class, a mixed bunch of students... We make it – together.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả có kể câu chuyện trải nghiệm mỗi năm một lần dắt cả lớp đi leo núi (<em data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">go on a hike</em>) cùng nhau để học cách phối hợp và giúp đỡ nhau. Tuy nhiên, bài viết <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">hoàn toàn không đưa ra kết luận hay thông tin</strong> nào khẳng định việc tham gia các hoạt động ngoài trời này sẽ giúp cải thiện kết quả học tập của học sinh khi quay trở lại lớp học (<em data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"347\">improve student outcomes in the classroom</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('167e7999-5c61-4651-87c7-f75a2228d2e3', 'd847081f-29da-424a-bd52-986753b7892e', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon was famous for his work before he designed the Opera House"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon’s design was favoured by the four judges of the competition from the beginning."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": " Utzon’s knowledge of boats gave him the idea for parts of the Opera House."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon was impressed by the opera houses he had seen in Mexico."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon changed his designs in the 1960s after construction began."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Seidler defended Utzon’s role as architect."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Utzon went back to Australia in 1973 for the opening of the Opera House."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 1: Utzon was famous for his work before he designed the Opera House.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><em data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Utzon đã nổi tiếng với các công trình của mình trước khi thiết kế Nhà hát Opera.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng trong bài:</strong> Đoạn 2, câu 2: “…was won by Jorn Utzon, a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">relatively little-known architect</strong> from Denmark.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói rằng Jorn Utzon là một kiến trúc sư “tương đối ít tên tuổi” (relatively little-known) trước khi thắng cuộc thi. Điều này trái ngược hoàn toàn với từ “famous” (nổi tiếng) trong câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 2: Utzon’s design was favoured by the four judges of the competition from the beginning.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><em data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Thiết kế của Utzon được cả bốn giám khảo của cuộc thi ủng hộ ngay từ đầu.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng trong bài:</strong> Đoạn 2, câu 3-4: “The story goes that… American architect Eero Saarinen, arrived in Sydney after the other three judges had started assessing the entries. He looked through their <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"202\">rejected entries</strong> and stopped at the Utzon design…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc kể rằng 3 giám khảo đầu tiên đã bỏ qua (rejected) bài thi của Utzon. Chỉ khi giám khảo thứ 4 (Eero Saarinen) đến muộn và xem lại đống bài bị loại thì mới chọn nó. Do đó, không phải tất cả giám khảo đều ủng hộ “ngay từ đầu”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 3: Utzon’s knowledge of boats gave him the idea for parts of the Opera House.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><em data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Kiến thức về tàu thuyền của Utzon đã cho ông ý tưởng cho các phần của Nhà hát Opera.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng trong bài:</strong> Đoạn 3, câu 2-3: “Though he had never visited the site, he used his <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">maritime background</strong> to study naval charts… His early exposure to <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">shipbuilding</strong> provided the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"182\">inspiration for the design of the roof</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Maritime background” (nền tảng hàng hải) và “shipbuilding” (đóng tàu) tương đương với “knowledge of boats”. Bài đọc xác nhận rằng kiến thức này đã truyền cảm hứng (gave idea) cho thiết kế mái vòm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 4: Utzon was impressed by the opera houses he had seen in Mexico.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><em data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Utzon đã bị ấn tượng bởi các nhà hát opera mà ông đã thấy ở Mexico.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng trong bài:</strong> Đoạn 3, câu cuối: “From his travels to Mexico, he had the idea of placing his building on a wide horizontal platform.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc ông đi du lịch Mexico và lấy ý tưởng về cái bệ (platform) từ đó. Tuy nhiên, bài <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">không hề nhắc đến</strong> việc ông có xem “nhà hát opera” (opera houses) nào ở Mexico hay không, hay ông có bị ấn tượng bởi các nhà hát đó không. Ông có thể đã xem đền đài Maya (thường có bệ lớn), nhưng bài viết không nói rõ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 5: Utzon changed his designs in the 1960s after construction began.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><em data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Utzon đã thay đổi thiết kế của mình vào những năm 1960 sau khi việc xây dựng bắt đầu.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng trong bài:</strong> Đoạn 4, câu 1: “Construction of the platform began in 1959, and throughout the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">early 1960s Utzon amended his original designs</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc xây dựng bắt đầu năm 1959. Đoạn văn nói rõ trong những năm đầu thập niên 60, Utzon đã “amended” (sửa đổi/thay đổi) thiết kế gốc. Thông tin hoàn toàn trùng khớp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 6: Seidler defended Utzon’s role as architect.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><em data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Seidler đã bảo vệ vai trò kiến trúc sư của Utzon.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng trong bài:</strong> Đoạn 5, câu 4: “…protests through the streets led by prominent architect <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">Harry Seidler</strong> and others, <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">demanding Utzon be reinstated</strong> as architect.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Harry Seidler đã dẫn đầu các cuộc biểu tình yêu cầu phục chức (reinstated) cho Utzon. Hành động này chính là bảo vệ (defended) vai trò của Utzon.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 7: Utzon went back to Australia in 1973 for the opening of the Opera House.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><em data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Utzon đã quay lại Úc vào năm 1973 cho lễ khai trương Nhà hát Opera.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng trong bài:</strong> Đoạn 5, câu 5-6: “…Utzon was not reinstated and left Australia in 1966. <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">He never returned</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định rõ ràng rằng sau khi rời Úc năm 1966, ông “không bao giờ quay trở lại” (He never returned). Do đó, việc nói ông quay lại năm 1973 là sai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f0327ecc-9051-4f0b-ab0e-f53210a0f248', 'd847081f-29da-424a-bd52-986753b7892e', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<p>Complete the table below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Sydney Opera House</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Final cost</strong>: $ {102 million}<br />
<strong>Construction</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>A large platform acting as a base for the building</li>
<li>Concrete panels used to make ‘shells’, which are covered in tiles</li>
<li>Over a million tiles from {Sweden}</li>
<li>{granite} from Australia covering the outside walls</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Use</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>More than 1,500 performances annually</li>
<li>{4|four} performing arts companies have their home base at the Opera House</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Outside</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>A large {forecourt} at the foot of a wide staircase</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Alterations</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>A colonnade was added in 2006</li>
<li>Openings made the {harbor | harbour} visible from foyers</li>
</ul>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\">8. Final cost: <strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">$102 million</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 5, câu cuối: “…having cost <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">$102 million</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết đối chiếu giữa dự toán ban đầu (7 triệu đô) và chi phí thực tế khi hoàn thành là 102 triệu đô.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">9. Over a million tiles from <strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">Sweden</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu 2: “The ‘shells’ are covered with 1,056,006 white and cream-coloured tiles manufactured in a factory in <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">Sweden</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Con số 1,056,006 tương ứng với “over a million” (hơn 1 triệu), và nơi sản xuất gạch là Thụy Điển (Sweden).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">10. <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"3\">Granite</strong> from Australia covering the outside walls</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu cuối: “…the building’s exterior is mostly clad with <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">granite</strong> quarried in Australia.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “exterior” tương ứng với “outside walls” (tường bên ngoài). Vật liệu được khai thác tại Úc để ốp bên ngoài là đá hoa cương (granite).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">11. <strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"3\">4 / Four</strong> performing arts companies have their home base at the Opera House</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 8, câu cuối: “…including the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">four</strong> resident companies: Opera Australia, the Australian Ballet…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Resident companies” (các công ty thường trú) đồng nghĩa với việc họ lấy nơi đây làm “home base” (căn cứ/trụ sở chính). Có 4 công ty như vậy được liệt kê.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">12. A large <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">forecourt</strong> at the foot of a wide staircase</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9, câu cuối: “There is a sizeable outdoor <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">forecourt</strong> from which people ascend to the main entrance. The steps… are nearly 100 metres wide.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Sizeable” đồng nghĩa với “large”. “Steps” tương ứng với “staircase” (cầu thang). Khu vực sân phía trước nằm dưới chân cầu thang chính là “forecourt”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">13. Openings made the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">harbor / harbour</strong> visible from foyers</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 10, câu 3: “…enabled theatre patrons to see the <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">harbour</strong> for the first time from the theatre foyers.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc thêm các ô cửa kính lớn (glass openings) đã cho phép khán giả nhìn thấy bến cảng (harbour) từ sảnh đợi (foyers). <em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">Lưu ý: Bạn có thể viết theo kiểu Anh (harbour) hoặc kiểu Mỹ (harbor) đều được chấp nhận.</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('34dfcd79-e043-403a-a95a-2d3ab3cdcfd8', '3ca9ce22-9869-42ee-9ed8-fb9a32e77cfb', 'fillup', 'Questions 14–18', '<p>Complete the summary below</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>The thylacine was a dog-like animal which had a {striped} coat and was carnivorous. It was originally spread widely throughout the mainland of {Australia} but started to disappear from that area around {12 million years} ago because of climate change.</p>
<p>In the end, thylacines were found only on the island of {Tasmania} until the arrival of {Europeans} with their farming practices brought about a drastic reduction in thylacine numbers. The last one is thought to have died in Hobart Zoo in 1936.</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. striped</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"It was given the name ‘tiger’ because it had <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">striped fur</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc mô tả loài này được gọi là \"hổ\" vì có bộ lông vằn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">striped coat/fur</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Australia</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...many types of thylacine roamed across <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">Australia</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Loài hổ Tasmania này ban đầu phân bố rộng rãi khắp lục địa <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">Australia</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. 12 million years</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"But when a period of climate change cooled Australia about <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">12 million years ago</strong>, the numbers of these ancient thylacines began to <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"151\">decline</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Do biến đổi khí hậu, số lượng loài này bắt đầu giảm sút (bắt đầu biến mất dần) từ khoảng <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">12 triệu năm</strong> trước.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Tasmania</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...so that <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">Tasmania</strong>, a large island to the south of Australia, became the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">last remaining place</strong> where thylacines existed.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cuối cùng, nơi duy nhất còn loài này sinh sống là hòn đảo <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">Tasmania</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Europeans</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"They ruled the island’s animal life unchallenged until <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">Europeans</strong> – with sheep, dogs... seem to have brought about their <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">extinction</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự xuất hiện của người <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">Châu Âu</strong> cùng các tập quán chăn nuôi (sheep, dogs) đã dẫn đến sự sụt giảm nghiêm trọng và tuyệt chủng của loài này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('201616e4-8dfd-474f-8609-1f4a05d747b2', '3ca9ce22-9869-42ee-9ed8-fb9a32e77cfb', 'matrix', 'Questions 19-24', NULL, '<p>Match each statement with the correct person, A, В, C or D.</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, A, В, C or D, in boxes 19-24.</p>', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "There is no longer any hope of finding a surviving Tasmanian tiger.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "It would be preferable not to disturb any surviving Tasmanian tigers.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Many who claim to have seen Tasmanian tigers are not objective witnesses.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Expert estimates of numbers needed to ensure species survival may be inaccurate.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "There is a great deal of international interest in Tasmanian tiger stories.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Some fresh evidence provided by a visitor to Tasmania seems credible.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Hans Naarding", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Randolph Rose", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "David Pemberton", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Nick Mooney", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. There is no longer any hope of finding a surviving Tasmanian tiger. — {B. Randolph Rose}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Randolph Rose... says that he dreamed of seeing a thylacine, but is now <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">convinced that his dream will go unfulfilled</strong>... Take it from me, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">tiger is gone</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Randolph Rose khẳng định giấc mơ nhìn thấy hổ Tasmania của ông sẽ không thành hiện thực và chốt lại rằng \"con hổ đã biến mất rồi\". Điều này tương ứng với việc không còn hy vọng tìm thấy chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. It would be preferable not to disturb any surviving Tasmanian tigers. — {A. Hans Naarding}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Naarding believes that any discovery... would be rather <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">pointless</strong>... If there are thylacines out there, they are <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">better off right where they are</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hans Naarding cho rằng nếu chúng còn tồn tại thì tốt nhất là cứ để chúng ở yên đó (\"better off right where they are\"), tức là không nên làm phiền hay quấy rầy chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Many who claim to have seen Tasmanian tigers are not objective witnesses. — {D. Nick Mooney}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Mooney says... Many other sightings have been <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">hoaxes</strong>, and many sincere seekers are <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">victims of obsession</strong>. ‘It is a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">blind optimism</strong>...’\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nick Mooney nhận định nhiều người báo cáo nhìn thấy hổ là do ám ảnh hoặc lạc quan mù quáng, dẫn đến việc họ không còn nhìn nhận một cách khách quan (không đặt câu hỏi đó là con gì mà khẳng định ngay đó là hổ Tasmania).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Expert estimates of numbers needed to ensure species survival may be inaccurate. — {C. David Pemberton}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Dr David Pemberton... states that, <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">despite scientific thinking that a relatively large number of animals required</strong> to sustain a population, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">Florida panther is down to a dozen or so... and is still ticking along</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> David Pemberton đưa ra ví dụ về loài báo Florida vẫn tồn tại dù số lượng cực thấp để phản bác lại quan điểm khoa học thông thường về số lượng tối thiểu để duy trì bầy đàn. Điều này có nghĩa là các ước tính của chuyên gia có thể không chính xác (inaccurate).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. There is a great deal of international interest in Tasmanian tiger stories. — {A. Hans Naarding}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"‘When the news broke,’ said Naarding, ‘I was <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">besieged by television crews, including four or five from Japan, and others from the United Kingdom, Germany, New Zealand and South America</strong>.’\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc các đài truyền hình từ khắp nơi trên thế giới (Nhật, Anh, Đức...) đổ xô đến tìm Naarding sau khi ông báo cáo nhìn thấy hổ chính là minh chứng cho sự quan tâm quốc tế (international interest).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Some fresh evidence provided by a visitor to Tasmania seems credible. — {D. Nick Mooney}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"It was Mooney who was first consulted... about the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">authenticity of new digital photographic images</strong>... allegedly taken by a <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">tourist</strong>... this particular account... amount to one of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">most convincing cases</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nick Mooney đánh giá những tấm ảnh kỹ thuật số mới từ một khách du lịch (tourist/visitor) là một trong những bằng chứng thuyết phục (convincing/credible) nhất mà ông từng thấy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('073fc5d1-6113-475a-9169-1fe258bc935b', 'c1d994c3-f090-4530-add8-9cfe3a340b2d', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21 and 22', '', '<p data-start="54" data-end="82">Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="84" data-end="150">Which <strong>TWO </strong>opinions about the Luddites do the students express?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "Their actions were ineffective"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "They are still influential today"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "They have received unfair criticism"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "They were proved right"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "Their attitude is understandable"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('21e8f854-7467-446f-b983-682925855a63', '3ca9ce22-9869-42ee-9ed8-fb9a32e77cfb', 'radio', 'Questions 25-26', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers.</p>', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "the capture of the tiger."}, {"content": "an extensive follow up."}, {"content": "many other sightings."}, {"content": "the death of the tiger."}], "question": " Hans Naarding’s sighting of a Tasamanian tiger resulted in"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "new animal species are still evolving."}, {"content": "animals can possess surprising physical characteristics."}, {"content": "species of sea animals can be saved from extinction."}, {"content": "opinions regarding extinction of animal species can be mistaken."}], "question": "The example of the coelacanth is used to show that"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. B (an extensive follow up)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Government and private search parties <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">combed the region</strong>, but no further sightings were made.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sau khi Naarding nhìn thấy hổ Tasmania, một cuộc tìm kiếm quy mô lớn (extensive follow up) đã được chính phủ và các tổ chức tư nhân thực hiện để rà soát khu vực.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. D (opinions regarding extinction of animal species can be mistaken)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"The strange fish known as <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">coelacanth</strong>... was <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">thought to have died out</strong> with the dinosaurs 700 million years ago <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">until a specimen was dragged to the surface</strong>... in 1938.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ví dụ về cá vây tay (coelacanth) được dùng để chứng minh rằng quan điểm về sự tuyệt chủng của một loài có thể bị sai (tưởng tuyệt chủng rồi nhưng thực ra vẫn còn sống).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e1c6d031-e2a4-48e8-b777-cfef2cff4082', '2eca7386-054f-41ea-94ef-da768169cb00', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<div class="relative basis-auto flex-col -mb-(--composer-overlap-px) pb-(--composer-overlap-px) [--composer-overlap-px:28px] grow flex" data-voice-floating-orb-focus-background="">
<div class="flex flex-col text-sm">
<div class="qMYqUG_convSearchResultHighlightRoot">
<div class="" data-turn-id-container="6c6e4899-f6a6-4d54-84f9-154bafb7544f" data-is-intersecting="true">
<section class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto R6Vx5W_threadScrollVars scroll-mb-[calc(var(--scroll-root-safe-area-inset-bottom,0px)+var(--thread-response-height))] scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" data-turn-id="6c6e4899-f6a6-4d54-84f9-154bafb7544f" data-turn-id-container="6c6e4899-f6a6-4d54-84f9-154bafb7544f" data-testid="conversation-turn-154" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" data-conversation-screenshot-content="">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" tabindex="0" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="37bd0062-ebc8-4714-b68b-d6a7cd8a3f4e" data-turn-start-message="true" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling">
<p data-section-id="1i6hwlk" data-start="28" data-end="57">Complete the notes below.</p>
<p data-start="58" data-end="109">Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-section-id="uw4fxu" data-start="111" data-end="147"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Job details from employment agency</strong></span></p>
<p data-section-id="ynpk8i" data-start="149" data-end="157"><strong>Role          </strong>{receptionist}</p>
<strong>Location    </strong>Fordham {Medical} Centre
<p data-start="239" data-end="277">                   {Chastons} Road, Fordham</p>
<h3 data-section-id="13g2adx" data-start="279" data-end="296">Work involves</h3>
<ul data-start="297" data-end="454">
<li data-section-id="a8rw6l" data-start="297" data-end="321">dealing with enquiries</li>
<li data-section-id="1w2j9zw" data-start="322" data-end="377">making {appointments} and reorganising them</li>
<li data-section-id="1joq58a" data-start="378" data-end="429">maintaining the internal {database}</li>
<li data-section-id="f6o70w" data-start="430" data-end="454">general administration</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-section-id="14esvje" data-start="456" data-end="472">Requirements</h3>
<ul data-start="473" data-end="573">
<li data-section-id="58xiw1" data-start="473" data-end="511">{experience} (essential)</li>
<li data-section-id="16edvrh" data-start="512" data-end="556">a calm and {confident} manner</li>
<li data-section-id="b8pvxw" data-start="557" data-end="573">good IT skills</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-section-id="adrvke" data-start="575" data-end="596">Other information</h3>
<ul data-start="597" data-end="787" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-section-id="1ox0yhn" data-start="597" data-end="670">a {temporary} job – further opportunities may be available</li>
<li data-section-id="1xiyark" data-start="671" data-end="739">hours: 7.45 a.m. to {1.15} p.m. Monday to Friday</li>
<li data-section-id="1307p40" data-start="740" data-end="787" data-is-last-node="">{parking} is available onsite</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
