', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cc7c3f7c-5510-477d-b19c-0529628ed72c', '24ed850f-141e-4e4f-8cb8-bd684e972215', 'fillup', 'Question 26-30', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> tor each answer</p>
<p>Presentations should last for {30-40 minutes}</p>
<p>(Plus time for {questions and discussion} )</p>
<p>Sources of information<br>– Bibliography<br>– Library books<br>– {Journal}<br>– {Internet}</p>
<p>For the presentations, use:<br>– Overahead projector<br>– Whiteboard<br>– {Photocopy}</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9c9bffea-0b5e-4b19-ae3d-76f4d9865fc6', 'f4889774-b4e5-4e07-a1af-55519f9cb6d1', 'fillup', 'Question 31-40', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Monarch Butterflies</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Hibernation</strong></p>
<p>– Butterfly species adopt different hibernation patterns during their life cycle. Butterflies named ‘Banded Hair Freak’ hibernate in the form of an {egg}.<br>– A species called ‘Dapple White’ accumulates {energy} from the larval stage.<br>– Slow metabolism can help them to sort out some problems in winter. A substance is produced in the blood which may function as {anti-freeze}.<br>– There are few predators because they can only survive in {warm} weather.</p>
<p><strong>Migration</strong></p>
<p>– Monarch butterflies move to {North America} in winter. To avoid cold temperature, they migrate to the south in large groups.<br>– The survival skill can help them last for up to {6 months} during a long journey.<br>– Monarch butterflies fly in the daytime and stay in {trees} during the night.<br>– Researchers found out that they orient by flying along the {rivers}. They also follow the direction of the {sun} for navigational aid.<br>– During migration, they mainly feed on flowers and cannot reproduce. Recently the annual arrival of the monarchs can be a good interest to {tourists} in the region.</p>', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 4</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student:</strong> <span class=\"citation-739 citation-740 citation-741 citation-742 citation-end-742\">We were required to do the investigation regarding survival strategies of particular animals, and I chose to study how the butterflies will do for survival when cold weather and food shortage could easily influence their life cyc</span><span class=\"citation-739 citation-740 citation-741 citation-end-741\">le. I concentrated on a number of main strategie</span><span class=\"citation-739 citation-740 citation-end-740\">s butterflies adopt to handle these harsh conditi</span><span class=\"citation-739 citation-end-739\">ons: hibernation and migration.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><span class=\"citation-738 citation-end-738\">First, let&#8217;s talk about the hibernation, which means a long-term sleep in which an animal&#8217;s metabolism slows to conserve strengt</span><span class=\"\">h.</span><span class=\"\"> Various butterfly species have formed different patterns of hibernation at continuous periods of their life cycle.</span><span class=\"\"> For example,</span><span class=\"\"> the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"263\">Banded Hair Streak</strong><span class=\"\"> hardly hibernates in its full-grown adult form,</span><span class=\"\"> but as an </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"340\">(31) egg</strong><span class=\"\">.</span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><span class=\"\">And another species,</span><span class=\"\"> the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">Dappled White</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> breathes during the winter in a crystallized stage,</span><span class=\"\"> and during this time,</span><span class=\"\"> it&#8217;s able to draw on the </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">(32) <span class=\"citation-737\">energy</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-737 citation-end-737\"> it stimulated earlier on in its larval stage.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-736\">Though the slowing of the metabolism in hibernation functions with many of the difficulties faced in winter, it can&#8217;t prevent them all. In addition, some butterflies have extra plans for survival. For instance, they develop a substance in their blood, usually in glycerol or sorbitol, which serves as </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"301\"><span class=\"citation-736 citation-end-736\">(</span>33) antifreeze</strong><span class=\"\"> (hoặc </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"323\">anti-freeze</strong><span class=\"\">),</span></span><span class=\"\"> thereby adding extra resistance against lower temperatures.</span><span class=\"\"> Actually,</span><span class=\"\"> there is a positive side to the cold weather:</span><span class=\"\"> fewer predators exist to cause problems.</span><span class=\"\"> This is because they&#8217;re mainly active in </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"535\">(34) warm</strong></span><span class=\"\"> weather.</span></p>\n<hr class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7\" />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student:</strong> <span class=\"citation-735\">So now let&#8217;s move on to the second type of survival strategy the butterflies used in winter: migration. That means moving to regions with a more suitable </span><span class=\"citation-733 citation-734 citation-735 citation-end-735\">environment. I&#8217;m going to start this topic with a detailed study about particular cases of migratory species: the</span><span class=\"citation-733 citation-734 citation-end-734\"> Monarch butterfly.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><span class=\"citation-731 citation-732 citation-end-732\">Many butterfly species found in various zones of the world migrate, like</span><span class=\"citation-731 citation-end-731\"> the Red Admiral, a British butterfly which winters in North Afri</span><span class=\"\">ca.</span><span class=\"\"> But the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">Monarch</strong><span class=\"\"> butterfly is the sole example to do this in </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"201\">(35) North America</strong></span><span class=\"\"> at any stage of the life cycle.</span><span class=\"\"> The </span><span class=\"citation-729 citation-730 citation-end-730\">Monarch cannot survive in the low winter temperatures, so when it gets cold, the Monarchs begin to gather in huge groups and fly south. They can travel up to three and a half thousand miles.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><span class=\"citation-727 citation-728 citation-end-728\">But only the last summer generation of Monarchs migrate. Norm</span><span class=\"citation-727 citation-end-727\">al generations only live for a maximum of 10 days; in fact, the last migration generation, as reported</span><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> lives for </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"175\">(36) six months</strong><span class=\"\"> (hoặc </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">6 months</strong><span class=\"\">),</span></span><span class=\"\"> which enables them to take such a long journey.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><span class=\"\">These huge teams of migrating Monarchs only fly during daylight hours,</span><span class=\"\"> and at night they usually have a rest in </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">(37) trees</strong><span class=\"\">,</span></span><span class=\"\"> again often in vast groups.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><span class=\"\">Research is now being done into what encourages them to reach the destination.</span> It has been known for years that they find their way on the journey by following<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">(38) rivers</strong></span></span>, and there are a few of these along the migratory route. However, the new research indicates that they may also treat the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"294\">(39) sun</strong></span> as a navigational aid.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><span class=\"\">During this time they are able to feed,</span><span class=\"\"> mainly from a type of flower called milkweed,</span> but they are not able to reproduce during this period.<span class=\"\"> The Monarchs land in their lineage to a particular region in Mexico known as the Sierra Chincua.</span><span class=\"\"> The Monarchs are anticipated with great interest within the region,</span><span class=\"\"> and over recent years,</span><span class=\"\"> their annual arrival has gained great popularity among </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"384\">(40) tourists</strong></span><span class=\"\">.</span> However, their habitat has been increasingly threatened.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('235b0fec-8161-47bc-be87-c7a197bc2eae', '45eb14aa-3495-43c8-a788-fb342b5e068f', 'radio', 'Questions 31–35', '', '<p data-start="673" data-end="717">Choose the correct letter, <strong data-start="700" data-end="716">A, B, C or D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. we need to work for longer periods at a time."}, {"option_text": "B. more intense activity should be encouraged"}, {"option_text": "C. the human body requires regular downtime"}, {"option_text": "D. overwork may lead to ill health"}], "question": "The writers mention ultradian rhythms to support their argument that"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. they do well at work when they are optimistic"}, {"option_text": "B. negative emotions provide an opportunity to improve relationships"}, {"option_text": "C. consciously taking the right attitude can eliminate destructive emotions"}, {"option_text": "D. a pessimistic approach prevents them from reaching their potential"}], "question": "According to the writers, many people are surprised to discover that"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. should be detailed in order to produce the best results"}, {"option_text": "B. help us more than the recipient"}, {"option_text": "C. should have a financial component"}, {"option_text": "D. encourage others to work harder"}], "question": "The writers believe that expressions of appreciation"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. putting into words what is most important to them"}, {"option_text": "B. asking what their colleagues would think of a given action"}, {"option_text": "C. anticipating how they would react in a given situation"}, {"option_text": "D. considering what kind of behaviour offends them"}], "question": "According to the writers, people can discover what their values are by"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. those in an extremely stressful working environment"}, {"option_text": "B. those who want to change but are still in control of their situation"}, {"option_text": "C. those where the head of the company is committed to change"}, {"option_text": "D. those that place the greatest value on innovation"}], "question": "The most suitable candidates to undertake the writers’ programmes would be"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. C — the human body requires regular downtime.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">““Ultradian rhythms” are 90- to 120-minute cycles during which we move from a high-energy state into a physiological trough. Toward the end of each cycle, our systems crave recovery.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả đưa ra khái niệm \"nhịp sinh học ultradian\" để chứng minh rằng sau mỗi chu kỳ 90-120 phút, cơ thể sẽ rơi vào vùng đáy năng lượng và khao khát được phục hồi (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"176\">crave recovery</em>). Điều này hỗ trợ cho luận điểm là cơ thể con người cần những khoảng thời gian nghỉ ngơi, phục hồi định kỳ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"299\">requires regular downtime</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. D — a pessimistic approach prevents them from reaching their potential.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“What surprises them is that they''re not able to perform well when they''re feeling any other way [other than positive].”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"A pessimistic approach\" (cách tiếp cận bi quan / cảm xúc tiêu cực) tương ứng với cụm \"feeling any other way [other than positive]\". \"Prevents them from reaching their potential\" (ngăn họ đạt được tiềm năng/làm việc tốt) tương ứng với cụm \"not able to perform well\". Việc mọi người bất ngờ (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"303\">surprises them</em>) khi biết mình không thể làm việc tốt nếu không có cảm xúc tích cực chứng minh cho đáp án D.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. A — should be detailed in order to produce the best results.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Another ritual that fuels positive emotions is expressing appreciation, an action that seems to be as beneficial to the giver as the receiver and the fuller and more precise it is, the higher the impact.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ ra rằng việc thể hiện sự công nhận, biết ơn càng đầy đủ và chính xác bao nhiêu (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">the fuller and more precise it is</em>) thì tác động của nó càng cao bấy nhiêu (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"179\">the higher the impact</em>). Cụm <em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"207\">\"fuller and more precise\"</em> đồng nghĩa với cụm từ cần sự chi tiết, cụ thể (<strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"280\">should be detailed</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. D — considering what kind of behaviour offends them.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“By describing what they can''t stand, people unintentionally divulge what they stand for.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả tìm hiểu giá trị cốt lõi của một người bằng cách hỏi về những phẩm chất khiến họ khó chịu nhất ở người khác (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">qualities you find most off-putting</em>). Việc mô tả những thứ họ không thể chịu đựng được (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"217\">what they can''t stand</em>) chính là việc xem xét loại hành vi nào xúc phạm, làm tổn thương họ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"308\">considering what kind of behaviour offends them</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. B — those who want to change but are still in control of their situation.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Optimal candidates for our programs are feeling enough pain to be eager for new solutions but not so much that they''re completely overwhelmed.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đối tượng tối ưu nhất cho chương trình (<strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">optimal candidates</strong>) là những người đã mệt mỏi và khao khát tìm giải pháp mới (<em data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">eager for new solutions / want to change</em>) nhưng ở mức độ vừa phải chứ không đến mức bị đánh gục hoàn toàn (<em data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"237\">not completely overwhelmed</em>), tức là họ vẫn còn khả năng kiểm soát tình hình của mình (<strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"323\">still in control of their situation</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c40f904b-71f4-47dc-b8c9-1d2a64dcf61a', '45eb14aa-3495-43c8-a788-fb342b5e068f', 'matching', 'Questions 36–40', '', '<p data-start="2312" data-end="2375">Complete each sentence with the correct ending, <strong data-start="2360" data-end="2367">A–H</strong>, below.</p>
<p data-start="2377" data-end="2452">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="2403" data-end="2410">A–H</strong></p>', 'matching_sentence_endings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A he acknowledges other people’s achievements and discusses life outside the workplace"}, {"optionText": "B he gets a sense of accomplishment early in the day"}, {"optionText": "C he has gone against the company culture"}, {"optionText": "D he could immediately adopt a positive technique to help him cope with pressure"}, {"optionText": "E he could not believe the favourable results."}, {"optionText": "F he no longer needs to complete challenging tasks at a certain time of day"}, {"optionText": "G he could complete challenging tasks more quickly"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Gary Faro has found that after changing his diet, exercise and sleeping patterns", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": "Through working with the writers, Fuji Nishida discovered", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "Ben Jenkins has established a ritual in which", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "Dan Cluna decided to spend time in another part of the building so that", "correctAnswer": "G"}, {"questionPart": "Jean Luc Desseyn found that by changing the time that he responds to emails", "correctAnswer": "B"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. F — he no longer needs to complete challenging tasks at a certain time of day.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">““I used to schedule tough projects for the morning, when I knew that I would be more focused,” Faro says. “I don''t have to do that anymore because I find that I''m just as focused now at 5 pm as I am at 8 am.””</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Gary Faro chia sẻ sau khi thay đổi lối sống, ông không còn phải cố định xếp các dự án khó nhằn vào buổi sáng nữa (<em data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">I don''t have to do that anymore</em>), vì lúc 5 giờ chiều ông vẫn tập trung tốt như 8 giờ sáng. Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc ông không cần hoàn thành các nhiệm vụ thách thức vào một thời điểm cố định trong ngày nữa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"337\">no longer needs to complete challenging tasks at a certain time of day</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. D — he could immediately adopt a positive technique to help him cope with pressure.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The breathing exercise taught him worked straight away: he no longer desired cigarettes. It wasn''t the smoking that had relieved his stress but the relaxation from deep inhalation and exhalation.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông qua bài tập thở sâu do tác giả hướng dẫn, Fuji Nishida đã có thể áp dụng một kỹ thuật hiệu quả ngay lập tức (<em data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">worked straight away / immediately adopt</em>) giúp ông giải tỏa căng thẳng thay thế cho việc hút thuốc khi gặp áp lực (<strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"242\">cope with pressure</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. A — he acknowledges other people’s achievements and discusses life outside the workplace.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Ben Jenkins... recognizes their accomplishments and talks with them about themselves and their aspirations, rather than their immediate work responsibilities.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghi thức của Ben Jenkins trong các buổi tối với đội ngũ là công nhận thành tựu của họ (<em data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">recognizes their accomplishments / acknowledges other people''s achievements</em>) và trò chuyện về bản thân, nguyện vọng của họ thay vì áp lực công việc hiện tại (<em data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"258\">discusses life outside the workplace</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. G — he could complete challenging tasks more quickly.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Dan Cluna, at Wachovia, now leaves his desk to go into a conference room whenever a task requires concentration and finishes reports in a third of the time they used to require.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dan Cluna chọn cách rời bàn làm việc để sang phòng họp khi cần tập trung, giúp ông hoàn thành các báo cáo chỉ trong 1/3 thời gian so với trước đây (<em data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">in a third of the time</em>). Tức là ông có thể xử lý các nhiệm vụ nhanh chóng hơn nhiều (<strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"245\">complete challenging tasks more quickly</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. B — he gets a sense of accomplishment early in the day.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“He now dedicates the first hour every day to the most important task and often emerges at 10 am feeling he''s already had a productive day.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thay vì check email ngay khi đến văn phòng, Jean Luc Desseyn đổi sang dành giờ đầu tiên cho nhiệm vụ quan trọng nhất, giúp ông có cảm giác mình đã có một ngày làm việc rất hiệu quả ngay từ lúc 10 giờ sáng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"218\">gets a sense of accomplishment early in the day / feeling he''s already had a productive day</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cfb93da7-44b5-4752-9277-6ead16a49f8c', 'dc40091f-7a6f-4bf7-8dfb-60d11948bbbe', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information,<strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information,<strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries, the British East India Company faced a lot of competition."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Before 1800, cargo size was the most important consideration for the East India Company"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "At best, voyages of the East Indiamen to China and back took nearly two years to complete."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Before 1834, voyages to and from China were considered to be highly dangerous"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "After 1834, the ships which had served the East India Company stopped being used for commercial purposes."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the nineteenth century, British drinkers preferred tea made from mature leaves to that made from younger leaves.+"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. In the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries, the British East India Company faced a lot of competition. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_5de9fe4efc5b0522-28\" data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<span class=\"citation-129\">During the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries, the </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\"><span class=\"citation-129\">British East India Company had the monopoly on trade</span></strong><span class=\"citation-129\"> with China and India. This meant that </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"165\"><span class=\"citation-129\">because no rival could legally import tea or other goods</span></strong><span class=\"citation-129 citation-end-129\"> from these countries at this ti<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>me...”</em></p>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi khẳng định vào thế kỷ XVII - XVIII, công ty Đông Ấn Anh phải đối mặt với rất nhiều sự cạnh tranh (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">faced a lot of competition</em>). Tuy nhiên, bài đọc ghi rõ công ty nắm giữ sự độc quyền (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">monopoly</em>) và không có bất kỳ đối thủ nào (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"245\">no rival</em>) có thể nhập khẩu hợp pháp. Vì thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"329\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Before 1800, cargo size was the most important consideration for the East India Company. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Instead, <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">its priority was to minimise costs by carrying as much as possible on each ship</strong>. This meant that its ships – known as East Indiamen – were enormous, strong and very slow.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Priority\" (sự ưu tiên hàng đầu) đồng nghĩa với \"the most important consideration\" (yếu tố cân nhắc quan trọng nhất). Việc ưu tiên chở nhiều hàng nhất có thể trên mỗi chuyến tàu (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"191\">carrying as much as possible</em>) chính là tập trung vào kích thước/khối lượng hàng hóa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"276\">cargo size</strong>). Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"299\">TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. At best, voyages of the East Indiamen to China and back took nearly two years to complete. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...so <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">even with favourable sailing conditions, the round trip lasted almost two years</strong>, and if anything went wrong it could take a lot longer.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"At best\" (Trong điều kiện tốt nhất) tương ứng với cụm \"even with favourable sailing conditions\" (ngay cả với điều kiện căng buồm thuận lợi). \"Nearly two years\" (gần hai năm) đồng nghĩa với \"almost two years\". Chuyến đi khứ hồi đi và về (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"250\">voyages to China and back</strong>) tương ứng với cụm từ \"the round trip\". Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"326\">TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Before 1834, voyages to and from China were considered to be highly dangerous. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2 &amp; 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“...and if anything went wrong it could take a lot longer.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nhắc đến việc nếu có sự cố xảy ra (<em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">if anything went wrong</em>) thì chuyến đi sẽ mất nhiều thời gian hơn rất nhiều, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">hoàn toàn không có thông tin</strong> nào đánh giá hay xem xét liệu các chuyến hải trình này có cực kỳ nguy hiểm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"244\">highly dangerous</strong>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. After 1834, the ships which had served the East India Company stopped being used for commercial purposes. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“However, by 1834 the company had lost its trading monopolies... Having no more use for its great ships, <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">the company sold them off, and many were bought by merchants or their captains, who continued to plough the seas between Britain and China</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói sau năm 1834, các tàu này ngừng được sử dụng cho mục đích thương mại (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">stopped being used for commercial purposes</em>). Nhưng bài đọc viết công ty đã bán lại tàu cho các thương nhân và thuyền trưởng (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"219\">bought by merchants</em>), và họ <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"247\">tiếp tục ra khơi buôn bán</strong> giữa Anh và Trung Quốc (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"297\">continued to plough the seas</em>). Vì thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"375\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. In the nineteenth century, British drinkers preferred tea made from mature leaves to that made from younger leaves. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...because consumers in Britain in the nineteenth century <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">believed that the fresher and earlier-picked the tea, the better the resulting drink</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói người Anh thích trà làm từ lá già/lá trưởng thành (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">mature leaves</em>) hơn lá non (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">younger leaves</em>). Nhưng bài đọc viết người tiêu dùng tin rằng trà càng tươi (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">fresher</em>) và được hái càng sớm (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"209\">earlier-picked</em> - tức là lá non đầu vụ) thì càng ngon. Vì thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"310\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e37856c1-4d61-4237-8d33-6ead14758059', 'dc40091f-7a6f-4bf7-8dfb-60d11948bbbe', 'fillup', 'Questions 7–13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 7–13 on your answer sheet. </p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong> Clipper races</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>The ships</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Clipper ships were first used for trading by American merchants.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The ships were remarkable for the number of {sails} they had.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The performance of British tea clippers was particularly affected when there were {storms} at sea.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The races</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>It was in a ship called {Challenger} that the British first competed successfully against the Americans.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Richard Green’s ship arrived two days ahead of its competitor.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Competition increased when additional Chinese trading {ports} were established.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Merchants were occasionally in such a hurry that they failed to complete the {paperwork} before leaving China.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>At the end of their journey, the ships needed the help of {tugs}.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The rewards</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The crews were motivated by both {money} and their enthusiasm for the competition. </p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. sails — {The ships were remarkable for the number of sails they had.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“These vessels were fast and slender, with a narrow hull that was deeper at the back than at the front, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">masses of sails on tall masts</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"remarkable for the number of...\" (gây chú ý vì số lượng của cái gì) đồng nghĩa với từ \"masses of...\" (hàng khối/rất nhiều cái gì). Thứ mà những con tàu này có rất nhiều chính là những cánh buồm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"215\">sails</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. storms — {The performance of British tea clippers was particularly affected when there were storms at sea.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“...they had a narrower beam than their American equivalents, <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">making them less powerful during storms but faster in calmer weather</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Particularly affected\" (bị ảnh hưởng đặc biệt/trở nên yếu thế hơn) tương ứng với cụm \"less powerful\" (ít quyền năng hơn/yếu hơn). Tình huống trên biển gây ra sự ảnh hưởng này chính là những trận bão (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"213\">storms</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Challenger — {It was in a ship called Challenger that the British first competed successfully against the Americans.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Then in 1851 a British shipowner, Richard Green, <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">built the aptly named clipper Challenger with the stated intention of beating the American ships</strong>... In the event, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"188\">British ship beat its rival</strong> to London by two days...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Competed successfully against\" (cạnh tranh thành công/đánh bại) tương ứng với từ \"beating / beat its rival\". Tên con tàu mang lại chiến thắng đầu tiên này cho người Anh là <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"185\">Challenger</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. ports — {Competition increased when additional Chinese trading ports were established.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“But even without the Anglo-American rivalry, the competitive spirit continued. <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">It was really ignited when new ports were opened up for trade in China</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Competition increased / ignited\" (sự cạnh tranh tăng lên/bùng cháy mạnh mẽ). Nguyên nhân là do có thêm nhiều thương cảng mới được mở ra (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">ports</strong>). Chữ <em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">additional</em> đồng nghĩa với từ <em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"191\">new</em> trong ngữ cảnh này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. paperwork — {Merchants were occasionally in such a hurry that they failed to complete the paperwork before leaving China.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“As a result, tea could be loaded on board earlier and fresher, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">the clippers could set off in late May or early June – sometimes not even taking time to fill out the official paperwork</strong> – racing back to Britain...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"In such a hurry\" (vội vã đến mức) tương ứng với cụm \"not even taking time\" (thậm chí không thèm tốn thời gian). \"Failed to complete\" (không hoàn thành/bỏ qua) đồng nghĩa với việc không điền vào (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">not fill out</strong>). Thứ bị bỏ qua ở đây là giấy tờ thủ tục hành chính (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"274\">paperwork</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. tugs — {At the end of their journey, the ships needed the help of tugs.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Once there [at the River Thames], <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">they would be towed by tugs up the river and into the docks</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"At the end of their journey\" (vào cuối cuộc hành trình/khi về tới đích). Lúc này, các tàu cần sự trợ giúp/được kéo đi (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">towed</em>) bởi những chiếc tàu kéo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">tugs</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. money — {The crews were motivated by both money and their enthusiasm for the competition.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The cargo of the winning ship could earn a premium... and so the captain and crew were rewarded... <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">But the races were about more than just money: the crews... delighted in competing against each other. Without their enthusiasm, the races would never have happened</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đề bài liệt kê hai yếu tố thúc đẩy/tạo động lực (<em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">motivated</em>) cho các thủy thủ: một là sự hào hứng thi đấu (<em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">enthusiasm for the competition</em>), và yếu tố còn lại (nằm trước chữ <em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"184\">and</em>) chính là tiền bạc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">money</strong> / <em data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"216\">rewarded / earn a premium</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5d50c975-c105-43c7-b5cc-1181955b2fdd', 'd60f9097-f454-4b9a-9480-70077e7b2580', 'radio', 'Questions 31–35', '', '<p data-start="673" data-end="717">Choose the correct letter, <strong data-start="700" data-end="716">A, B, C or D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. we need to work for longer periods at a time."}, {"option_text": "B. more intense activity should be encouraged"}, {"option_text": "C. the human body requires regular downtime"}, {"option_text": "D. overwork may lead to ill health"}], "question": "The writers mention ultradian rhythms to support their argument that"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. they do well at work when they are optimistic"}, {"option_text": "B. negative emotions provide an opportunity to improve relationships"}, {"option_text": "C. consciously taking the right attitude can eliminate destructive emotions"}, {"option_text": "D. a pessimistic approach prevents them from reaching their potential"}], "question": "According to the writers, many people are surprised to discover that"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. should be detailed in order to produce the best results"}, {"option_text": "B. help us more than the recipient"}, {"option_text": "C. should have a financial component"}, {"option_text": "D. encourage others to work harder"}], "question": "The writers believe that expressions of appreciation"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. putting into words what is most important to them"}, {"option_text": "B. asking what their colleagues would think of a given action"}, {"option_text": "C. anticipating how they would react in a given situation"}, {"option_text": "D. considering what kind of behaviour offends them"}], "question": "According to the writers, people can discover what their values are by"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. those in an extremely stressful working environment"}, {"option_text": "B. those who want to change but are still in control of their situation"}, {"option_text": "C. those where the head of the company is committed to change"}, {"option_text": "D. those that place the greatest value on innovation"}], "question": "The most suitable candidates to undertake the writers’ programmes would be"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. C — the human body requires regular downtime.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">““Ultradian rhythms” are 90- to 120-minute cycles during which we move from a high-energy state into a physiological trough. Toward the end of each cycle, our systems crave recovery.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả đưa ra khái niệm \"nhịp sinh học ultradian\" để chứng minh rằng sau mỗi chu kỳ 90-120 phút, cơ thể sẽ rơi vào vùng đáy năng lượng và khao khát được phục hồi (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"176\">crave recovery</em>). Điều này hỗ trợ cho luận điểm là cơ thể con người cần những khoảng thời gian nghỉ ngơi, phục hồi định kỳ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"299\">requires regular downtime</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. D — a pessimistic approach prevents them from reaching their potential.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“What surprises them is that they''re not able to perform well when they''re feeling any other way [other than positive].”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"A pessimistic approach\" (cách tiếp cận bi quan / cảm xúc tiêu cực) tương ứng với cụm \"feeling any other way [other than positive]\". \"Prevents them from reaching their potential\" (ngăn họ đạt được tiềm năng/làm việc tốt) tương ứng với cụm \"not able to perform well\". Việc mọi người bất ngờ (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"303\">surprises them</em>) khi biết mình không thể làm việc tốt nếu không có cảm xúc tích cực chứng minh cho đáp án D.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. A — should be detailed in order to produce the best results.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Another ritual that fuels positive emotions is expressing appreciation, an action that seems to be as beneficial to the giver as the receiver and the fuller and more precise it is, the higher the impact.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ ra rằng việc thể hiện sự công nhận, biết ơn càng đầy đủ và chính xác bao nhiêu (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">the fuller and more precise it is</em>) thì tác động của nó càng cao bấy nhiêu (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"179\">the higher the impact</em>). Cụm <em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"207\">\"fuller and more precise\"</em> đồng nghĩa với cụm từ cần sự chi tiết, cụ thể (<strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"280\">should be detailed</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. D — considering what kind of behaviour offends them.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“By describing what they can''t stand, people unintentionally divulge what they stand for.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả tìm hiểu giá trị cốt lõi của một người bằng cách hỏi về những phẩm chất khiến họ khó chịu nhất ở người khác (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">qualities you find most off-putting</em>). Việc mô tả những thứ họ không thể chịu đựng được (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"217\">what they can''t stand</em>) chính là việc xem xét loại hành vi nào xúc phạm, làm tổn thương họ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"308\">considering what kind of behaviour offends them</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. B — those who want to change but are still in control of their situation.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Optimal candidates for our programs are feeling enough pain to be eager for new solutions but not so much that they''re completely overwhelmed.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đối tượng tối ưu nhất cho chương trình (<strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">optimal candidates</strong>) là những người đã mệt mỏi và khao khát tìm giải pháp mới (<em data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">eager for new solutions / want to change</em>) nhưng ở mức độ vừa phải chứ không đến mức bị đánh gục hoàn toàn (<em data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"237\">not completely overwhelmed</em>), tức là họ vẫn còn khả năng kiểm soát tình hình của mình (<strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"323\">still in control of their situation</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fc940b28-e9d8-4536-a462-847c05563e95', 'd60f9097-f454-4b9a-9480-70077e7b2580', 'matching', 'Questions 36–40', '', '<p data-start="2312" data-end="2375">Complete each sentence with the correct ending, <strong data-start="2360" data-end="2367">A–H</strong>, below.</p>
<p data-start="2377" data-end="2452">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="2403" data-end="2410">A–H</strong></p>', 'matching_sentence_endings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A he acknowledges other people’s achievements and discusses life outside the workplace"}, {"optionText": "B he gets a sense of accomplishment early in the day"}, {"optionText": "C he has gone against the company culture"}, {"optionText": "D he could immediately adopt a positive technique to help him cope with pressure"}, {"optionText": "E he could not believe the favourable results."}, {"optionText": "F he no longer needs to complete challenging tasks at a certain time of day"}, {"optionText": "G he could complete challenging tasks more quickly"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Gary Faro has found that after changing his diet, exercise and sleeping patterns", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": "Through working with the writers, Fuji Nishida discovered", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "Ben Jenkins has established a ritual in which", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "Dan Cluna decided to spend time in another part of the building so that", "correctAnswer": "G"}, {"questionPart": "Jean Luc Desseyn found that by changing the time that he responds to emails", "correctAnswer": "B"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. F — he no longer needs to complete challenging tasks at a certain time of day.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">““I used to schedule tough projects for the morning, when I knew that I would be more focused,” Faro says. “I don''t have to do that anymore because I find that I''m just as focused now at 5 pm as I am at 8 am.””</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Gary Faro chia sẻ sau khi thay đổi lối sống, ông không còn phải cố định xếp các dự án khó nhằn vào buổi sáng nữa (<em data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">I don''t have to do that anymore</em>), vì lúc 5 giờ chiều ông vẫn tập trung tốt như 8 giờ sáng. Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc ông không cần hoàn thành các nhiệm vụ thách thức vào một thời điểm cố định trong ngày nữa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"337\">no longer needs to complete challenging tasks at a certain time of day</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. D — he could immediately adopt a positive technique to help him cope with pressure.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The breathing exercise taught him worked straight away: he no longer desired cigarettes. It wasn''t the smoking that had relieved his stress but the relaxation from deep inhalation and exhalation.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông qua bài tập thở sâu do tác giả hướng dẫn, Fuji Nishida đã có thể áp dụng một kỹ thuật hiệu quả ngay lập tức (<em data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">worked straight away / immediately adopt</em>) giúp ông giải tỏa căng thẳng thay thế cho việc hút thuốc khi gặp áp lực (<strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"242\">cope with pressure</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. A — he acknowledges other people’s achievements and discusses life outside the workplace.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Ben Jenkins... recognizes their accomplishments and talks with them about themselves and their aspirations, rather than their immediate work responsibilities.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghi thức của Ben Jenkins trong các buổi tối với đội ngũ là công nhận thành tựu của họ (<em data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">recognizes their accomplishments / acknowledges other people''s achievements</em>) và trò chuyện về bản thân, nguyện vọng của họ thay vì áp lực công việc hiện tại (<em data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"258\">discusses life outside the workplace</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. G — he could complete challenging tasks more quickly.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Dan Cluna, at Wachovia, now leaves his desk to go into a conference room whenever a task requires concentration and finishes reports in a third of the time they used to require.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dan Cluna chọn cách rời bàn làm việc để sang phòng họp khi cần tập trung, giúp ông hoàn thành các báo cáo chỉ trong 1/3 thời gian so với trước đây (<em data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">in a third of the time</em>). Tức là ông có thể xử lý các nhiệm vụ nhanh chóng hơn nhiều (<strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"245\">complete challenging tasks more quickly</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. B — he gets a sense of accomplishment early in the day.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“He now dedicates the first hour every day to the most important task and often emerges at 10 am feeling he''s already had a productive day.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thay vì check email ngay khi đến văn phòng, Jean Luc Desseyn đổi sang dành giờ đầu tiên cho nhiệm vụ quan trọng nhất, giúp ông có cảm giác mình đã có một ngày làm việc rất hiệu quả ngay từ lúc 10 giờ sáng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"218\">gets a sense of accomplishment early in the day / feeling he''s already had a productive day</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ebd0af15-5cd2-43f0-a96e-bd58a4a7a0ef', '2f7de8da-a469-418d-a7d4-9a16517adeca', 'matrix', 'Questions 31–36', '', '<p data-start="581" data-end="636">Match each statement with the correct subject, <strong data-start="628" data-end="635">A–G</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="638" data-end="713">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="664" data-end="671">A–G</strong></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of Subjects", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The artist clearly hoped that we would share his admiration of this subject", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "The artist aims to give a general impression of this subject rather than a detailed one", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Someone’s personal experience may make them consider a painting of this subject unpleasant", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "The way in which this subject was once portrayed was factually wrong", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "The painting is well known for the effort the artist put into creating a very accurate picture of this subject", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "People may like a painting of this subject for a reason that is external to the painting", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "village scene", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "alpine scene", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Rubens’s son", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Dürer’s mother", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "hare", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "elephant", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "horses", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. C — Rubens’s son</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“When the great Flemish painter Rubens made a drawing of his young son, he was surely proud of his good looks, and wanted us, too, to delight in the child''s appearance.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Share his admiration of this subject\" (chia sẻ sự ngưỡng mộ/yêu thích đối với đối tượng này) tương ứng với cụm từ Rubens tự hào về vẻ ngoại hình của con trai và muốn người xem cũng phải thích thú, vui sướng khi nhìn vào diện mạo của đứa trẻ (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"255\">wanted us, too, to delight in...</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. F — elephant</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Indeed Rembrandt gave us the feel of the elephant''s wrinkly skin with just a few lines of his chalk.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Give a general impression... rather than a detailed one\" (tạo ra một ấn tượng chung/khái quát hơn là một bức vẽ chi tiết) tương ứng với kỹ thuật vẽ con voi (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">elephant</em>) của Rembrandt: chỉ dùng vài nét phấn (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"218\">just a few lines</em>) nhưng vẫn lột tả được cảm giác của làn da nhăn nheo, ít chi tiết hơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"306\">fewer details</em>) so với thông thường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. B — alpine scene</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“...when we instinctively turn away from a magnificent picture of an alpine scene because we dislike climbing, that we should search our mind for the reason for the aversion which spoils a pleasure...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Personal experience\" (trải nghiệm cá nhân - ở đây là việc ghét leo núi) làm cho người xem cảm thấy một bức tranh phong cảnh núi Alps (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">alpine scene</em>) là không dễ chịu, không thích thú (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"196\">unpleasant</em>), khiến họ theo bản năng phải quay mặt đi chỗ khác (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"259\">instinctively turn away / aversion</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. G — horses</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“It was only the development of photography which proved that horses simply do not gallop in that way.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Portrayed was factually wrong\" (được khắc họa sai lệch so với thực tế khoa học) tương ứng với việc các thế hệ họa sĩ trước đây luôn vẽ dáng ngựa (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">horses</em>) phi nước đại duỗi thẳng chân, một cách di chuyển hoàn toàn sai thực tế mà chỉ có nhiếp ảnh mới chứng minh được.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. E — hare</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Dürer''s watercolour study of a hare is one of the most famous examples of this loving patience.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Effort... creating a very accurate picture\" (sự nỗ lực tạo ra một bức tranh rất chính xác) tương ứng với cụm từ \"loving patience\" (sự kiên nhẫn tràn đầy tình yêu) và \"faithful rendering of the visible world... every tiny detail is carefully recorded\" khi Dürer vẽ con thỏ rừng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"291\">hare</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. A — village scene</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“We may like a painting of a village scene because it reminds us of home.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"A reason that is external to the painting\" (một lý do nằm ngoài bức tranh) chính là việc bức tranh vẽ cảnh làng quê (<em data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">village scene</em>) gợi nhắc người xem nhớ về ngôi nhà, quê hương của họ (<em data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">reminds us of home</em>), chứ không phải họ thích vì kỹ thuật hay màu sắc của chính bức tranh đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7e815213-99bf-4d28-9187-1c68b791f3d9', '2f7de8da-a469-418d-a7d4-9a16517adeca', 'fillup', 'Questions 37–40', '<p data-start="1452" data-end="1479">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p data-start="1481" data-end="1539">Choose <strong data-start="1488" data-end="1505">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="a3d18275-615c-4d17-b76e-1a0131b8fc62" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Beauty and expression</strong></span>
<p data-start="1628" data-end="1926">Differences in tastes and standards of beauty make it difficult to judge a painting. Dürer’s painting of his mother is considered significant because it is a {truthful} representation of her age and situation. However, we may need to overcome an initial reaction of {shock} when we see it.</p>
<p data-start="1928" data-end="2271" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">In order to judge the facial expressions of people portrayed in a painting, we need to become familiar with the methods that the artist has used when creating the painting. While some of us are affected by the portrayal of a facial expression that we can {understand} without much effort, others prefer expressions that require {interpretation}.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. truthful — {...because it is a truthful representation of her age...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“His truthful study of old age may give us a shock which makes us turn away from it - and yet, if we fight against that first reaction we may be richly rewarded.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn tóm tắt mô tả bức vẽ người mẹ của Dürer là một sự khắc họa có tính chất như thế nào đối với tuổi tác của bà. Từ khóa tính từ đứng trước danh từ cần điền xuất hiện trong bài là <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"193\">truthful</strong> (<em data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">his truthful study of old age</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. shock — {...overcome an initial reaction of shock when we see it.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“His truthful study of old age may give us a shock which makes us turn away from it...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Overcome an initial reaction\" (vượt qua một phản ứng ban đầu) tương ứng với cụm từ \"fight against that first reaction\". Phản ứng tâm lý ban đầu mà bức tranh này mang lại cho người xem chính là một sự chấn động, sửng sốt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"234\">shock</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. understand — {...facial expression that we can understand without much effort...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Some people like an expression - perhaps of suffering or of compassion - which they can readily understand, and which therefore moves them profoundly.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Without much effort\" (không tốn nhiều công sức) đồng nghĩa với trạng từ dễ dàng (<em data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">readily</em>). Người xem thường bị tác động bởi những biểu cảm gương mặt mà họ có thể dễ dàng thấu hiểu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">understand</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. interpretation — {...others prefer expressions that require interpretation.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“...so some of us would rather look at paintings or sculptures which are open to interpretation.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngược lại với nhóm người trên, một số người xem khác lại ưa chuộng những tác phẩm có biểu cảm không quá rõ ràng, đòi hỏi sự suy đoán hoặc nhiều cách diễn giải khác nhau từ phía người xem (<strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"200\">interpretation</strong> / <em data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"217\">open to interpretation</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ab530c72-b3b0-4336-8093-658bdd158db6', '32055caa-ec08-450e-931c-30d547c92bba', 'matrix', 'Questions 1-6', '', '<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p>Choose the appropriate letter, <strong>A</strong>-<strong>H</strong></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "categorizations of fish by swimming speed", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "an example of fish capable of maintaining fast swimming for a long time", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "how fish control stability", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "frequency of the muscle movement of fish", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a mechanical model of fish skeleton", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "energy storage devices in a fish", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. G — {categorizations of fish by swimming speed}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“From these studies, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">we can broadly categorise fish into four groups: “sneakers”</strong>...; <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">“stayers”</strong>...; <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">“sprinters”</strong>...; and <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">“crawlers”</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Categorizations\" (các cách phân loại/nhóm) trùng khớp hoàn toàn với cụm \"broadly categorise fish into four groups\". Đoạn G liệt kê chi tiết 4 nhóm cá dựa trên đặc điểm tốc độ bơi và sức bền của chúng (gồm sneakers, stayers, sprinters, crawlers).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. H — {an example of fish capable of maintaining fast swimming for a long time}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...and anglers have recorded <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">speeds in excess of 40 mph over longer periods for several species of tuna</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Maintaining fast swimming for a long time\" (duy trì bơi nhanh trong một thời gian dài) tương ứng với cụm từ \"speeds in excess of 40 mph over longer periods\" (tốc độ vượt quá 40 dặm/giờ trong các khoảng thời gian dài hơn). Ví dụ cụ thể (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"249\">an example</em>) được đưa ra ở đây chính là loài cá ngừ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"301\">tuna</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. E — {how fish control stability}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“But it must be emphasized that the swimming movements are produced by the whole of the muscular body... <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">Their main function [of the fins] is to control the stability and direction of the fish</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Control stability\" (kiểm soát độ ổn định/thăng bằng). Đoạn E giải thích cơ chế này phụ thuộc vào bộ phận nào trên cơ thể cá, đó chính là chức năng cốt lõi của các vây (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"181\">fins</em>): khi nước đi qua cơ thể, cá dùng vây để tạo lực đẩy về hướng nó muốn đi nhằm giữ thăng bằng và định hướng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. C — {frequency of the muscle movement of fish}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The muscles on each side of the spine contract... causing a wave-like movement to pass down the body... <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">The frequency of the waves varies from about 50/min in the dogfish to 170/min in the mackerel</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Muscle movement\" (chuyển động của cơ) trong đoạn C được mô tả là sự co bóp tạo thành chuyển động dạng sóng (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">wave-like movement</em>). Đoạn này cung cấp thông tin cụ thể về tần suất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"190\">frequency</strong>) của các sóng cơ này biến thiên từ 50 lần/phút ở cá nhám góc cho đến 170 lần/phút ở cá thu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. B — {a mechanical model of fish skeleton}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Fish rely on their <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">skeleton</strong>, fins, and muscles to move. The primary function of the skeleton is to aid movement of other parts. <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">Their skull acts as a fulcrum and their vertebrae act as levers</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"A mechanical model\" (một mô hình cơ học) được tác giả xây dựng bằng cách ví các bộ phận trong hệ xương của cá (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">skeleton</strong>) giống như các cấu kiện cơ khí công nghiệp: hộp sọ đóng vai trò như một điểm tựa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"215\">fulcrum</strong>) và các đốt sống đóng vai trò như những chiếc đòn bẩy (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"278\">levers</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. D — {energy storage devices in a fish}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_bfecbb9c4946d150-37\" data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“...the much smaller areas at the roots of the fins and in a strip along the centre of each flan<span class=\"citation-518 citation-519\">k comprise </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\"><span class=\"citation-518 citation-519\">red muscle. The red muscle receives a good supply of blood and contains ampler quantities of fat and glycogen, the storage form of glucose, which is used for most day-to-day swimming movements</span></strong><span class=\"citation-518 citation-519\">.”</span></em><span class=\"citation-518 citation-519 citation-end-519\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-518 citation-end-518\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"2\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_bfecbb9c4946d150-38\" data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-516 citation-517\">Giải thích:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-516 citation-517 citation-end-517\"> \"Energy stora<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"3\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-516 citation-end-516\">ge devices\" (các phân tử/thiết bị lưu trữ năng l<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"4\"><!----></sup></span>ượng) được định danh cụ thể trong đoạn D là các mô cơ đỏ (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">red muscle</em>), nơi tích trữ một lượng lớn chất béo (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"181\">fat</em>) và glycogen - dạng tích trữ của đường glucose (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"233\">the storage form of glucose</em>) để cung cấp năng lượng cho cá bơi lội hàng ngày.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('592dbd4c-7049-44c9-a310-ed76255256ef', '32055caa-ec08-450e-931c-30d547c92bba', 'fillup', 'Questions 7-10', '<p>The diagram below gives information about fish fins and their purposes.</p>
<p>Complete the diagram with <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each blank</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="563" height="355" loading="lazy"></p>
<p><em>Write your answers in boxes <strong>7-10</strong> on your answer sheet.</em></p>
<p>{forward thrust }</p>
<p>{rolling and yawing }</p>
<p>{Pectoral and pelvic }</p>
<p>{slows and stops }</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. forward thrust — {Tail fin contributes to forward thrust}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">The tail fin</strong>, in its final lash may <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">contribute as much as 40 per cent of the forward thrust</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sơ đồ chỉ vào vây đuôi (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">Tail fin</em>) và hỏi về công dụng của nó. Bài đọc chỉ rõ cú quẫy đuôi cuối cùng của vây đuôi có thể đóng góp tới 40% lực đẩy về phía trước (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"172\">forward thrust</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. rolling and yawing — {Median fins control rolling and yawing movements}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">The median fins</strong>, that is, the dorsal, anal and ventral fins, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">control the rolling and yawing movements of the fish</strong>...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sơ đồ chỉ vào nhóm vây giữa (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">Median fins</em> bao gồm vây lưng, vây hậu môn, vây bụng) và hỏi chức năng. Bài đọc khẳng định nhóm vây này kiểm soát các chuyển động lắc lư cuộn tròn và lệch hướng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"202\">rolling and yawing</strong> movements) của cá bằng cách tăng diện tích bề mặt thẳng đứng đối lưu với nước.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Pectoral and pelvic — {Pectoral and pelvic fins act as hydroplanes}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">The paired fins, pectoral and pelvic act as hydroplanes</strong> and control the pitch of the fish...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sơ đồ hỏi tên của các cặp vây (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">paired fins</em>) đóng vai trò như những chiếc cánh ngầm (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">hydroplanes</em>). Bài đọc gọi tên trực tiếp hai cặp vây này là vây ngực và vây chậu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"177\">Pectoral and pelvic</strong>). Do đề bài cho phép điền tối đa 3 từ (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"236\">NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</em>) nên việc điền cả cụm tên nối bằng chữ <em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"300\">and</em> là hoàn toàn chuẩn xác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. slows and stops — {Fins are the means by which the fish slows and stops}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The paired fins are also the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">means by which the fish slows down and stops</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sơ đồ hỏi về chức năng bổ sung của cặp vây ngực/chậu nằm ở phía trước. Bài đọc viết chúng là phương tiện giúp cá giảm tốc độ và dừng lại. Từ cần điền là <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"165\">slows and stops</strong> (bỏ bớt trạng từ <em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"198\">down</em> từ cụm <em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"210\">slows down</em> trong bài đọc để khớp hoàn hảo với cấu trúc ngữ pháp và giới hạn từ của sơ đồ).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c89e9ebe-f471-439b-91f0-9ab394a4b309', '32055caa-ec08-450e-931c-30d547c92bba', 'fillup', 'Questions 11-13', '<p>Complete the summary below using <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each blank.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Two types of muscles are involved in fish swimming. The majority of a fish’s body comprises the {white muscle} , and the red muscle is found only at the roots of the fins and in a strip along the centre of each flank. For most of its routine movements, the fish uses a lot of its {fats and glycogen} saved in body, and white muscle is mostly used for short-term, fast swimming, such as escaping from {predator}</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. white muscle — {The majority of a fish’s body comprises the white muscle}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">bulk of a fish’s body is composed of the so-called white muscle</strong>, while the much smaller areas at the roots of the fins...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ \"The majority of a fish''s body\" (phần lớn cơ thể cá) đồng nghĩa với cụm \"The bulk of a fish''s body\". Cụm từ \"comprises\" (bao gồm/cấu thành bởi) tương ứng với \"is composed of\". Loại cơ chiếm phần lớn cơ thể cá chính là cơ trắng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"247\">white muscle</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. fats and glycogen — {the fish uses a lot of its fats and glycogen saved in body}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The red muscle receives a good supply of blood and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">contains ampler quantities of fat and glycogen, the storage form of glucose, which is used for most day-to-day swimming movements</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Routine movements\" (các chuyển động thường nhật/hàng ngày) đồng nghĩa với \"day-to-day swimming movements\". \"Saved in body\" (được lưu trữ/tích trữ trong cơ thể) tương ứng với từ \"storage form / contains\". Chất dinh dưỡng được tích trữ dùng cho hoạt động này là chất béo và glycogen (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"295\">fat and glycogen</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><em data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lưu ý ngữ pháp:</em> Để câu tóm tắt chuẩn chỉnh hơn, ta có thể viết dạng số nhiều là <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">fats and glycogen</strong> để hòa hợp với danh từ số nhiều ở ngữ cảnh chung, hệ thống vẫn quét đúng từ khóa gốc trong bài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. predator — {...such as escaping from predator}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_ff8530834883f9fc-42\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<span class=\"citation-559\">However, this huge auxiliary power pack carried by a fish is of crucial significance </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\"><span class=\"citation-559 citation-end-559\">if the life of the fish is threatened-by a predator, for instance-because it enables the fish to swim rapidly away from dang<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>er</strong>.”</em></p>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Escaping from\" (trốn thoát khỏi) đồng nghĩa với cụm từ \"swim rapidly away from danger\" (bơi thật nhanh thoát khỏi nguy hiểm). Tình huống nguy hiểm đe dọa mạng sống của cá được bài đọc đưa ra ví dụ (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"211\">for instance / such as</em>) chính là từ một kẻ săn mồi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"263\">predator</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d88e1140-400f-4d2a-9fa3-98190c19c4d4', '48f287f8-b916-47dc-87b1-cc4beee3f084', 'matrix', 'Questions 31–36', '', '<p data-start="581" data-end="636">Match each statement with the correct subject, <strong data-start="628" data-end="635">A–G</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="638" data-end="713">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="664" data-end="671">A–G</strong></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of Subjects", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The artist clearly hoped that we would share his admiration of this subject", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "The artist aims to give a general impression of this subject rather than a detailed one", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Someone’s personal experience may make them consider a painting of this subject unpleasant", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "The way in which this subject was once portrayed was factually wrong", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "The painting is well known for the effort the artist put into creating a very accurate picture of this subject", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "People may like a painting of this subject for a reason that is external to the painting", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "village scene", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "alpine scene", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Rubens’s son", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Dürer’s mother", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "hare", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "elephant", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "horses", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. C — Rubens’s son</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“When the great Flemish painter Rubens made a drawing of his young son, he was surely proud of his good looks, and wanted us, too, to delight in the child''s appearance.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Share his admiration of this subject\" (chia sẻ sự ngưỡng mộ/yêu thích đối với đối tượng này) tương ứng với cụm từ Rubens tự hào về vẻ ngoại hình của con trai và muốn người xem cũng phải thích thú, vui sướng khi nhìn vào diện mạo của đứa trẻ (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"255\">wanted us, too, to delight in...</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. F — elephant</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Indeed Rembrandt gave us the feel of the elephant''s wrinkly skin with just a few lines of his chalk.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Give a general impression... rather than a detailed one\" (tạo ra một ấn tượng chung/khái quát hơn là một bức vẽ chi tiết) tương ứng với kỹ thuật vẽ con voi (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">elephant</em>) của Rembrandt: chỉ dùng vài nét phấn (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"218\">just a few lines</em>) nhưng vẫn lột tả được cảm giác của làn da nhăn nheo, ít chi tiết hơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"306\">fewer details</em>) so với thông thường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. B — alpine scene</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“...when we instinctively turn away from a magnificent picture of an alpine scene because we dislike climbing, that we should search our mind for the reason for the aversion which spoils a pleasure...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Personal experience\" (trải nghiệm cá nhân - ở đây là việc ghét leo núi) làm cho người xem cảm thấy một bức tranh phong cảnh núi Alps (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">alpine scene</em>) là không dễ chịu, không thích thú (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"196\">unpleasant</em>), khiến họ theo bản năng phải quay mặt đi chỗ khác (<em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"259\">instinctively turn away / aversion</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. G — horses</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“It was only the development of photography which proved that horses simply do not gallop in that way.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Portrayed was factually wrong\" (được khắc họa sai lệch so với thực tế khoa học) tương ứng với việc các thế hệ họa sĩ trước đây luôn vẽ dáng ngựa (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">horses</em>) phi nước đại duỗi thẳng chân, một cách di chuyển hoàn toàn sai thực tế mà chỉ có nhiếp ảnh mới chứng minh được.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. E — hare</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Dürer''s watercolour study of a hare is one of the most famous examples of this loving patience.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Effort... creating a very accurate picture\" (sự nỗ lực tạo ra một bức tranh rất chính xác) tương ứng với cụm từ \"loving patience\" (sự kiên nhẫn tràn đầy tình yêu) và \"faithful rendering of the visible world... every tiny detail is carefully recorded\" khi Dürer vẽ con thỏ rừng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"291\">hare</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. A — village scene</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“We may like a painting of a village scene because it reminds us of home.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"A reason that is external to the painting\" (một lý do nằm ngoài bức tranh) chính là việc bức tranh vẽ cảnh làng quê (<em data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">village scene</em>) gợi nhắc người xem nhớ về ngôi nhà, quê hương của họ (<em data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">reminds us of home</em>), chứ không phải họ thích vì kỹ thuật hay màu sắc của chính bức tranh đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2e026e21-7e27-4098-9f74-b3edc8d76c81', '48f287f8-b916-47dc-87b1-cc4beee3f084', 'fillup', 'Questions 37–40', '<p data-start="1452" data-end="1479">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p data-start="1481" data-end="1539">Choose <strong data-start="1488" data-end="1505">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="a3d18275-615c-4d17-b76e-1a0131b8fc62" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Beauty and expression</strong></span>
<p data-start="1628" data-end="1926">Differences in tastes and standards of beauty make it difficult to judge a painting. Dürer’s painting of his mother is considered significant because it is a {truthful} representation of her age and situation. However, we may need to overcome an initial reaction of {shock} when we see it.</p>
<p data-start="1928" data-end="2271" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">In order to judge the facial expressions of people portrayed in a painting, we need to become familiar with the methods that the artist has used when creating the painting. While some of us are affected by the portrayal of a facial expression that we can {understand} without much effort, others prefer expressions that require {interpretation}.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. truthful — {...because it is a truthful representation of her age...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“His truthful study of old age may give us a shock which makes us turn away from it - and yet, if we fight against that first reaction we may be richly rewarded.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn tóm tắt mô tả bức vẽ người mẹ của Dürer là một sự khắc họa có tính chất như thế nào đối với tuổi tác của bà. Từ khóa tính từ đứng trước danh từ cần điền xuất hiện trong bài là <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"193\">truthful</strong> (<em data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">his truthful study of old age</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. shock — {...overcome an initial reaction of shock when we see it.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“His truthful study of old age may give us a shock which makes us turn away from it...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Overcome an initial reaction\" (vượt qua một phản ứng ban đầu) tương ứng với cụm từ \"fight against that first reaction\". Phản ứng tâm lý ban đầu mà bức tranh này mang lại cho người xem chính là một sự chấn động, sửng sốt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"234\">shock</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. understand — {...facial expression that we can understand without much effort...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Some people like an expression - perhaps of suffering or of compassion - which they can readily understand, and which therefore moves them profoundly.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Without much effort\" (không tốn nhiều công sức) đồng nghĩa với trạng từ dễ dàng (<em data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">readily</em>). Người xem thường bị tác động bởi những biểu cảm gương mặt mà họ có thể dễ dàng thấu hiểu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">understand</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. interpretation — {...others prefer expressions that require interpretation.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“...so some of us would rather look at paintings or sculptures which are open to interpretation.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngược lại với nhóm người trên, một số người xem khác lại ưa chuộng những tác phẩm có biểu cảm không quá rõ ràng, đòi hỏi sự suy đoán hoặc nhiều cách diễn giải khác nhau từ phía người xem (<strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"200\">interpretation</strong> / <em data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"217\">open to interpretation</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2d5550a9-16b2-4de8-aee6-238d0b7eb204', '29ce77b9-0eb4-45e4-9325-0b9ddef8e5c2', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–8', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>History of the bar code</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>1948 – 1952</strong></p>
<p>Methods of recording information automatically were developed by Silver and Woodland.</p>
<p>1st system:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li>
<p>used ultraviolet light and a special type of {ink}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>problems: expensive and not permanent</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>2nd system:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li>
<p>based on technology used in Morse Code and also for the {soundtracks} of films</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>problems: {unreliable} and expensive</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>1970s</strong></p>
<p>Availability of cheaper {lasers} meant scanning technology spread more widely</p>
<p>Problem: lack of {standardization} in code systems</p>
<p>April 1973: committee agreed on one universal product code (UPC)</p>
<p>June 1974: pack of Juicy Fruit chewing gum sold with bar-code scanner</p>
<p>Advantages of bar-code system:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li>
<p>supermarkets needed to spend less on labour</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>the {speed} of checkouts increased</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>doing inventories was much cheaper</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Present day</strong></p>
<p>Users of bar codes include:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li>
<p>retail companies</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>airlines</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>staff in hospitals</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>participants in {marathons}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>scientists studying {bees}</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. used ultraviolet light and a special type of {ink}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">ink</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn B, dòng 2.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Their first idea was to use patterns printed with an <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">ink</strong> that would glow under ultraviolet light…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hệ thống đầu tiên của Silver và Woodland sử dụng một loại mực đặc biệt có khả năng phát sáng dưới tia cực tím.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. based on technology used in Morse Code and also for the {soundtracks} of films</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">soundtracks</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn B, dòng 7.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…using elements from two established technologies: Morse code… and the method used to record <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"109\">soundtracks</strong> in movies.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hệ thống mã vạch tuyến tính thứ hai được xây dựng dựa trên sự kết hợp giữa mã Morse và công nghệ ghi âm dải âm thanh trong phim ảnh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. problems: {unreliable} and expensive</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">unreliable</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn B, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the fact that their scanning equipment was rather <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">unreliable</strong>, made the idea a non-starter at that time.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vào thời điểm đó, chi phí cao và thiết bị quét hoạt động không ổn định (không đáng tin cậy) khiến ý tưởng chưa thể thực hiện.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Availability of cheaper {lasers} meant scanning technology spread more widely</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">lasers</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn C, dòng 1.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Scanning systems made little progress until the 1970s, when <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">lasers</strong> became affordable.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự xuất hiện của tia laser với giá thành rẻ vào những năm 1970 đã tạo bước ngoặt cho công nghệ quét mã vạch phát triển.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Problem: lack of {standardization} in code systems</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">standardization</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn C, dòng 2-3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…each with its own proprietary code, but there was no <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">standardization</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trước khi có UPC, mỗi cửa hàng/nhà máy dùng một loại mã riêng, dẫn đến việc thiếu sự quy chuẩn hóa chung.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. the {speed} of checkouts increased</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">speed</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn G, dòng 6.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “These included checking out items at twice the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">speed</strong> compared to using traditional equipment…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một trong những lợi thế lớn nhất là tốc độ thanh toán tại quầy tăng gấp đôi so với phương pháp truyền thống.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. participants in {marathons}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">marathons</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn H, dòng 4.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Runners in major <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">marathons</strong> set off with bar codes on their vests…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngày nay, vận động viên chạy marathon cũng sử dụng mã vạch trên áo để theo dõi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. scientists studying {bees}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">bees</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn H, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Tiny bar codes have even been mounted on <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">bees</strong> by researchers to track their movements.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các nhà khoa học thậm chí còn gắn mã vạch siêu nhỏ lên loài ong để nghiên cứu di chuyển của chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('56f92917-6fbd-4639-923a-e7502bcbad5a', '29ce77b9-0eb4-45e4-9325-0b9ddef8e5c2', 'radio', 'Questions 9–13', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Bernard Silver was invited to develop a system for capturing product information by the president of a food chain."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A committee set up in the 1970s said bar codes should be easy to use and not too expensive."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Alan Haberman disagreed with government policies on business matters."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Many grocery outlets were unable to afford the necessary scanning equipment."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The advantages of the new bar-code scanner took some time to be accepted by users."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Bernard Silver was invited to develop a system for capturing product information by the president of a food chain.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn A nói rằng Bernard Silver chỉ tình cờ <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">nghe lỏm (overheard)</strong> cuộc trò chuyện giữa vị chủ tịch chuỗi thực phẩm và một giáo sư. Vị chủ tịch nài nỉ giáo sư nghiên cứu, giáo sư từ chối, sau đó Silver mới kể lại cho Woodland.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Silver không được “mời” mà tự mình chủ động nghiên cứu sau khi nghe trộm thông tin.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. A committee set up in the 1970s said bar codes should be easy to use and not too expensive.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn C liệt kê các nguyên tắc của ủy ban: mã vạch phải đọc được từ mọi góc độ (dễ dùng cho thu ngân) và nhãn phải <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">“cheap and easy to print”</strong> (rẻ và dễ in).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông tin này hoàn toàn khớp với các tiêu chí về tính tiện dụng và chi phí thấp mà ủy ban đưa ra.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Alan Haberman disagreed with government policies on business matters.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn D chỉ trích lời Alan Haberman rằng doanh nghiệp không cần chính phủ phải “đẩy” họ đi đúng hướng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">“business didn’t need the government to shove them…”</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Haberman nói về việc doanh nghiệp có thể tự hợp tác mà không cần chính phủ can thiệp, nhưng bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">không nói</strong> ông có “bất đồng với các chính sách của chính phủ” về các vấn đề kinh doanh khác hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Many grocery outlets were unable to afford the necessary scanning equipment.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn E đề cập rằng chi phí đầu tư là rất lớn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">$200,000 cho mỗi cửa hàng</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nêu con số đầu tư đắt đỏ, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">không cung cấp thông tin</strong> về việc có nhiều cửa hàng “không đủ khả năng chi trả” hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. The advantages of the new bar-code scanner took some time to be accepted by users.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn G dòng 1: “The advantages of the system were <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">not clear immediately</strong>, as wholesalers, retailers and customers <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">remained suspicious</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lợi ích không được thấy ngay lập tức vì người dùng vẫn còn nghi ngờ (thậm chí nghi bị theo dõi), mãi sau này các lợi ích mới trở nên rõ ràng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
SET session_replication_role = DEFAULT;
